1
00:00:31,035 --> 00:00:33,078
- It's day two today.
- Day two.

2
00:00:33,078 --> 00:00:34,680
It's only day two

3
00:00:34,680 --> 00:00:37,349
and we're still the rookies, guys.

4
00:00:37,349 --> 00:00:38,684
No, it's day one.

5
00:00:38,684 --> 00:00:39,852
[Flustered rambling]
No.

6
00:00:39,852 --> 00:00:41,387
- No.
- It's still day one.

7
00:00:41,387 --> 00:00:44,857
The goal is to climb to the top in five days

8
00:00:44,857 --> 00:00:48,060
and get our own dish on the menu.

9
00:00:48,060 --> 00:00:50,696
- We didn't actually go in as real rookies.
- Right.

10
00:00:50,696 --> 00:00:54,099
- Honestly, we just need time to adjust.
- Right.

11
00:00:54,099 --> 00:00:56,235
You said you'd adjust in a day, Sung Jun.

12
00:00:56,235 --> 00:00:58,103
- No, but the thing is...
- You said one day was enough.

13
00:00:58,103 --> 00:00:59,905
[Sung Jun, the rookie spokesperson]
The tricky part is...

14
00:00:59,905 --> 00:01:02,708
We're undercover,
so we have to hide who we are.

15
00:01:02,708 --> 00:01:05,477
We have to fly under the radar,
but still crush it.

16
00:01:05,477 --> 00:01:06,979
- Right.
- That's the tricky part.

17
00:01:06,979 --> 00:01:09,448
We're undercover on purpose.

18
00:01:09,448 --> 00:01:10,916
- Playing dumb.
- I was...

19
00:01:10,916 --> 00:01:12,463
Like, "I don't get what you're saying."

20
00:01:12,463 --> 00:01:14,086
[Strong agreement]
Turns out you were doing it on purpose.

21
00:01:14,086 --> 00:01:14,887
- Right?
- Exactly.

22
00:01:14,887 --> 00:01:17,323
- I had no idea.
- That's it.

23
00:01:17,323 --> 00:01:19,425
But in the end, out of the three of you...

24
00:01:19,425 --> 00:01:21,694
- Maybe only one moves up.
- Yeah.

25
00:01:21,694 --> 00:01:23,529
Or, you know, nobody moves up at all.

26
00:01:23,529 --> 00:01:25,130
I'm worried that could happen.

27
00:01:25,130 --> 00:01:27,800
I mean, at least one of us can do it, right?

28
00:01:27,800 --> 00:01:29,802
Really?

29
00:01:29,802 --> 00:01:33,138
- Who's he talking about? Himself?
- Like, is he saying...

30
00:01:33,138 --> 00:01:35,507
- Confidence?
- Right, what? Is it confidence?

31
00:01:35,507 --> 00:01:38,010
- What is it?
- So one of us made it.

32
00:01:38,010 --> 00:01:40,713
[Surprise announcement]
Today, finally...

33
00:01:40,713 --> 00:01:43,649
- One chef is graduating from rookie!
- Oh? Really?

34
00:01:43,649 --> 00:01:45,351
- Who is it?
- Who do you think?

35
00:01:45,351 --> 00:01:46,785
Sung Jun.

36
00:01:46,785 --> 00:01:48,387
Seriously? Why?

37
00:01:48,387 --> 00:01:49,788
[I get it, sis]
Because I'm too cocky?

38
00:01:49,788 --> 00:01:51,156
[No way]

39
00:01:51,156 --> 00:01:53,792
Ji Sun, stop hating on him.

40
00:01:53,792 --> 00:01:55,861
No, he's just like that.

41
00:01:55,861 --> 00:01:57,563
- Still.
- It's an act.

42
00:01:57,563 --> 00:01:59,798
- It's an act.
- It's an act.

43
00:01:59,798 --> 00:02:01,445
Chef Sam Kim, on the other hand...

44
00:02:01,445 --> 00:02:03,202
- You've got one more rival now.
- Right.

45
00:02:03,202 --> 00:02:04,403
- Right?
- Yeah.

46
00:02:04,403 --> 00:02:06,839
[Hee Tae has an unexpected rival]
Turns out, this guy Sorem showed up too.

47
00:02:06,839 --> 00:02:10,042
And Chef Ji Sun has to practice
her wok work now.

48
00:02:10,042 --> 00:02:13,479
The wok doesn't have a handle.
She has to practice with that wok.

49
00:02:13,479 --> 00:02:14,847
She's not used to it yet.

50
00:02:14,847 --> 00:02:16,482
Watching me was so frustrating.

51
00:02:16,482 --> 00:02:17,616
- Right.
- Yeah.

52
00:02:17,616 --> 00:02:19,918
I wanted to bring that wok in here.

53
00:02:19,918 --> 00:02:21,020
For everyone to try.

54
00:02:21,020 --> 00:02:22,554
- For them to try?
- For all the staff too?

55
00:02:22,554 --> 00:02:24,289
- Yeah, everyone.
- I want to try it.

56
00:02:24,289 --> 00:02:26,258
Chef Sung Jun, too...

57
00:02:26,258 --> 00:02:27,793
Pasta is next.

58
00:02:27,793 --> 00:02:30,396
- I should start soon.
- Yeah, it's time.

59
00:02:30,396 --> 00:02:35,467
Who will be the chef
that escapes rookie status today?

60
00:02:35,467 --> 00:02:37,936
- Let's find out.
- There's actually someone?

61
00:02:37,936 --> 00:02:38,871
On day two?

62
00:02:38,871 --> 00:02:40,406
[Who gets the glory?]

63
00:02:40,406 --> 00:02:41,407
[Parma, Italy. Hee Tae, not Sam Kim]

64
00:02:41,407 --> 00:02:44,877
[Undercover day two, finishing lunch service]

65
00:02:44,877 --> 00:02:49,181
[As guests slowly leave]

66
00:02:49,181 --> 00:02:52,751
[Hee Tae finally catches his breath]

67
00:02:52,751 --> 00:02:56,522
[Lunch service in one line...]

68
00:02:56,522 --> 00:02:59,491
[He gave it everything...]

69
00:02:59,491 --> 00:03:02,194
[Blind showdown with Senior Lu!]

70
00:03:02,194 --> 00:03:06,632
Believe it or not,
Hee Tae's pasta looked better.

71
00:03:06,632 --> 00:03:08,267
[Praised for craft, Winner!]
He won the test.

72
00:03:08,267 --> 00:03:10,002
Right.

73
00:03:10,002 --> 00:03:11,203
It's the pinching.

74
00:03:11,203 --> 00:03:14,940
[But too much Italian, so he missed the result]
It's a good pinch for the pasta.

75
00:03:14,940 --> 00:03:17,154
I was going to put Hee Tae
in charge of the pasta station

76
00:03:17,154 --> 00:03:19,244
almost entirely on his own.

77
00:03:19,244 --> 00:03:21,980
[Earning the head chef's trust]

78
00:03:21,980 --> 00:03:25,350
[Running the pasta factory solo]

79
00:03:25,350 --> 00:03:27,252
[But the solo show was brutal...]

80
00:03:27,252 --> 00:03:29,922
No.

81
00:03:29,922 --> 00:03:32,958
[Seniors hitting him with notes]
I'll make it again.

82
00:03:32,958 --> 00:03:35,027
Don't make them this small.

83
00:03:35,027 --> 00:03:36,328
This is not good.

84
00:03:36,328 --> 00:03:39,398
You're wasting time.

85
00:03:39,398 --> 00:03:40,632
[Lunch ends in nonstop criticism...]

86
00:03:40,632 --> 00:03:42,534
[Sad...]
Is something wrong with me?

87
00:03:43,702 --> 00:03:44,970
[Hee Tae missed the praise, only got beaten up]

88
00:03:44,970 --> 00:03:49,096
On day two, doing all the pasta
on my own really wasn't easy.

89
00:03:49,708 --> 00:03:54,346
[A bitter break time]

90
00:03:54,346 --> 00:03:56,181
[Sigh]

91
00:03:56,181 --> 00:03:58,784
He just went back to get some rest.

92
00:03:58,784 --> 00:04:01,119
[Hee Tae] [Rooting for you!]
- This is so rough. - Right.

93
00:04:05,157 --> 00:04:09,728
[He hits the couch the second he's home]

94
00:04:09,728 --> 00:04:12,931
[Radiating heavy energy]

95
00:04:12,931 --> 00:04:17,369
[Then he watches something and smiles?]

96
00:04:17,369 --> 00:04:18,737
[Pung's YouTube where he appears]
<i>Even the crows are crying.</i>

97
00:04:18,737 --> 00:04:19,838
[Delighted]

98
00:04:19,838 --> 00:04:21,173
You're watching that right now?

99
00:04:21,173 --> 00:04:23,175
- Yeah.
- My channel?

100
00:04:23,175 --> 00:04:24,810
Yeah.

101
00:04:24,810 --> 00:04:27,012
You told me to watch it.

102
00:04:27,012 --> 00:04:28,881
[Finding peace with Pung's voice]
<i>Me...</i>

103
00:04:28,881 --> 00:04:30,916
<i>Watch episode one of Ramen Geezer.</i>

104
00:04:30,916 --> 00:04:33,485
<i>Me, getting better little by little.</i>

105
00:04:33,485 --> 00:04:35,487
<i>You've got to improve.</i>

106
00:04:37,222 --> 00:04:38,990
<i>You've got to improve.</i>

107
00:04:42,494 --> 00:04:46,799
[Suddenly springs up]

108
00:04:46,799 --> 00:04:48,733
[Video OFF]

109
00:04:50,903 --> 00:04:52,204
<i>You've got to improve.</i>

110
00:04:52,204 --> 00:04:57,776
[Heading to work with new resolve]

111
00:04:57,776 --> 00:05:01,384
[Five days, every moment counts]

112
00:05:02,581 --> 00:05:04,149
[I'll show you a whole new me]

113
00:05:04,149 --> 00:05:08,187
[Back to full power]

114
00:05:08,187 --> 00:05:10,655
I really want to do well.

115
00:05:11,323 --> 00:05:12,858
[Tension] [No joke]
More than Sung Jun's clips,

116
00:05:12,858 --> 00:05:15,260
[Steeling himself again]
there's so much tension.

117
00:05:15,260 --> 00:05:16,528
Because he's actually nervous.

118
00:05:16,528 --> 00:05:19,698
[Day two, dinner shift begins]
He's really tense.

119
00:05:19,698 --> 00:05:20,732
[With his game plan notes out]

120
00:05:20,732 --> 00:05:22,968
Because he really meant business.

121
00:05:22,968 --> 00:05:24,803
He went in fully committed.

122
00:05:24,803 --> 00:05:26,505
Did you bring that hat?

123
00:05:26,505 --> 00:05:28,205
Tossed it.

124
00:05:29,975 --> 00:05:32,277
[Even the bread hat reminds him
of Parma rookie days]

125
00:05:32,277 --> 00:05:35,047
- It suits you.
- I left it at the restaurant.

126
00:05:35,047 --> 00:05:39,985
[Right in, prepping for dinner service]

127
00:05:39,985 --> 00:05:45,624
[Doing it without being told, of course!]

128
00:05:45,624 --> 00:05:47,926
To move up, I need to stand out.

129
00:05:47,926 --> 00:05:52,764
Working twice as hard
as everyone else is the best...

130
00:05:52,764 --> 00:05:55,400
He came in late and wolfed down his food.

131
00:05:56,101 --> 00:05:59,238
He's in this serious battle all by himself.

132
00:05:59,238 --> 00:06:00,239
[Quickly finishing his meal]

133
00:06:00,239 --> 00:06:03,876
[Pulling out tools for dinner service]

134
00:06:03,876 --> 00:06:06,489
[Setting up the pasta station]

135
00:06:08,180 --> 00:06:10,916
[Stepping away for ingredients]

136
00:06:10,916 --> 00:06:12,974
[He hurries back and...]

137
00:06:14,186 --> 00:06:16,255
Sorem.

138
00:06:16,255 --> 00:06:17,289
[His center spot got taken]

139
00:06:17,289 --> 00:06:18,590
[Tsk]

140
00:06:18,590 --> 00:06:19,925
What is this situation?

141
00:06:19,925 --> 00:06:22,561
[He sets down the flour]

142
00:06:22,561 --> 00:06:25,130
[And just hangs back, watching]

143
00:06:25,130 --> 00:06:26,598
[I...]

144
00:06:26,598 --> 00:06:28,766
Fidgeting with his hands.

145
00:06:30,493 --> 00:06:32,637
[Quick toss]
Yeah. Thank you.

146
00:06:34,139 --> 00:06:37,109
[Taking over Sorem's piping bag]

147
00:06:37,109 --> 00:06:40,378
[Working hard!]
He's filling the tortelli.

148
00:06:41,747 --> 00:06:43,681
Okay, that's enough.

149
00:06:44,616 --> 00:06:47,219
[Putting the cheese filling back in the fridge]

150
00:06:47,219 --> 00:06:49,488
Oh, we had this one too.

151
00:06:49,488 --> 00:06:51,690
Oh, we had this one too.

152
00:06:51,690 --> 00:06:53,692
What?

153
00:06:53,692 --> 00:06:56,099
[Trouble incoming]

154
00:06:57,062 --> 00:06:59,765
I didn't see it.

155
00:06:59,765 --> 00:07:02,467
- What's wrong?
- What's wrong?

156
00:07:02,467 --> 00:07:04,636
[Sorem used this cheese filling]

157
00:07:04,636 --> 00:07:07,572
[But should have used this one!]

158
00:07:07,572 --> 00:07:08,907
You know, first in, first out.

159
00:07:08,907 --> 00:07:12,844
[Used the fresh batch instead...]
You're supposed to use the older one first.

160
00:07:14,179 --> 00:07:17,348
[Kitchen rule 101 to avoid waste]
Otherwise you end up wasting ingredients.

161
00:07:19,651 --> 00:07:21,787
That's on Sorem.

162
00:07:21,787 --> 00:07:23,855
He's walking on eggshells.

163
00:07:23,855 --> 00:07:25,490
Simone!

164
00:07:25,490 --> 00:07:27,471
I didn't see that we still had this.

165
00:07:27,471 --> 00:07:29,761
And I used the new batch.

166
00:07:29,761 --> 00:07:30,696
This is bad.

167
00:07:30,696 --> 00:07:33,732
[He messed up?]

168
00:07:33,732 --> 00:07:34,766
[So much for the fresh start, trouble already]

169
00:07:34,766 --> 00:07:37,536
[Conflicted]

170
00:07:37,536 --> 00:07:38,770
We ran out.

171
00:07:38,770 --> 00:07:39,871
[On top of that, something feels...]

172
00:07:39,871 --> 00:07:40,939
[Like he's an accomplice...]

173
00:07:40,939 --> 00:07:43,475
- He's suddenly an accomplice.
- Right!

174
00:07:43,475 --> 00:07:45,677
Why are you standing right next to him?

175
00:07:45,677 --> 00:07:49,081
You should've slowly backed away.

176
00:07:49,081 --> 00:07:51,583
This guy is killing me, seriously.

177
00:07:51,583 --> 00:07:52,584
I didn't know that.

178
00:07:52,584 --> 00:07:55,153
[Hee Tae stuck right behind his senior]
In a moment like this, you slowly back away.

179
00:07:55,153 --> 00:07:56,922
That's what I should have done.

180
00:07:56,922 --> 00:07:58,657
Why are you standing right next to him?

181
00:07:58,657 --> 00:08:01,093
Like a dummy. Oh, come on.

182
00:08:01,093 --> 00:08:03,962
Sam, you're not a dummy, you know?

183
00:08:03,962 --> 00:08:05,897
But come on, it looks dumb!

184
00:08:05,897 --> 00:08:07,665
It's all good.

185
00:08:08,400 --> 00:08:11,102
- Empty the piping bag.
- Okay.

186
00:08:11,937 --> 00:08:14,306
[Ugh...]

187
00:08:14,306 --> 00:08:16,208
He's standing right there.

188
00:08:16,208 --> 00:08:18,376
[A bit unfair]

189
00:08:19,177 --> 00:08:22,447
[Troubled]

190
00:08:22,447 --> 00:08:25,884
[Cleaning up his senior's mess...]

191
00:08:25,884 --> 00:08:31,156
[Current time, 8 PM]

192
00:08:31,156 --> 00:08:34,526
[Bell rings, dinner service is on]

193
00:08:34,526 --> 00:08:37,332
[Swoosh]

194
00:08:38,997 --> 00:08:42,500
So that's how he was watching me,
first time seeing this.

195
00:08:43,602 --> 00:08:44,903
[He pulled off the station after the mistake?]
Right now...

196
00:08:44,903 --> 00:08:47,973
After those earlier mistakes...

197
00:08:47,973 --> 00:08:50,776
it actually worked out, didn't it?

198
00:08:50,776 --> 00:08:52,077
It does seem like it worked out.

199
00:08:52,077 --> 00:08:53,478
That spot...

200
00:08:53,478 --> 00:08:55,813
- It's such a busy spot.
- It's a tough spot.

201
00:08:58,950 --> 00:08:59,918
[A bit shaken]

202
00:08:59,918 --> 00:09:02,054
Hey, leave the cheese alone.

203
00:09:02,054 --> 00:09:03,021
[Sigh]

204
00:09:03,021 --> 00:09:07,159
- Want me to prep something?
- No, stop touching the cheese.

205
00:09:07,159 --> 00:09:09,193
Oh well...

206
00:09:10,195 --> 00:09:13,098
Sorem is so cute.

207
00:09:13,098 --> 00:09:15,600
[Sorem reassigned behind Hee Tae?]
- Sorem. - So cute.

208
00:09:15,600 --> 00:09:18,837
[Tsk...]

209
00:09:18,837 --> 00:09:20,938
[Glance]

210
00:09:21,807 --> 00:09:24,842
- Sorem, help Hee Tae make more anolini.
- Helping Hee Tae.

211
00:09:25,877 --> 00:09:28,546
Yeah, do anolini with Hee Tae.

212
00:09:29,381 --> 00:09:30,682
Stick with Hee Tae.

213
00:09:30,682 --> 00:09:32,717
With Hee Tae!

214
00:09:32,717 --> 00:09:37,093
[Trudge...]

215
00:09:37,093 --> 00:09:38,290
Switched from yesterday, huh?

216
00:09:38,290 --> 00:09:39,691
[Off to the pasta station to help Hee Tae]
Off to the pasta.

217
00:09:39,691 --> 00:09:41,245
Remember?

218
00:09:41,245 --> 00:09:43,328
Hold on. This isn't right.

219
00:09:43,328 --> 00:09:44,696
[This morning, Sorem led, Hee Tae backed up...]

220
00:09:44,696 --> 00:09:47,132
[Now Sorem is backup]

221
00:09:47,132 --> 00:09:49,701
[Hee Tae is lead]
Hold on, didn't he just naturally...

222
00:09:49,701 --> 00:09:51,169
take his senior's spot?

223
00:09:51,169 --> 00:09:52,838
Right.

224
00:09:52,838 --> 00:09:55,307
- That's...
- That looks like it.

225
00:09:55,307 --> 00:09:56,908
- Yeah, looks that way.
- Right.

226
00:09:56,908 --> 00:09:57,909
- Looks like it.
- I was just...

227
00:09:57,909 --> 00:10:00,412
- You didn't know?
- I was just working hard.

228
00:10:00,412 --> 00:10:02,214
My back was turned.

229
00:10:02,214 --> 00:10:05,417
And Sorem's face doesn't look happy.

230
00:10:05,417 --> 00:10:08,120
- His spot got taken.
- Feels like he got pushed out.

231
00:10:08,120 --> 00:10:10,822
No wonder his tone was a bit grumpy.

232
00:10:10,822 --> 00:10:12,924
Right.

233
00:10:12,924 --> 00:10:14,926
[Whoosh]

234
00:10:14,926 --> 00:10:18,329
[Do it like this]

235
00:10:19,498 --> 00:10:21,233
What?

236
00:10:21,233 --> 00:10:22,868
[Reading the room]
A little more?

237
00:10:22,868 --> 00:10:25,070
- A little more?
- Yeah, just that much.

238
00:10:25,070 --> 00:10:26,271
[Just touch it?]

239
00:10:26,271 --> 00:10:27,806
[Tense vibe]

240
00:10:27,806 --> 00:10:29,907
They're fighting.

241
00:10:31,209 --> 00:10:33,056
He's nitpicking the shape on purpose...

242
00:10:33,056 --> 00:10:34,212
He's picking a fight.

243
00:10:34,212 --> 00:10:35,915
[Hmm...]

244
00:10:35,915 --> 00:10:38,050
I was a little thrown off.

245
00:10:39,050 --> 00:10:40,352
[Tsk...]

246
00:10:40,352 --> 00:10:42,254
I am the rookie here.

247
00:10:42,254 --> 00:10:45,123
[Big-hearted Hee Tae]
He clearly thinks I'm below him.

248
00:10:45,123 --> 00:10:47,292
Fair enough...

249
00:10:47,292 --> 00:10:49,093
Fair enough.

250
00:10:50,829 --> 00:10:52,397
He was kind of...

251
00:10:52,397 --> 00:10:54,299
- There was some tension.
- A competitive streak.

252
00:10:54,299 --> 00:10:55,033
You've changed.

253
00:10:55,033 --> 00:10:57,569
- There was tension, I see.
- He got mad.

254
00:10:57,569 --> 00:10:59,137
But what can you do?

255
00:10:59,137 --> 00:11:01,005
You've got to step over him.

256
00:11:01,907 --> 00:11:04,242
[Sorem, after the tension with Hee Tae]

257
00:11:04,242 --> 00:11:08,647
[Steps away for a bit...]

258
00:11:08,647 --> 00:11:09,981
[Order in]

259
00:11:09,981 --> 00:11:11,550
Prosciutto, salami and neck.

260
00:11:11,550 --> 00:11:13,564
One guinea fowl, two fried breads,

261
00:11:13,564 --> 00:11:15,453
one fried polenta,
one Parmigiano, one red onion.

262
00:11:15,453 --> 00:11:18,323
[The boss's Italian order rap is back...]
Two fried breads, one polenta...

263
00:11:18,323 --> 00:11:19,724
Can you catch all that?

264
00:11:19,724 --> 00:11:20,792
I can't.

265
00:11:20,792 --> 00:11:23,328
- Of course not.
- Way too fast.

266
00:11:23,328 --> 00:11:26,898
[Didn't catch a thing]

267
00:11:27,799 --> 00:11:30,200
[No replays]

268
00:11:31,102 --> 00:11:32,204
Where's Sorem?

269
00:11:32,204 --> 00:11:33,905
Sorem speaks some English, at least.

270
00:11:33,905 --> 00:11:36,040
- He translates.
- Sorem.

271
00:11:37,976 --> 00:11:39,444
[Gone when he needs him...]
Where did Sorem go?

272
00:11:39,444 --> 00:11:41,379
What do you do?

273
00:11:43,215 --> 00:11:44,916
Make one fried bread torta.

274
00:11:44,916 --> 00:11:46,616
Okay.

275
00:11:47,886 --> 00:11:49,254
[With Sorem gone, it all falls on Hee Tae...]
Oh, right.

276
00:11:49,254 --> 00:11:52,324
Here's exactly what was happening.

277
00:11:52,324 --> 00:11:54,693
"They left me here all alone.

278
00:11:54,693 --> 00:11:56,728
Where did everyone go?" That kind of feeling.

279
00:11:56,728 --> 00:11:59,998
[His bread hat looks as wilted as he does...]

280
00:11:59,998 --> 00:12:01,266
[Behind the lone mushroom Hee Tae...]

281
00:12:01,266 --> 00:12:03,868
[Sorem ended up with the head chef]

282
00:12:03,868 --> 00:12:07,472
See? This part, smooth and shiny...

283
00:12:07,472 --> 00:12:08,840
What's Sorem doing?

284
00:12:08,840 --> 00:12:13,011
[Sorem learning recipes near the stove]
Looks like he's helping with other prep.

285
00:12:13,011 --> 00:12:15,747
[Glance]
So Sorem is learning the sauce right now.

286
00:12:15,747 --> 00:12:19,618
[I should be doing that...]

287
00:12:19,618 --> 00:12:22,220
That bothered me the most.

288
00:12:22,220 --> 00:12:26,191
More than pasta, the cooking side...

289
00:12:26,191 --> 00:12:29,794
is where I need to focus...

290
00:12:29,794 --> 00:12:33,365
[Anxious inside]
The pasta here is basically the main thing.

291
00:12:33,365 --> 00:12:35,045
He's got to do that, plus service.

292
00:12:35,045 --> 00:12:36,734
[Mountains of work...]
Right.

293
00:12:38,536 --> 00:12:41,206
[The harder he works,
the farther he feels from the stove]

294
00:12:41,206 --> 00:12:44,042
- The stove is still really far.
- Far away.

295
00:12:44,042 --> 00:12:45,944
Because they're full.

296
00:12:45,944 --> 00:12:48,913
They're not giving me that spot, but...

297
00:12:48,913 --> 00:12:52,284
I don't have a lot of time...

298
00:12:52,284 --> 00:12:54,252
[Hee Tae's strategy here was...]
So...

299
00:12:54,252 --> 00:12:57,022
I figured I should nail this first, because...

300
00:12:57,022 --> 00:13:01,626
I need to show I can handle it all
even when it's crazy.

301
00:13:01,626 --> 00:13:05,742
That's how I get a shot at moving up,
that's what I thought.

302
00:13:05,742 --> 00:13:07,399
Exactly!

303
00:13:07,399 --> 00:13:11,569
[Decided to nail the pasta station work]

304
00:13:11,569 --> 00:13:14,506
At that point, I was like...

305
00:13:14,506 --> 00:13:16,908
[Behind him, Sorem's doing what he wants]
"Am I really doing this alone?"

306
00:13:16,908 --> 00:13:20,211
"Why did they dump it on me
when I just got here?"

307
00:13:20,211 --> 00:13:22,514
[Focus on the pasta in front of him]
So if I can just get through this...

308
00:13:22,514 --> 00:13:24,949
that's the only way to get to the next thing.

309
00:13:24,949 --> 00:13:26,584
[One by one, quietly]

310
00:13:26,584 --> 00:13:28,853
[Even the messy bits, careful!]

311
00:13:28,853 --> 00:13:30,555
[Making them]

312
00:13:30,555 --> 00:13:33,725
[Hee Tae keeps making them]
When Sam Kim can't read the room...

313
00:13:33,725 --> 00:13:36,828
he just goes hard on what's in front of him.

314
00:13:36,828 --> 00:13:39,197
[Just then...]
Two mixed salami,

315
00:13:39,197 --> 00:13:42,467
[Another storm of orders rolls in]
one fried bread, potato tortelli,

316
00:13:42,467 --> 00:13:44,636
cheese tortelli, potato tortelli.

317
00:13:44,636 --> 00:13:48,440
[And he hears it]
Cheese tortelli, potato tortelli.

318
00:13:48,440 --> 00:13:49,441
[Una patata]

319
00:13:49,441 --> 00:13:50,608
[One potato tortelli]
Potato tortelli.

320
00:13:50,608 --> 00:13:53,111
Potato tortelli.

321
00:13:53,111 --> 00:13:56,748
[Confirmed out of stock]

322
00:13:56,748 --> 00:13:59,784
[Grabs the piping bag right away]

323
00:13:59,784 --> 00:14:03,421
If we're out, you make more.

324
00:14:03,421 --> 00:14:07,324
Potato tortelli isn't square, I know that now.

325
00:14:08,393 --> 00:14:10,028
[Embarrassed]
Now...

326
00:14:10,028 --> 00:14:11,408
I learned it too.

327
00:14:11,408 --> 00:14:12,697
I picked it up watching.

328
00:14:12,697 --> 00:14:14,238
[Even Pung memorized potato tortelli...]

329
00:14:15,066 --> 00:14:18,203
[You pinch both ends to seal]

330
00:14:18,203 --> 00:14:21,272
[It should come out round like this]

331
00:14:21,272 --> 00:14:26,544
[Made it square, messed up twice!]

332
00:14:26,544 --> 00:14:29,581
[A jinx for pasta rookie Hee Tae]

333
00:14:29,581 --> 00:14:32,089
The jinx is back for real.

334
00:14:33,585 --> 00:14:38,156
[For potato...]
[Pinch round!]

335
00:14:38,156 --> 00:14:41,179
[Reminding himself,
piping the potato filling...]

336
00:14:44,729 --> 00:14:48,668
- He won't mess up again, right?
- No way he does.

337
00:14:49,601 --> 00:14:51,970
Got an order from the other dining room!

338
00:14:51,970 --> 00:14:53,772
More pasta?

339
00:14:53,772 --> 00:14:54,806
[Another order in]
Coming right up.

340
00:14:54,806 --> 00:14:56,107
Hee Tae.

341
00:14:56,107 --> 00:14:57,942
One more cheese tortelli!

342
00:14:57,942 --> 00:14:59,912
Cheese, we already have six...

343
00:14:59,912 --> 00:15:01,646
- Just two more, please.
- Huh?

344
00:15:01,646 --> 00:15:03,481
Hold on.

345
00:15:03,481 --> 00:15:05,128
Finish the eight potato tortelli,

346
00:15:05,128 --> 00:15:07,252
- then two cheese.
- Okay.

347
00:15:07,252 --> 00:15:08,887
Finish the eight potato tortelli,

348
00:15:08,887 --> 00:15:10,989
[Two kinds on one strip!]
- then two cheese. - Okay.

349
00:15:10,989 --> 00:15:12,957
Seriously?

350
00:15:13,892 --> 00:15:15,660
Difficulty just shot up.

351
00:15:15,660 --> 00:15:18,630
[Jinx potato tortelli... harder now]

352
00:15:18,630 --> 00:15:20,932
[Dead serious]

353
00:15:20,932 --> 00:15:23,234
They didn't teach him the variation.

354
00:15:23,234 --> 00:15:25,096
[Tense right along with him]

355
00:15:26,137 --> 00:15:28,620
[Pipe cheese next to potato, side by side]

356
00:15:29,541 --> 00:15:32,143
[Cheese] [Potato]

357
00:15:32,143 --> 00:15:34,493
Wait, so the shape has to change
halfway through?

358
00:15:34,493 --> 00:15:36,748
[Each one needs a different finish!]
Right, they have to be different.

359
00:15:36,748 --> 00:15:38,283
[Potato ones, round]

360
00:15:38,283 --> 00:15:43,555
[Cheese ones, square]

361
00:15:43,555 --> 00:15:45,756
[Even Naples rookies know this]
One like this, one like this.

362
00:15:46,658 --> 00:15:50,495
[Hee Tae, fighting solo...]

363
00:15:50,495 --> 00:15:52,397
[Tension like a cooking showdown]

364
00:15:52,397 --> 00:15:54,432
The vibe just turned into a cooking show.

365
00:15:54,432 --> 00:15:56,201
[Closing them one by one...]
He's got this, right?

366
00:15:56,201 --> 00:15:57,968
Let's see!

367
00:16:03,208 --> 00:16:04,509
- Wait.
- Wait.

368
00:16:04,509 --> 00:16:05,977
- Hold on.
- Hold on, that's already wrong.

369
00:16:05,977 --> 00:16:07,278
- Wait.
- Wait.

370
00:16:07,278 --> 00:16:08,646
- Hold on.
- Hold on, that's already wrong.

371
00:16:08,646 --> 00:16:10,482
Hold on.

372
00:16:11,082 --> 00:16:14,652
[Square again?]

373
00:16:14,652 --> 00:16:16,087
Hold on.

374
00:16:16,087 --> 00:16:17,689
- Hold on.
- Seriously?

375
00:16:17,689 --> 00:16:19,190
- No way...
- Really?

376
00:16:19,190 --> 00:16:20,124
- No way...
- Really?

377
00:16:20,124 --> 00:16:21,426
- Are we watching a rerun?
- No, hold on.

378
00:16:21,426 --> 00:16:22,694
This is lunch service, right?

379
00:16:22,694 --> 00:16:25,163
[This can't be real]

380
00:16:25,163 --> 00:16:27,398
- No, look!
- They're showing lunch again, right?

381
00:16:27,398 --> 00:16:29,334
[Can't believe my eyes]
No, this is...

382
00:16:29,334 --> 00:16:32,070
[In denial]
Am I getting this wrong?

383
00:16:32,070 --> 00:16:33,738
[This one, right?]
Left is this, right is...

384
00:16:33,738 --> 00:16:37,041
Even I can tell now!

385
00:16:37,041 --> 00:16:39,076
[Possessed by squares for sure]
He must be really nervous.

386
00:16:40,945 --> 00:16:45,507
[Potato trapped in squares again]

387
00:16:46,718 --> 00:16:51,356
<i>♫ Same dough, just square potato ♫</i>

388
00:16:51,356 --> 00:16:57,295
<i>♫ Make square potato, eat square potato ♫</i>

389
00:16:57,295 --> 00:17:01,299
[Big trouble]

390
00:17:01,299 --> 00:17:03,434
[Glance]

391
00:17:03,434 --> 00:17:04,602
- He saw.
- Oh, no!

392
00:17:04,602 --> 00:17:05,770
[He saw it]

393
00:17:05,770 --> 00:17:07,739
He saw.

394
00:17:07,739 --> 00:17:09,707
[Caught by Sorem again]
You have to pinch these.

395
00:17:12,210 --> 00:17:14,945
[Oh, no...]
His face.

396
00:17:16,648 --> 00:17:18,749
[Look at his face]
His face.

397
00:17:19,350 --> 00:17:20,585
[Agony bleeding through the screen]

398
00:17:20,585 --> 00:17:21,553
No.

399
00:17:21,553 --> 00:17:23,721
- Hey, what do you do?
- No, I can save it.

400
00:17:23,721 --> 00:17:26,090
[Wheezing]
No, can this be saved?

401
00:17:28,726 --> 00:17:30,261
[Pinching it round, too late]
Turn in your chef title.

402
00:17:30,261 --> 00:17:32,963
This isn't working.

403
00:17:34,999 --> 00:17:36,968
[But the No. 1 catches him too]
They know it now.

404
00:17:36,968 --> 00:17:38,336
[Sad]

405
00:17:38,336 --> 00:17:39,971
[A mistake even he can't explain]

406
00:17:39,971 --> 00:17:41,772
Oh, come on.

407
00:17:42,440 --> 00:17:44,876
[Is the promotion off the table?]
His hat keeps...

408
00:17:44,876 --> 00:17:46,411
[Even gloomier mushroom hat]

409
00:17:46,411 --> 00:17:50,748
Sam Kim might be the slowest to move up.

410
00:17:50,748 --> 00:17:52,283
Or he could be the fastest, actually.

411
00:17:52,283 --> 00:17:55,619
- It's not easy.
- Oh, I don't know, watching this.

412
00:17:56,321 --> 00:17:57,922
- Before cutting it...
- That was close.

413
00:17:57,922 --> 00:17:59,991
[Still scrambling to fix it]

414
00:18:01,726 --> 00:18:03,027
- Oh, still.
- Still, the shape...

415
00:18:03,027 --> 00:18:04,662
- Came out nice.
- At least the shape...

416
00:18:04,662 --> 00:18:07,231
- Got it back, thank God.
- Thank God.

417
00:18:07,231 --> 00:18:09,334
- Sorem still...
- Sorem saved it.

418
00:18:09,334 --> 00:18:10,568
- Caught it for him.
- Right?

419
00:18:10,568 --> 00:18:13,103
- Sorem saved him.
- Sorem saved this one.

420
00:18:14,939 --> 00:18:17,808
- Two tagliatelle.
- Yes!

421
00:18:18,910 --> 00:18:21,813
Fresh pasta every time an order
comes in, right?

422
00:18:21,813 --> 00:18:23,147
[No time to mope, next pasta order]

423
00:18:23,147 --> 00:18:24,582
[Tagliatelle by feel, zip zip]
Just...

424
00:18:24,582 --> 00:18:26,284
- Without measuring.
- Yeah.

425
00:18:26,284 --> 00:18:28,820
- Cutting by feel.
- Naturally.

426
00:18:28,820 --> 00:18:32,657
[Four to five pastas made on the spot]
Every order means making fresh pasta.

427
00:18:32,657 --> 00:18:34,591
Too many menu items.

428
00:18:35,259 --> 00:18:36,260
Looks good.

429
00:18:36,260 --> 00:18:38,362
[Hee Tae's pasta goes to the guests]
That really looks good.

430
00:18:39,697 --> 00:18:43,534
[Hee Tae's fresh pasta is up]

431
00:18:43,534 --> 00:18:45,898
[How will the guests react?]

432
00:18:50,975 --> 00:18:53,410
Try it. It's really good.

433
00:18:54,245 --> 00:18:55,761
[Both, taking a bite]

434
00:18:57,682 --> 00:18:58,850
[Gesture of satisfaction]

435
00:18:58,850 --> 00:19:00,852
[Even some serious nodding!]
The food here is genuinely great.

436
00:19:00,852 --> 00:19:02,787
That's why it looks so good.

437
00:19:02,787 --> 00:19:05,123
[At another table]

438
00:19:05,123 --> 00:19:07,225
[Almost every type ordered]

439
00:19:07,225 --> 00:19:08,459
They all ordered different things.

440
00:19:08,459 --> 00:19:10,361
[Pheasant agnolotti, cheese tortelli,
duck tagliatelle, chicken anolini]

441
00:19:12,797 --> 00:19:14,498
It's incredible.

442
00:19:16,034 --> 00:19:17,734
This is good.

443
00:19:19,404 --> 00:19:21,438
This one too!

444
00:19:23,741 --> 00:19:26,611
[All praise for the pasta]
Everyone really talks about the food.

445
00:19:26,611 --> 00:19:27,745
- They mean it, really.
- Right?

446
00:19:27,745 --> 00:19:30,581
Italians are really genuine.

447
00:19:30,581 --> 00:19:33,351
[Glum from his mistake, Hee Tae has no idea]

448
00:19:33,351 --> 00:19:36,054
[Down to the last bite]

449
00:19:36,054 --> 00:19:39,321
[Guests fully satisfied]

450
00:19:40,425 --> 00:19:41,793
I want to tell myself...

451
00:19:41,793 --> 00:19:43,894
That must have been rough.

452
00:19:45,196 --> 00:19:46,798
- To yourself?
- Yeah.

453
00:19:46,798 --> 00:19:48,700
- That must have been rough.
- He's starting to sound like someone...

454
00:19:48,700 --> 00:19:50,535
- Hold on.
- About himself.

455
00:19:50,535 --> 00:19:52,403
- Similar.
- Their narcissism is rubbing off on each other.

456
00:19:52,403 --> 00:19:54,474
- Self-love.
- All alike.

457
00:19:55,573 --> 00:19:57,241
Everything okay?

458
00:19:57,241 --> 00:19:58,776
You alright?

459
00:19:58,776 --> 00:20:00,078
Waiting for the gelato?

460
00:20:00,078 --> 00:20:01,746
[Meanwhile, the owner checks the guests]

461
00:20:01,746 --> 00:20:04,428
[Pasta plates wiped clean]
Did you get everything?

462
00:20:06,150 --> 00:20:07,785
[Visits the kitchen]

463
00:20:07,785 --> 00:20:09,549
[Peeking]

464
00:20:10,388 --> 00:20:12,724
- Hee Tae doing okay?
- Yes!

465
00:20:12,724 --> 00:20:14,459
He's actually really good.

466
00:20:14,459 --> 00:20:16,160
He's not so bad.

467
00:20:16,160 --> 00:20:16,994
[Smile]

468
00:20:16,994 --> 00:20:20,898
[Misses the praise, just working hard]

469
00:20:20,898 --> 00:20:25,136
What I hoped for at first was
just that he wouldn't mess up in the kitchen.

470
00:20:25,136 --> 00:20:29,173
Hee Tae is way past those expectations!

471
00:20:29,173 --> 00:20:30,408
Isn't that high praise?

472
00:20:30,408 --> 00:20:34,679
What Hee Tae has shown us so far...

473
00:20:34,679 --> 00:20:37,749
I hope he keeps it up.

474
00:20:37,749 --> 00:20:39,183
[Pleased]

475
00:20:39,183 --> 00:20:40,017
He's getting recognition.

476
00:20:40,017 --> 00:20:41,952
- Good!
- Proper recognition.

477
00:20:43,521 --> 00:20:46,290
[Owner recognizes his work and skill]

478
00:20:46,290 --> 00:20:48,826
[Good!]

479
00:20:50,795 --> 00:20:53,898
[Lu plating Hee Tae's anolini]

480
00:20:53,898 --> 00:20:55,566
Who made this?

481
00:20:55,566 --> 00:20:56,868
Hee Tae.

482
00:20:56,868 --> 00:20:58,002
- Pretty.
- Huh?

483
00:20:58,002 --> 00:21:00,271
I said it's pretty.

484
00:21:00,271 --> 00:21:01,839
Bravo!

485
00:21:01,839 --> 00:21:05,409
She praised him where he couldn't hear.

486
00:21:05,409 --> 00:21:07,545
[Hee Tae has no idea about the praise]

487
00:21:07,545 --> 00:21:10,347
- Didn't hear a word, not one.
- That's genuine.

488
00:21:12,416 --> 00:21:18,015
[One by one with care]

489
00:21:20,024 --> 00:21:21,526
[Hard at work]

490
00:21:21,526 --> 00:21:25,897
[Why does this hurt to watch]

491
00:21:25,897 --> 00:21:29,867
[Hee Tae lost in his work]

492
00:21:29,867 --> 00:21:33,538
[And Sorem watching his back]

493
00:21:33,538 --> 00:21:36,474
[Dark]
Why does Sorem look so worn out?

494
00:21:36,474 --> 00:21:37,809
All of a sudden.

495
00:21:37,809 --> 00:21:40,111
- Looks like she'd stab him with a fork.
- Right?

496
00:21:40,111 --> 00:21:42,479
[Watching Hee Tae's every move]
Like, "That's my spot."

497
00:21:43,581 --> 00:21:44,949
Sorem.

498
00:21:44,949 --> 00:21:46,918
He's better than you, leave him alone.

499
00:21:46,918 --> 00:21:48,252
No, I was just checking if he was adding flour.

500
00:21:48,252 --> 00:21:51,355
- He's doing fine, leave him.
- That's a bit much for Sorem...

501
00:21:52,123 --> 00:21:54,846
[Slide...]

502
00:21:56,561 --> 00:21:58,328
[Whimper]
My heart hurts.

503
00:22:00,031 --> 00:22:02,533
[Now I'm curious]

504
00:22:02,533 --> 00:22:04,569
[About what Sorem is thinking]

505
00:22:04,569 --> 00:22:06,571
[Uncomfortable?]
So awkward.

506
00:22:06,571 --> 00:22:08,105
Can you go somewhere else?

507
00:22:08,105 --> 00:22:10,107
- Must be uncomfortable.
- Oh, so awkward.

508
00:22:10,107 --> 00:22:11,409
[Sorem, you aren't upset, right?]

509
00:22:11,409 --> 00:22:17,114
How do I put it... my situation is unique.

510
00:22:17,114 --> 00:22:21,953
I was happy with my role in this kitchen,
making fresh pasta.

511
00:22:21,953 --> 00:22:26,524
But then Hee Tae came
and I had to work a new section.

512
00:22:26,524 --> 00:22:29,427
I was actually worried
about whether I could pull my weight.

513
00:22:29,427 --> 00:22:31,462
- So sweet.
- This kid is too sweet.

514
00:22:31,462 --> 00:22:32,997
[Q. Ever jealous of Hee Tae?]

515
00:22:32,997 --> 00:22:34,232
[Stunned]
No.

516
00:22:34,232 --> 00:22:39,136
If anything, I thought I'd be in the way.

517
00:22:39,136 --> 00:22:44,642
Because anything outside the pasta section
isn't familiar to me.

518
00:22:44,642 --> 00:22:48,246
[That worried face was about being in the way]
He was worried he'd get in the way.

519
00:22:48,246 --> 00:22:51,649
Hee Tae has things he needs to work on, but...

520
00:22:51,649 --> 00:22:53,417
He's got stuff to work on, sure.

521
00:22:53,417 --> 00:22:54,919
From Sorem's view, definitely!

522
00:22:54,919 --> 00:22:56,187
- He made that mistake earlier.
- Yeah.

523
00:22:56,187 --> 00:22:58,155
- Of course there's stuff to work on!
- That potato pasta earlier...

524
00:22:58,155 --> 00:22:59,257
You have to admit that.

525
00:22:59,257 --> 00:23:01,525
To Sorem, he's still a shaky junior.

526
00:23:01,525 --> 00:23:03,661
- Of course!
- He caught his mistake.

527
00:23:03,661 --> 00:23:05,563
[Senior Sorem]
He messed up on something important.

528
00:23:05,563 --> 00:23:10,201
[Super serious]
Overall, for a first try, it's good.

529
00:23:10,201 --> 00:23:11,135
[Even little senior Sorem gives a nod]

530
00:23:11,135 --> 00:23:12,869
This is fun.

531
00:23:13,471 --> 00:23:16,340
But from what I saw of Sorem,
he's so sweet.

532
00:23:16,340 --> 00:23:19,810
- This kid is too sweet...
- Now I see he's letting his mistake slide.

533
00:23:20,878 --> 00:23:22,425
[More flour! Don't forget!]
Sorem is so sweet.

534
00:23:22,425 --> 00:23:24,415
Everyone here is sweet.

535
00:23:24,415 --> 00:23:26,217
[Lu walks up to Hee Tae]

536
00:23:26,217 --> 00:23:28,419
Okay.

537
00:23:28,419 --> 00:23:31,055
Grab a tray,

538
00:23:31,055 --> 00:23:32,590
fill it with fresh pasta,

539
00:23:32,590 --> 00:23:34,992
and go show the guests.

540
00:23:34,992 --> 00:23:37,161
- They do that too?
- So they do that too.

541
00:23:37,161 --> 00:23:39,130
[Like this]
"Good evening, that's fresh pasta."

542
00:23:39,130 --> 00:23:40,398
[Wait, what?]
Oh, you have to do that too?

543
00:23:40,398 --> 00:23:41,699
This kind of thing...

544
00:23:41,699 --> 00:23:44,468
- That's so not your personality.
- Right?

545
00:23:45,503 --> 00:23:47,004
Good evening, ladies and gentlemen!

546
00:23:47,004 --> 00:23:49,840
We'd like to show you
the fresh pasta we just made.

547
00:23:49,840 --> 00:23:53,510
[Introvert headache]
Hey, asking him to do this?

548
00:23:54,512 --> 00:23:55,646
[Showing the guests his pasta]
Pheasant agnolotti.

549
00:23:55,646 --> 00:23:57,348
- Cheese tortelli.
- Goes around table to table.

550
00:23:57,348 --> 00:23:59,717
[Not easy]

551
00:23:59,717 --> 00:24:01,518
[Only the maker of the pasta can do this]
Thank you.

552
00:24:02,119 --> 00:24:03,421
Is this a regular thing?

553
00:24:03,421 --> 00:24:04,755
It's a regular thing.

554
00:24:04,755 --> 00:24:06,357
[A key part of the Parma restaurant]

555
00:24:06,357 --> 00:24:09,660
[Double trouble for introverts]
Next to gelato, this was the hardest.

556
00:24:09,660 --> 00:24:12,295
This is a full-on personality makeover.

557
00:24:13,364 --> 00:24:14,832
[Save Hee Tae]
He's in trouble.

558
00:24:14,832 --> 00:24:17,034
[In front of the guests?]

559
00:24:17,034 --> 00:24:18,302
- Me?
- Yeah.

560
00:24:18,302 --> 00:24:20,838
You've really picked up a lot here.

561
00:24:20,838 --> 00:24:22,773
[Another shock after the square potato...]
There's been a lot to learn here.

562
00:24:22,773 --> 00:24:24,008
- Hee Tae!
- Yes!

563
00:24:24,008 --> 00:24:25,643
You explain it!

564
00:24:25,643 --> 00:24:27,611
[No backing out ]
You're talking to the guests.

565
00:24:27,611 --> 00:24:31,215
[A sudden high-stakes mission]

566
00:24:31,215 --> 00:24:33,017
- I'll try.
- You have to go alone.

567
00:24:33,017 --> 00:24:34,751
Alone?

568
00:24:35,419 --> 00:24:37,221
[Just kidding]

569
00:24:37,221 --> 00:24:38,823
[Phew]

570
00:24:38,823 --> 00:24:41,726
We're going to do
a little show for the customers.

571
00:24:41,726 --> 00:24:43,594
Good evening, everyone!

572
00:24:43,594 --> 00:24:46,998
We'd like to show you our fresh pasta.

573
00:24:46,998 --> 00:24:48,244
We have potato tortelli,

574
00:24:48,244 --> 00:24:49,500
cheese tortelli, and tagliatelle.

575
00:24:49,500 --> 00:24:50,835
- It was tough.
- You have to say it yourself like this, okay?

576
00:24:50,835 --> 00:24:53,004
He has to say all that in Italian too.

577
00:24:53,004 --> 00:24:54,205
[Three Italian lines Hee Tae must say]

578
00:24:54,205 --> 00:24:56,326
Three of them?

579
00:24:56,326 --> 00:24:59,043
- Signori buonasera.
- Signori buonasera.

580
00:24:59,043 --> 00:25:01,445
Volevo farvi vedere le nostre paste freshe.

581
00:25:01,445 --> 00:25:04,915
Tortelli di patate, erbetta, tagliatelle...

582
00:25:04,915 --> 00:25:06,917
[Super hard!]

583
00:25:06,917 --> 00:25:08,786
Could you actually do that right now?

584
00:25:08,786 --> 00:25:10,721
No way.

585
00:25:11,355 --> 00:25:12,356
Okay.

586
00:25:12,356 --> 00:25:13,424
Yeah, say it like this.

587
00:25:13,424 --> 00:25:16,560
Here you are our fresh pasta.

588
00:25:16,560 --> 00:25:17,595
Go on, say it.

589
00:25:17,595 --> 00:25:19,764
[Can Hee Tae pull off the pasta intro?]

590
00:25:19,764 --> 00:25:21,032
[Finally at the customer's table]
You tell the guys.

591
00:25:21,032 --> 00:25:22,433
[Tense...]
Good evening guys.

592
00:25:22,433 --> 00:25:23,367
Come on, say it!

593
00:25:23,367 --> 00:25:24,802
Good evening, everyone.

594
00:25:24,802 --> 00:25:25,669
Come on, say it!

595
00:25:25,669 --> 00:25:28,873
- Here you are...
- Oh no.

596
00:25:28,873 --> 00:25:30,875
This is our fresh pasta.

597
00:25:30,875 --> 00:25:32,510
Thank you.

598
00:25:32,510 --> 00:25:33,878
That's it, perfect!

599
00:25:33,878 --> 00:25:35,312
Shall we keep going?

600
00:25:35,312 --> 00:25:36,747
[Somehow nailed the first table]

601
00:25:36,747 --> 00:25:39,150
[Nerve-racking...]
Just do the same thing at every table.

602
00:25:39,150 --> 00:25:40,851
- Buonasera!
- Sera.

603
00:25:40,851 --> 00:25:41,786
- "Sera."
- Sera.

604
00:25:41,786 --> 00:25:43,487
[Shyly repeats the greeting and starts]
Our fresh pasta.

605
00:25:43,487 --> 00:25:44,555
[Way to go, Sam Kim!]
So beautiful.

606
00:25:44,555 --> 00:25:46,490
Beautiful pasta.

607
00:25:47,992 --> 00:25:49,093
Thank you.

608
00:25:49,093 --> 00:25:51,162
[A shy smile at the warm response]

609
00:25:51,162 --> 00:25:54,365
Now try telling them what kind of pasta it is.

610
00:25:54,365 --> 00:25:55,433
Potato, and...

611
00:25:55,433 --> 00:25:59,003
[Difficulty spike]
Potato tortelli, cheese tortelli, tagliatelle.

612
00:25:59,003 --> 00:26:01,038
[Explaining is still too much for Hee Tae]
- Thank you. - Thank you.

613
00:26:01,038 --> 00:26:02,773
- You made this so well!
- Thank you.

614
00:26:02,773 --> 00:26:05,342
[Hee Tae's fresh pasta gets a glowing review]
Like a real pasta master!

615
00:26:06,377 --> 00:26:08,813
Try smiling a little more next time.

616
00:26:08,813 --> 00:26:12,149
Smile, man! Come on, crack a smile!

617
00:26:12,149 --> 00:26:15,252
- Our fresh pasta.
- Show some teeth!

618
00:26:15,252 --> 00:26:17,021
[Teeth: deployed]

619
00:26:17,021 --> 00:26:18,689
Okay.

620
00:26:18,689 --> 00:26:20,091
Here you are.

621
00:26:20,091 --> 00:26:22,860
[Shy, but showing off his own pasta]
Our fresh pasta.

622
00:26:22,860 --> 00:26:24,628
Our fresh pasta.

623
00:26:24,628 --> 00:26:27,731
- The pasta was incredible.
- Really?

624
00:26:27,731 --> 00:26:32,002
- After doing it a bunch of times...
- Right, the same line every time.

625
00:26:32,002 --> 00:26:33,871
- Thank you! He's the one who made them.
- Thank you.

626
00:26:33,871 --> 00:26:35,106
I made them.

627
00:26:35,106 --> 00:26:39,043
- Bravo!
- Best pasta I've ever had.

628
00:26:39,043 --> 00:26:40,744
[Bashful at the praise...]
- Bravo! - Seriously?

629
00:26:40,744 --> 00:26:43,013
The dough's so thin,
and the filling just melts in your mouth.

630
00:26:43,013 --> 00:26:45,483
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

631
00:26:45,483 --> 00:26:48,618
- You made this pasta yourself?
- Yes, I made it myself.

632
00:26:49,787 --> 00:26:51,487
- Thank you.
- Bravo!

633
00:26:52,256 --> 00:26:53,524
Thank you.

634
00:26:53,524 --> 00:26:54,658
[Pasta showcase ends in big praise]

635
00:26:54,658 --> 00:26:56,494
[Thumbs up]

636
00:26:56,494 --> 00:26:58,362
[Well done!]

637
00:26:58,362 --> 00:27:00,064
You could really tell they meant it

638
00:27:00,064 --> 00:27:02,900
- when they said it was beautiful.
- Yeah, you could.

639
00:27:02,900 --> 00:27:04,568
- The people...
- You could just feel it.

640
00:27:04,568 --> 00:27:06,564
- Right, everyone walks away feeling good.
- Yeah.

641
00:27:06,564 --> 00:27:09,840
- And the people making it feel proud, too.
- Right, exactly.

642
00:27:09,840 --> 00:27:11,041
[Back to the kitchen after the showcase]

643
00:27:11,041 --> 00:27:13,810
- You did amazing!
- Okay.

644
00:27:16,180 --> 00:27:18,082
Hee Tae, how was it out there?

645
00:27:18,082 --> 00:27:19,316
How was it?

646
00:27:19,316 --> 00:27:21,152
Did you enjoy talking with the customers?

647
00:27:21,152 --> 00:27:23,320
Yes.

648
00:27:23,320 --> 00:27:27,591
[I was so embarrassed...]

649
00:27:27,591 --> 00:27:32,329
[Caught off guard, but he pulled through]

650
00:27:32,329 --> 00:27:35,699
[Meanwhile, Senior Lu's out in the dining room]

651
00:27:35,699 --> 00:27:38,302
What's that chef's name?

652
00:27:38,302 --> 00:27:40,070
The chef's name? Gianpietro.

653
00:27:40,070 --> 00:27:42,206
No, I mean the Korean guy from earlier.

654
00:27:42,206 --> 00:27:44,175
[Surprise]
Oh, Hee Tae!

655
00:27:44,175 --> 00:27:47,545
My daughter's really into Korea.

656
00:27:47,545 --> 00:27:48,879
Do you know him?

657
00:27:48,879 --> 00:27:49,980
Huh?

658
00:27:49,980 --> 00:27:52,176
Wait, hold on.

659
00:27:52,176 --> 00:27:54,251
- Hee Tae.
- Hee Tae.

660
00:27:54,251 --> 00:27:56,219
[Asked his name, now typing it in?]
Hee Tae.

661
00:27:57,121 --> 00:27:58,656
Don't tell me he's looking him up.

662
00:27:58,656 --> 00:27:59,723
[Tension rising]

663
00:27:59,723 --> 00:28:01,258
Hee Tae.

664
00:28:01,258 --> 00:28:03,059
[Is Sam Kim about to get exposed?]
Right here?

665
00:28:04,828 --> 00:28:09,833
[Let's see... Hee... Tae...]

666
00:28:09,833 --> 00:28:12,136
- Do you know him?
- No! Just curious.

667
00:28:12,136 --> 00:28:13,704
Hee Tae.

668
00:28:13,704 --> 00:28:17,608
[Just curious about Hee Tae]

669
00:28:17,608 --> 00:28:19,722
My daughter's obsessed with Korea.

670
00:28:19,722 --> 00:28:21,378
She went last year
and she's going back this year.

671
00:28:21,378 --> 00:28:22,646
Okay.

672
00:28:22,646 --> 00:28:24,815
[Crisis averted, undercover still safe]

673
00:28:24,815 --> 00:28:28,085
[Clueless "celebrity" Hee Tae cleans on]

674
00:28:28,085 --> 00:28:29,853
Chef Gianpi!

675
00:28:29,853 --> 00:28:32,389
Can I have Hee Tae do more gelato service?

676
00:28:32,389 --> 00:28:34,925
- Of course!
- Come.

677
00:28:34,925 --> 00:28:36,860
Hearing your name called was the worst, right?

678
00:28:36,860 --> 00:28:37,962
You hated hearing your name, didn't you?

679
00:28:37,962 --> 00:28:40,331
The worst.

680
00:28:40,331 --> 00:28:43,534
[Hee Tae's a bundle of nerves, of course]

681
00:28:43,534 --> 00:28:45,069
Smile.

682
00:28:45,069 --> 00:28:46,903
Hee Tae.

683
00:28:48,072 --> 00:28:49,873
Hee Tae.

684
00:28:51,909 --> 00:28:53,810
Hee Tae's so cute.

685
00:28:54,411 --> 00:28:56,614
You're doing amazing.

686
00:28:56,614 --> 00:28:58,249
I mean it.

687
00:28:58,249 --> 00:29:00,751
[Refocusing and heading back out]
You say chocolate, hazelnuts.

688
00:29:00,751 --> 00:29:04,388
But don't worry, you're very good.

689
00:29:04,388 --> 00:29:07,080
[Nerves]

690
00:29:07,925 --> 00:29:09,026
Gelato?

691
00:29:09,026 --> 00:29:14,765
[A brave first word]

692
00:29:14,765 --> 00:29:16,300
[Taking the order]
What flavor?

693
00:29:16,300 --> 00:29:17,368
Yes.

694
00:29:17,368 --> 00:29:19,937
By the way, how do you say "please" in Korean?

695
00:29:19,937 --> 00:29:21,705
- Booh-tak-ham-ni-da.
- Booh-tak-ham-ni-da.

696
00:29:21,705 --> 00:29:23,874
And "kam-sa-ham-ni-da" is "thank you," right?

697
00:29:23,874 --> 00:29:25,576
- So "booh-tak-ham-ni-da" is "please?"
- Right.

698
00:29:25,576 --> 00:29:28,846
Booh-tak-ham-ni-da! Gelato.

699
00:29:28,846 --> 00:29:30,314
[Local customer ordering in solid Korean]
"Booh-tak-ham-ni-da"... that's something.

700
00:29:30,314 --> 00:29:32,515
- Yes.
- Booh-tak-ham-ni-da.

701
00:29:34,585 --> 00:29:36,854
- People here are really warm.
- They're really into it.

702
00:29:36,854 --> 00:29:38,255
They're so warm.

703
00:29:38,255 --> 00:29:42,159
[Senior Lu, beaming]

704
00:29:42,159 --> 00:29:45,062
He's really good. He's got great hands.

705
00:29:45,062 --> 00:29:49,333
I never got to see Hee Tae's resume.
I'm curious now.

706
00:29:49,333 --> 00:29:50,601
[Suspiciously fast learner for a rookie]

707
00:29:50,601 --> 00:29:52,970
How long has he been working here?

708
00:29:52,970 --> 00:29:55,773
- Since yesterday.
- What's his name?

709
00:29:55,773 --> 00:29:57,741
He's a hit.

710
00:29:57,741 --> 00:29:59,677
- Kim Hee Tae.
- That's a tough one.

711
00:29:59,677 --> 00:30:00,978
My name is Hee Tae.

712
00:30:00,978 --> 00:30:02,413
[Mustering up the courage in Italian]

713
00:30:02,413 --> 00:30:06,116
"Mi chiamo..." Nice job!

714
00:30:06,116 --> 00:30:07,193
- Hee Tae.
- Hee Tae.

715
00:30:07,193 --> 00:30:08,585
- Right.
- Hee Tae.

716
00:30:08,585 --> 00:30:11,355
[Everyone's hooked on Hee Tae]
- They're trying to remember it. - Kim Hee Tae.

717
00:30:11,355 --> 00:30:13,190
So how do you like Italy?

718
00:30:13,190 --> 00:30:15,693
It's amazing.

719
00:30:15,693 --> 00:30:21,265
Working at a restaurant in Italy
has been my dream.

720
00:30:21,265 --> 00:30:23,300
And now I'm living it.

721
00:30:23,300 --> 00:30:24,301
Yeah.

722
00:30:24,301 --> 00:30:25,836
[Carefully]
Kam-sa-ham-ni-da.

723
00:30:25,836 --> 00:30:26,904
You're welcome.

724
00:30:26,904 --> 00:30:28,038
[Gelato service wrapped up nicely]

725
00:30:28,038 --> 00:30:29,540
- You're welcome.
- A lot of words.

726
00:30:29,540 --> 00:30:32,109
[Boss is pleased]

727
00:30:32,109 --> 00:30:33,911
You know what I really envy?

728
00:30:33,911 --> 00:30:36,080
The way the cook and the customer
actually talk like that.

729
00:30:36,080 --> 00:30:37,181
- Doing that...
- Right.

730
00:30:37,181 --> 00:30:39,450
It really builds a connection.

731
00:30:39,450 --> 00:30:41,760
[A Parma tradition rarely seen in Korea]
You don't really see that back home.

732
00:30:41,760 --> 00:30:44,121
- Right.
- Honestly, I'm jealous of that.

733
00:30:44,121 --> 00:30:45,688
You should try that. I think it'd work great.

734
00:30:45,688 --> 00:30:48,635
- I've actually been thinking about doing that.
- Right?

735
00:30:48,635 --> 00:30:50,194
- Oh, really?
- You walk right up to the table,

736
00:30:50,194 --> 00:30:52,496
[Doing the pasta showcase too!]
"Pretty pasta, right?"

737
00:30:52,496 --> 00:30:53,764
"How about our pasta?"

738
00:30:53,764 --> 00:30:55,899
Get one of those baby slings.

739
00:30:55,899 --> 00:30:59,203
Put on a baby sling and go,
"How about our pasta?"

740
00:30:59,203 --> 00:31:00,804
[Hard sell]
- I think it could work. - But...

741
00:31:00,804 --> 00:31:02,840
Once this airs,

742
00:31:02,840 --> 00:31:05,676
my staff are going to be a little on edge.

743
00:31:05,676 --> 00:31:09,113
[Bracing for the new policy?]
- "Are we getting roped into this too?" - Yes.

744
00:31:09,113 --> 00:31:11,482
[Good things are meant to be shared]
Like, "Now it's your turn to suffer."

745
00:31:11,482 --> 00:31:15,053
[After the last gelato run...]

746
00:31:15,053 --> 00:31:21,053
[Hee Tae powered through it all]

747
00:31:21,892 --> 00:31:25,162
Are you usually this shy?

748
00:31:25,162 --> 00:31:26,997
Hee Tae, are you shy?

749
00:31:26,997 --> 00:31:29,466
[A little bit?]

750
00:31:29,466 --> 00:31:30,934
Okay.

751
00:31:30,934 --> 00:31:34,772
It's because my Italian isn't good.

752
00:31:34,772 --> 00:31:36,840
- It makes me really embarrassed.
- Okay.

753
00:31:36,840 --> 00:31:39,009
Don't worry,
I'll help you out as much as you need.

754
00:31:39,009 --> 00:31:41,011
Okay.

755
00:31:41,011 --> 00:31:43,347
[Lucky to have such great seniors]
You'll be sad to leave on day five.

756
00:31:43,347 --> 00:31:46,282
- Looks like you're already attached.
- Yeah, exactly.

757
00:31:48,952 --> 00:31:51,655
[10:00 PM]

758
00:31:51,655 --> 00:31:54,858
[Service ends]

759
00:31:54,858 --> 00:31:56,293
[A particularly rough day
for rookie Hee Tae...]

760
00:31:56,293 --> 00:31:57,728
[Showdown with Senior Lu, FIFO accomplice]

761
00:31:57,728 --> 00:32:03,668
[Square potato disaster,
pasta intro, gelato runs]

762
00:32:05,402 --> 00:32:07,304
[Casually]

763
00:32:07,304 --> 00:32:09,706
- You alright?
- Yes.

764
00:32:09,706 --> 00:32:11,408
- Okay?
- Yeah.

765
00:32:11,408 --> 00:32:13,811
Everything's fine.

766
00:32:13,811 --> 00:32:17,347
Tomorrow, I'll...

767
00:32:17,347 --> 00:32:19,550
be more proactive.

768
00:32:19,550 --> 00:32:21,518
- "Piu?"
- More proactive.

769
00:32:21,518 --> 00:32:23,687
- Proactive?
- More proactive.

770
00:32:23,687 --> 00:32:25,756
- Proactive?
- Yeah.

771
00:32:25,756 --> 00:32:28,625
[And he promises the head chef he'll do better]
- Yes. - Bravo.

772
00:32:29,293 --> 00:32:32,395
- You're doing great.
- Thank you.

773
00:32:33,330 --> 00:32:35,299
Tomorrow...

774
00:32:35,299 --> 00:32:36,200
[Over there]

775
00:32:36,200 --> 00:32:37,100
Huh?

776
00:32:37,100 --> 00:32:38,836
- Huh?
- Huh?

777
00:32:38,836 --> 00:32:41,238
[No. 1 Gianpietro gestures to the stove]
- Already? - What is it?

778
00:32:41,238 --> 00:32:43,307
- No pasta.
- Yeah.

779
00:32:43,307 --> 00:32:46,143
Let's put you on cured meats as well.

780
00:32:46,143 --> 00:32:48,345
- Me?
- Yes.

781
00:32:48,345 --> 00:32:49,813
[Is this really happening?]
Moving up to plating?

782
00:32:49,813 --> 00:32:51,714
Escaping rookie status?

783
00:32:52,649 --> 00:32:54,618
Next step!

784
00:32:54,618 --> 00:32:56,787
Next step!

785
00:32:56,787 --> 00:32:58,622
Next step?

786
00:32:58,622 --> 00:33:00,724
[Day two, and Hee Tae's bumped up!]
He got recognized.

787
00:33:00,724 --> 00:33:04,461
- Hee Tae got the first promotion.
- On day two.

788
00:33:04,461 --> 00:33:06,830
It was me?

789
00:33:06,830 --> 00:33:09,633
[First rookie out: Hee Tae]
So it was Sam Kim.

790
00:33:09,633 --> 00:33:11,668
I thought it was me.

791
00:33:11,668 --> 00:33:14,671
I thought he'd be the last to move up.

792
00:33:14,671 --> 00:33:17,106
[The result no one expected]
I was doing it on purpose.

793
00:33:18,742 --> 00:33:20,644
[Tomorrow on, paired with No. 2]

794
00:33:20,644 --> 00:33:23,446
[Out of the fresh pasta station]

795
00:33:24,226 --> 00:33:26,750
[Hehehe...]

796
00:33:26,750 --> 00:33:27,985
How are you feeling?

797
00:33:27,985 --> 00:33:30,187
[Can't stop smiling]

798
00:33:30,187 --> 00:33:34,357
Feels like it was meant to be.

799
00:33:35,025 --> 00:33:36,960
Look at him. Suddenly all puffed up?

800
00:33:36,960 --> 00:33:39,363
- That's my line.
- Swagger.

801
00:33:39,363 --> 00:33:42,366
He told me he was keeping an eye on me.

802
00:33:42,366 --> 00:33:45,435
Felt like he was trying to teach me everything.

803
00:33:45,435 --> 00:33:47,904
That came through.

804
00:33:48,605 --> 00:33:51,575
I do things step by step.

805
00:33:51,575 --> 00:33:56,680
I try to let them figure things out,
but share as much knowledge as I can.

806
00:33:56,680 --> 00:33:59,883
[Hee Tae's effort paid off,
and No. 1 moved him up]

807
00:33:59,883 --> 00:34:01,318
Thank you.

808
00:34:01,318 --> 00:34:02,586
- That must feel good!
- Look at his face.

809
00:34:02,586 --> 00:34:04,521
- Thank you.
- Look at his face.

810
00:34:04,521 --> 00:34:07,590
[Pure happiness shows]
That's a happy face right there.

811
00:34:10,260 --> 00:34:13,229
[Sam Kim, the first to move up]
A face that happy, honestly...

812
00:34:13,964 --> 00:34:17,067
I was thrilled, despite all the mistakes.

813
00:34:17,067 --> 00:34:20,203
My only goal was to show
I was giving it everything.

814
00:34:20,203 --> 00:34:22,673
[Hee Tae's quiet effort earned the move-up]
Looks like that made a good impression.

815
00:34:22,673 --> 00:34:26,576
Felt like he saw me as worth investing in.

816
00:34:27,344 --> 00:34:28,011
[Italy, Naples]
[Not Kwon Sung Jun, but Sam Kwon]

817
00:34:28,011 --> 00:34:29,046
[Morning service, undercover day two]

818
00:34:29,046 --> 00:34:30,013
[Crisis hits on day two]

819
00:34:30,013 --> 00:34:32,549
What's going on?

820
00:34:32,549 --> 00:34:35,918
[Italian Father's Day]

821
00:34:36,653 --> 00:34:38,322
- That's chaos right there.
- How is he going to handle all that?

822
00:34:38,322 --> 00:34:40,524
- You put all the antipasto in the oven?
- Yes.

823
00:34:40,524 --> 00:34:42,726
[Focus]
That's not it.

824
00:34:42,726 --> 00:34:44,828
[Rookie Kwon stumbled all service long]
No, again.

825
00:34:44,828 --> 00:34:47,764
You can't do it that way.

826
00:34:47,764 --> 00:34:51,134
- The way you're doing it isn't good enough.
- Okay.

827
00:34:51,134 --> 00:34:52,869
You need the "Congratulations" garnish.

828
00:34:52,869 --> 00:34:55,672
- You told me you got it.
- Yes.

829
00:34:55,672 --> 00:34:58,341
[Worn-out Kwon]
You can tell me when you don't understand.

830
00:34:59,343 --> 00:35:00,877
[Senior An's getting irritated]
Table eight.

831
00:35:00,877 --> 00:35:02,512
One antipasti, two meatballs...

832
00:35:02,512 --> 00:35:04,247
[Sprinting around, face flushed red]

833
00:35:04,247 --> 00:35:06,550
- Kwon!
- Yes.

834
00:35:06,550 --> 00:35:07,618
- Kwon!
- Yes.

835
00:35:07,618 --> 00:35:11,688
- Come outside with me!
- Okay.

836
00:35:11,688 --> 00:35:17,393
[Dragged out by Senior An, no idea why...]

837
00:35:18,996 --> 00:35:22,933
[Just the two of them]

838
00:35:22,933 --> 00:35:24,801
[What is going on here...]
Seriously?

839
00:35:28,238 --> 00:35:29,962
[Holding his breath]

840
00:35:31,842 --> 00:35:33,976
[What's he going to do with him?]
What's he about to say?

841
00:35:34,611 --> 00:35:36,913
Senior An, why?

842
00:35:36,913 --> 00:35:38,930
[Gulp...]

843
00:35:41,518 --> 00:35:43,186
A little breather, right?

844
00:35:43,186 --> 00:35:45,022
[Vigorous nodding]

845
00:35:45,022 --> 00:35:46,456
[Oh, Senior An...]

846
00:35:46,456 --> 00:35:47,591
[Such a softie]
Oh, a break.

847
00:35:47,591 --> 00:35:49,760
[Senior An's softer side, who knew]
He's actually pretty sweet.

848
00:35:49,760 --> 00:35:52,929
[Senior An gave overwhelmed Kwon
some breathing room]

849
00:35:52,929 --> 00:35:57,234
[A moment to breathe at last]

850
00:35:57,234 --> 00:35:58,514
Today's lunch had

851
00:35:58,514 --> 00:36:01,004
- 30 to 35 guests, right?
- Yes.

852
00:36:01,004 --> 00:36:04,174
- This coming weekend,
- Yes.

853
00:36:04,174 --> 00:36:07,511
- we're looking at 70 to 80.
- 70?

854
00:36:07,511 --> 00:36:09,146
- That's insane.
- That's double.

855
00:36:09,146 --> 00:36:10,647
[This is the easy day]
This is insane.

856
00:36:10,647 --> 00:36:13,116
We're three in the kitchen
and there are 70 guests.

857
00:36:13,116 --> 00:36:14,751
[Disaster...]

858
00:36:14,751 --> 00:36:16,420
[Suddenly remembering the words...]
A word of resolve.

859
00:36:16,420 --> 00:36:18,789
Mai paura.

860
00:36:18,789 --> 00:36:20,824
[I'm afraid...]
Paura.

861
00:36:20,824 --> 00:36:21,992
Paura?

862
00:36:21,992 --> 00:36:23,627
[Day two, and fear shows up]
"Paura" already?

863
00:36:23,627 --> 00:36:24,961
Not "mai" anymore.

864
00:36:24,961 --> 00:36:26,763
[Struggling now... and double the crowd ahead?]

865
00:36:26,763 --> 00:36:27,931
Nothing I can do.

866
00:36:27,931 --> 00:36:31,068
No point thinking about what's done.

867
00:36:31,068 --> 00:36:33,336
Just look ahead.

868
00:36:33,336 --> 00:36:35,972
"Why did I mess that up?" "Am I stupid?"

869
00:36:35,972 --> 00:36:38,041
You do that, and you can't do the next task.

870
00:36:38,041 --> 00:36:40,811
Clear your head, keep your hands moving.

871
00:36:40,811 --> 00:36:42,279
- See you later, Kwon.
- Yes.

872
00:36:42,279 --> 00:36:45,549
[After a grueling lunch service...]
- See you later. - Rest well.

873
00:36:45,549 --> 00:36:48,251
[Heading home during the break...]
Oh, it's break time now.

874
00:36:48,702 --> 00:36:51,538
[But where's Kwon?]
Huh? He didn't go home?

875
00:36:52,539 --> 00:36:53,607
[Stuck on the couch]

876
00:36:53,607 --> 00:36:55,475
He's on the couch?

877
00:36:56,210 --> 00:36:59,446
- Too tired to even get changed.
- No energy left to climb the stairs.

878
00:36:59,446 --> 00:37:01,715
[No energy for stairs, glued to the couch...]
I didn't feel like changing.

879
00:37:01,715 --> 00:37:05,853
[Out of energy, just scrolling]

880
00:37:05,853 --> 00:37:11,091
[6:10 PM, resting until back to work]

881
00:37:11,091 --> 00:37:12,860
[The mashed hair says it all]

882
00:37:12,860 --> 00:37:14,895
Just looking at it is exhausting.

883
00:37:14,895 --> 00:37:17,385
[No matter the rest, still drained...]
[Eyeing him]

884
00:37:21,669 --> 00:37:23,570
You know...

885
00:37:23,570 --> 00:37:26,539
He keeps getting bigger, though.

886
00:37:27,444 --> 00:37:28,709
[Day 1] [Day 2]
He's getting rounder.

887
00:37:28,709 --> 00:37:31,378
[Visibly puffier after just two days...]
His face is getting bigger?

888
00:37:31,378 --> 00:37:33,080
Why's my face so swollen?

889
00:37:33,080 --> 00:37:34,948
[Welling up]
Guess the food's working for you.

890
00:37:34,948 --> 00:37:38,518
[Not what you think, just exhausted...]
It's tired-puffy, that's all.

891
00:37:39,253 --> 00:37:43,724
[Back to work, still exhausted]

892
00:37:43,724 --> 00:37:47,027
[Meanwhile]

893
00:37:47,027 --> 00:37:50,597
[Seniors show up early, full of energy]

894
00:37:50,597 --> 00:37:53,300
[Didn't they work the same shift?]
Everyone else looks fine.

895
00:37:53,300 --> 00:37:56,203
- Gosh.
- You're here.

896
00:37:56,203 --> 00:37:58,305
[Eyes locked on]
What?

897
00:37:58,305 --> 00:37:59,907
[Covered up the tattoo?]
Let me see it.

898
00:37:59,907 --> 00:38:01,909
- The tattoo, yes.
- The tattoo.

899
00:38:01,909 --> 00:38:02,876
[Quick chat about the tattoo]

900
00:38:02,876 --> 00:38:04,011
- Huh?
- Old school.

901
00:38:04,011 --> 00:38:05,612
[Huddled in close]
People in Naples love tattoos.

902
00:38:05,612 --> 00:38:08,214
- Do the others have tattoos too?
- They all have them.

903
00:38:09,817 --> 00:38:13,609
I like that. Also these.

904
00:38:13,609 --> 00:38:15,456
- Is that Pulcinella?
- Is that Pulcinella?

905
00:38:15,456 --> 00:38:16,523
I did this.

906
00:38:16,523 --> 00:38:18,759
- Is that Pulcinella?
- Is that Pulcinella?

907
00:38:18,759 --> 00:38:20,727
I did this.

908
00:38:21,862 --> 00:38:23,597
[A classic symbol of Naples folk culture]
Pulcinella?

909
00:38:23,597 --> 00:38:24,959
It's a symbol of Naples.

910
00:38:31,609 --> 00:38:34,278
But Kwon's from the other side of the world...

911
00:38:34,278 --> 00:38:39,417
It was wild to see someone like him
with a Naples tattoo.

912
00:38:39,417 --> 00:38:41,419
- Oh, he's right.
- Code red.

913
00:38:41,419 --> 00:38:43,321
[Things are looking sketchy]
This is weird.

914
00:38:43,321 --> 00:38:45,723
Code red.

915
00:38:45,723 --> 00:38:47,825
[Surprised and intrigued]
Why does he even have

916
00:38:47,825 --> 00:38:49,305
a tattoo of a Naples symbol?

917
00:38:49,305 --> 00:38:50,661
It's weird, right?

918
00:38:50,661 --> 00:38:52,496
- Did you get it in Naples?
- Yeah, in Naples.

919
00:38:52,496 --> 00:38:53,864
[In Naples?]
Yeah, in Naples.

920
00:38:53,864 --> 00:38:56,132
You've been here before?

921
00:38:56,981 --> 00:38:58,269
Huh?

922
00:38:58,269 --> 00:38:59,837
- At that moment, a bit...
- Busted.

923
00:38:59,837 --> 00:39:01,639
- Right then...
- Senior An's catching on.

924
00:39:01,639 --> 00:39:02,539
[Cover about to get blown]
It's strange.

925
00:39:02,539 --> 00:39:05,042
- That was a code red moment...
- His hands moving so fast made it look off.

926
00:39:05,042 --> 00:39:06,744
[Close call]
That was code red right there.

927
00:39:06,744 --> 00:39:08,412
[Anxious...]

928
00:39:08,412 --> 00:39:11,548
[So basically...]

929
00:39:11,548 --> 00:39:13,416
I almost got caught.

930
00:39:15,452 --> 00:39:19,723
Originally, two days ago
I told them it was my first trip to Naples.

931
00:39:22,893 --> 00:39:24,795
This is my first time in Italy.

932
00:39:24,795 --> 00:39:26,363
So it's your first time.

933
00:39:26,363 --> 00:39:28,198
Right.

934
00:39:28,874 --> 00:39:30,267
[But he said it was his first time?]
The tattoo came up,

935
00:39:30,267 --> 00:39:32,136
and I told them I got it here.

936
00:39:32,136 --> 00:39:34,672
[Voice crack]
- Napoli. - Yes.

937
00:39:34,672 --> 00:39:37,274
I came once, ten years ago.

938
00:39:37,274 --> 00:39:39,009
Wait, seriously?

939
00:39:39,009 --> 00:39:40,878
[Something's not right]
Really?

940
00:39:40,878 --> 00:39:41,879
Really.

941
00:39:41,879 --> 00:39:44,448
- I just came up with something.
- He's getting suspicious.

942
00:39:44,448 --> 00:39:48,385
[Just shifty eyes]
The whole undercover plan's done.

943
00:39:48,385 --> 00:39:49,620
[Hands clenched tight...]
Code red.

944
00:39:49,620 --> 00:39:51,855
[Anxious watching this back]

945
00:39:51,855 --> 00:39:55,392
[Suspicious eyes burning from behind...]
[Mmm...]

946
00:39:55,392 --> 00:39:57,360
- Kwon.
- Yes.

947
00:39:58,128 --> 00:40:00,563
What restaurant did you work at back in Korea?

948
00:40:01,231 --> 00:40:02,733
[A pointed question from Senior An]
He's starting the interrogation.

949
00:40:02,733 --> 00:40:05,102
[Tense by association]
Senior An's officially grilling him now.

950
00:40:05,102 --> 00:40:09,340
- Because it's suspicious.
- Something like fine dining.

951
00:40:09,340 --> 00:40:10,841
Michelin, you know?

952
00:40:10,841 --> 00:40:13,277
[Baseball player with Michelin experience?]

953
00:40:13,277 --> 00:40:15,546
- A baseball player who worked at Michelin.
- It is kind of weird.

954
00:40:15,546 --> 00:40:18,983
What is he even saying?
Michelin hires just anybody?

955
00:40:18,983 --> 00:40:21,151
They take baseball players just like that?

956
00:40:21,151 --> 00:40:22,953
- A year, I worked there for a year.
- No way.

957
00:40:22,953 --> 00:40:25,622
Could a baseball player
even work at Michelin like that?

958
00:40:25,622 --> 00:40:27,524
[Too much backstory?]
Is that even possible at Michelin?

959
00:40:27,524 --> 00:40:29,159
- Well, you can work there, but...
- Yeah.

960
00:40:29,159 --> 00:40:32,796
- He keeps lying.
- He's digging himself into a hole.

961
00:40:32,796 --> 00:40:35,065
That was a real mistake. The tattoo, yeah.

962
00:40:35,065 --> 00:40:36,567
[Kwon ends up with a tangled story]
- Really? - Yeah.

963
00:40:36,567 --> 00:40:38,769
What was your station at Michelin?

964
00:40:38,769 --> 00:40:41,672
What was your station at Michelin?

965
00:40:41,672 --> 00:40:43,607
- Just a kitchen assistant.
- Yeah?

966
00:40:43,607 --> 00:40:46,677
Just helping out with desserts.

967
00:40:46,677 --> 00:40:48,412
- Desserts?
- I was thrown off.

968
00:40:48,412 --> 00:40:50,581
Just desserts?

969
00:40:50,581 --> 00:40:52,983
[Suspicion that won't quit]
My bad.

970
00:40:52,983 --> 00:40:54,752
- His ears are turning red.
- He was thrown off.

971
00:40:54,752 --> 00:40:56,353
[Red ears matching the panic]

972
00:40:56,353 --> 00:41:00,090
- That's why you're good with the piping bag.
- Yes.

973
00:41:00,090 --> 00:41:02,059
[Senior Pa and Luisa bought it]
They finally see

974
00:41:02,059 --> 00:41:04,161
why the piping bag worked so well.

975
00:41:04,161 --> 00:41:06,096
[Crisis averted]

976
00:41:06,096 --> 00:41:07,464
Classic Senior Pa.

977
00:41:07,464 --> 00:41:09,533
[Crisis averted thanks to Senior Pa]

978
00:41:09,533 --> 00:41:12,272
[Crisis narrowly avoided]

979
00:41:12,272 --> 00:41:14,872
See, small talk is dangerous.

980
00:41:14,872 --> 00:41:16,206
That's what you took from this?

981
00:41:16,206 --> 00:41:18,675
- Small talk always gets you in trouble.
- No more small talk.

982
00:41:18,675 --> 00:41:21,078
[Small talk did this]
Let's not talk to them.

983
00:41:21,078 --> 00:41:23,047
- Kwon, ready to start prep for dinner service?
- Yes.

984
00:41:23,047 --> 00:41:24,181
Let's go.

985
00:41:24,181 --> 00:41:27,017
[Sliding over]

986
00:41:27,017 --> 00:41:30,821
Did you write it down?
Didn't see you doing it today.

987
00:41:30,821 --> 00:41:33,390
- I didn't take notes today.
- I didn't see you take notes.

988
00:41:33,390 --> 00:41:35,359
So I studied at the place I'm staying.

989
00:41:35,359 --> 00:41:37,828
- Really?
- Yes.

990
00:41:37,828 --> 00:41:40,130
I studied the appetizers and desserts.

991
00:41:40,130 --> 00:41:45,736
Then we should do it, a quiz.

992
00:41:45,736 --> 00:41:47,971
- A quiz?
- A quiz?

993
00:41:47,971 --> 00:41:54,244
I wanted to check if Kwon really got

994
00:41:54,244 --> 00:41:56,080
what he was taught.

995
00:41:56,080 --> 00:42:01,618
Only then can he move up to the next level.

996
00:42:01,618 --> 00:42:03,180
- He's no pushover either.
- Really?

997
00:42:03,180 --> 00:42:04,721
[Surprise test incoming]
It's a test.

998
00:42:04,721 --> 00:42:05,789
- You're being tested.
- They do tests too?

999
00:42:05,789 --> 00:42:06,657
[Bring it on]

1000
00:42:06,657 --> 00:42:08,659
[Boss joins in]
How is the antipasto platter put together?

1001
00:42:08,659 --> 00:42:10,427
[And so it began]
The menu test.

1002
00:42:10,427 --> 00:42:13,230
How is the antipasto platter put together?

1003
00:42:13,230 --> 00:42:16,834
List everything you put on the platter.

1004
00:42:16,834 --> 00:42:19,837
Every single piece.

1005
00:42:19,837 --> 00:42:21,538
[Will he get it right the first time?]
What's in the antipasto?

1006
00:42:21,538 --> 00:42:23,740
Can you say that?

1007
00:42:23,740 --> 00:42:25,075
- Potato cake.
- Yeah.

1008
00:42:25,075 --> 00:42:26,143
- Potato cake.
- Potato cake.

1009
00:42:26,143 --> 00:42:27,644
What's in it?

1010
00:42:27,644 --> 00:42:29,913
Potatoes.

1011
00:42:29,913 --> 00:42:30,914
Sausage.

1012
00:42:30,914 --> 00:42:32,583
- Friarielli.
- Good.

1013
00:42:32,583 --> 00:42:34,985
[Subtly joining the group]
- Then... - Another one.

1014
00:42:34,985 --> 00:42:36,453
- Bravo! Well done!
- Okay.

1015
00:42:36,453 --> 00:42:38,088
Piece of cake, honestly.

1016
00:42:38,088 --> 00:42:39,790
Meatballs.

1017
00:42:39,790 --> 00:42:41,658
- Rice cake, polenta.
- Rice cake.

1018
00:42:41,658 --> 00:42:42,626
Rice.

1019
00:42:42,626 --> 00:42:44,428
With?

1020
00:42:44,428 --> 00:42:46,163
- Then?
- What else?

1021
00:42:46,163 --> 00:42:48,132
[Now what else...]

1022
00:42:48,132 --> 00:42:49,133
Beef rolls.

1023
00:42:49,133 --> 00:42:51,502
- Beef rolls.
- Yeah.

1024
00:42:51,502 --> 00:42:53,137
The beef rolls have salad inside.

1025
00:42:53,137 --> 00:42:54,851
And...

1026
00:42:54,851 --> 00:42:56,740
[Nonstop questions]
How do you season it?

1027
00:42:56,740 --> 00:42:58,675
What goes on the plate?

1028
00:42:58,675 --> 00:43:00,644
What goes on the plate?

1029
00:43:00,644 --> 00:43:02,312
- Balsamic sauce.
- Bravo.

1030
00:43:02,312 --> 00:43:03,914
Cheese.

1031
00:43:03,914 --> 00:43:06,783
Kwon did great,

1032
00:43:06,783 --> 00:43:08,185
he really did.

1033
00:43:08,185 --> 00:43:13,524
I think this is what really matters.

1034
00:43:13,524 --> 00:43:17,828
Because he actually understands
what he's working with.

1035
00:43:17,828 --> 00:43:18,962
Right.

1036
00:43:18,962 --> 00:43:20,676
The most important thing is

1037
00:43:20,676 --> 00:43:23,167
[Got the seniors' nod, test passed]
knowing your stuff inside and out.

1038
00:43:23,167 --> 00:43:27,905
[Feeling lighter, getting ready for service]

1039
00:43:27,905 --> 00:43:29,773
[But then...]

1040
00:43:29,773 --> 00:43:31,141
[Senior An, why again?]
What now?

1041
00:43:31,141 --> 00:43:33,777
[Twitchy]
What now? Senior An, why?

1042
00:43:33,777 --> 00:43:35,979
What's he up to?

1043
00:43:35,979 --> 00:43:38,248
- For tonight's service,
- Yes.

1044
00:43:38,248 --> 00:43:39,950
I'm going to back you up.

1045
00:43:39,950 --> 00:43:41,084
What?

1046
00:43:41,084 --> 00:43:42,186
You're running it solo.

1047
00:43:42,186 --> 00:43:43,387
Okay.

1048
00:43:43,387 --> 00:43:44,354
You're running it solo.

1049
00:43:44,354 --> 00:43:45,856
[Solo?]
Okay.

1050
00:43:45,856 --> 00:43:47,925
He wants him to do it alone.

1051
00:43:47,925 --> 00:43:51,995
It just so happens
that he gave me this opportunity.

1052
00:43:51,995 --> 00:43:55,666
[A huge task on his second day undercover]

1053
00:43:55,666 --> 00:43:56,900
[Running the appetizer station]

1054
00:43:56,900 --> 00:44:00,170
[Handling it all alone from start to finish]

1055
00:44:00,170 --> 00:44:02,439
Still, to some extent,
he must have earned their trust

1056
00:44:02,439 --> 00:44:04,675
- for them to let him do that, right?
- Right.

1057
00:44:04,675 --> 00:44:08,111
- He must have earned their trust.
- Exactly.

1058
00:44:08,111 --> 00:44:11,081
[Can he live up to their expectations?]

1059
00:44:11,081 --> 00:44:13,250
- Kwon.
- Yeah.

1060
00:44:13,250 --> 00:44:18,288
You know we have reservations for dinner.
So here is what you need to do.

1061
00:44:18,288 --> 00:44:20,089
Come over here.

1062
00:44:21,058 --> 00:44:23,093
[Checking the number of reservations!]
And we try to understand more or less

1063
00:44:23,093 --> 00:44:25,963
[Time to check]
how many tables we will serve today.

1064
00:44:25,963 --> 00:44:28,198
Okay. You just count roughly
how many people are coming.

1065
00:44:28,198 --> 00:44:29,466
Yes.

1066
00:44:29,466 --> 00:44:32,703
You always start by checking
the reservations like that.

1067
00:44:32,703 --> 00:44:35,572
[Figuring out the appetizers for each table]

1068
00:44:35,572 --> 00:44:36,719
38,

1069
00:44:36,719 --> 00:44:38,275
40.

1070
00:44:38,275 --> 00:44:39,876
- 44.
- 44.

1071
00:44:39,876 --> 00:44:43,447
[Seven portions at once is today's final test]
So we'll have 44 adults plus some kids.

1072
00:44:43,447 --> 00:44:44,281
Seven portions at once?

1073
00:44:44,281 --> 00:44:46,528
Based on the number of reservations,

1074
00:44:46,528 --> 00:44:48,785
[This won't be easy]
let's start prepping.

1075
00:44:48,785 --> 00:44:51,521
[8:00 PM Dinner service begins]
[44 reservations with different group sizes]

1076
00:44:51,521 --> 00:44:53,156
We have 44 reservations,

1077
00:44:53,156 --> 00:44:54,558
and we take walk-ins too.

1078
00:44:54,558 --> 00:44:56,927
[Keeping orders from backing up by himself]

1079
00:44:56,927 --> 00:44:58,762
[Not just cooking accurately]

1080
00:44:58,762 --> 00:45:00,897
[In exact order without missing anything]

1081
00:45:00,897 --> 00:45:02,499
[Communicating with the floor]
Table A?

1082
00:45:02,499 --> 00:45:03,300
Table A?

1083
00:45:03,300 --> 00:45:04,601
[Calling them right on time]
- Table A? - Yes.

1084
00:45:04,601 --> 00:45:07,736
[Knowing the orders and passing them on]

1085
00:45:08,605 --> 00:45:10,274
[Going beyond just cooking]
Honestly, giving a new guy

1086
00:45:10,274 --> 00:45:12,976
- complete control like that is not easy.
- Not easy at all.

1087
00:45:12,976 --> 00:45:17,214
[Kwon's solo stage,
can he run the appetizer station?]

1088
00:45:17,214 --> 00:45:22,886
[The dining room filling up with guests]

1089
00:45:22,886 --> 00:45:25,956
[The first order
signaling the start of service]

1090
00:45:25,956 --> 00:45:28,961
An antipasto platter for four
and one potato mushroom flan.

1091
00:45:28,961 --> 00:45:32,529
[Order for four in]
Two risottos, one potato pasta.

1092
00:45:32,529 --> 00:45:37,501
[Jumping right into action]

1093
00:45:37,501 --> 00:45:39,670
[Taking a deep breath before starting]

1094
00:45:39,670 --> 00:45:41,405
- I was a little nervous.
- He looks nervous.

1095
00:45:41,405 --> 00:45:42,406
- Look at his face.
- That must be a lot of pressure.

1096
00:45:42,406 --> 00:45:44,741
- It is.
- When Sung Jun gets tense,

1097
00:45:44,741 --> 00:45:46,910
his facial features really bunch up.

1098
00:45:46,910 --> 00:45:49,246
[Features bunching up]
He has that specific look when he gets nervous.

1099
00:45:49,246 --> 00:45:50,380
You see it? I know that look.

1100
00:45:50,380 --> 00:45:54,017
- He tenses his eyes a lot.
- He really flexes them like that.

1101
00:45:54,017 --> 00:45:56,953
[Alright, let's do this]

1102
00:45:56,953 --> 00:45:58,255
[Checking the whole order]
Are you done?

1103
00:45:58,255 --> 00:46:00,557
I was waiting for you.
You are doing it all tonight.

1104
00:46:00,557 --> 00:46:03,160
[Alright then]

1105
00:46:03,160 --> 00:46:04,594
[Channeling Senior An]

1106
00:46:04,594 --> 00:46:06,530
What about the potato pasta?

1107
00:46:06,530 --> 00:46:08,364
They are making it over there.

1108
00:46:09,333 --> 00:46:12,369
[Step 1. Checking the whole order]

1109
00:46:12,369 --> 00:46:15,172
[Setting up the soup bowls first]

1110
00:46:15,172 --> 00:46:17,174
[Half worried, half excited]

1111
00:46:17,174 --> 00:46:18,542
That is seriously so much pressure.

1112
00:46:18,542 --> 00:46:19,910
- Right.
- Hovering right next to him.

1113
00:46:19,910 --> 00:46:23,980
Having someone watch your every move
honestly makes you more tense than normal.

1114
00:46:23,980 --> 00:46:25,015
Exactly.

1115
00:46:25,015 --> 00:46:27,918
[Assistant An giving it a quick drizzle of oil]

1116
00:46:27,918 --> 00:46:30,287
Table 6.

1117
00:46:30,287 --> 00:46:32,823
[Step 2. Welcome food sent out]
- Table 6. - Table 6.

1118
00:46:32,823 --> 00:46:34,257
Take these two.

1119
00:46:34,257 --> 00:46:37,627
[Sending out the bean soup]

1120
00:46:38,628 --> 00:46:41,064
He is prepping the antipasto platter.

1121
00:46:42,099 --> 00:46:43,367
[Hmm]

1122
00:46:43,367 --> 00:46:45,435
[Sneaking over]

1123
00:46:45,435 --> 00:46:47,471
- He literally came right next to him.
- And he is just watching him.

1124
00:46:47,471 --> 00:46:49,439
- That is seriously so much pressure.
- He is right on top of him.

1125
00:46:49,439 --> 00:46:50,507
Tell me about it.

1126
00:46:50,507 --> 00:46:52,709
[Itching to help out with something]

1127
00:46:52,709 --> 00:46:55,379
[Fidgeting]
For now,

1128
00:46:55,379 --> 00:46:57,347
he still needs to check on me.

1129
00:46:57,347 --> 00:46:59,383
[While Kwon briefly steps away to the fryer]

1130
00:46:59,383 --> 00:47:02,853
[Assistant An mode instantly activated]

1131
00:47:02,853 --> 00:47:06,356
[The sauce drizzle that Kwon was doing]

1132
00:47:06,356 --> 00:47:09,693
[Assistant An handles it this time]

1133
00:47:09,693 --> 00:47:15,901
[Playing the loyal assistant today
instead of nagging]

1134
00:47:15,901 --> 00:47:18,034
[The chef in charge returns]

1135
00:47:18,034 --> 00:47:19,402
[Glancing over]

1136
00:47:21,471 --> 00:47:23,940
- You can take it from here.
- Okay.

1137
00:47:24,641 --> 00:47:27,043
[Taking the baton and getting back to work]

1138
00:47:27,043 --> 00:47:29,747
[Pausing]

1139
00:47:29,747 --> 00:47:31,114
Huh?

1140
00:47:31,114 --> 00:47:32,015
What's wrong?

1141
00:47:32,015 --> 00:47:34,551
[Is something wrong?]
What's wrong?

1142
00:47:34,551 --> 00:47:36,386
Antonio.

1143
00:47:36,386 --> 00:47:37,457
Antonio.

1144
00:47:37,457 --> 00:47:39,122
[Sorry, but...]

1145
00:47:39,723 --> 00:47:41,191
[Look at this]

1146
00:47:41,191 --> 00:47:42,192
[What's this doing here?]

1147
00:47:42,192 --> 00:47:43,894
Huh?

1148
00:47:43,894 --> 00:47:45,929
[What's the problem?]
[Assistant An's plating, original plating]

1149
00:47:45,929 --> 00:47:47,898
[Caught it instantly]
He got it wrong.

1150
00:47:47,898 --> 00:47:50,033
- No way.
- They got switched around.

1151
00:47:50,033 --> 00:47:51,701
Assistant An got it wrong.

1152
00:47:52,469 --> 00:47:54,604
I messed up.

1153
00:47:54,604 --> 00:47:57,641
[The student surpassing the master]

1154
00:47:57,641 --> 00:48:00,811
[And Senior An laughing awkwardly]

1155
00:48:00,811 --> 00:48:04,147
- Because they use different sauces.
- Yeah, the sauces are different.

1156
00:48:04,147 --> 00:48:05,549
[Matching them to the right sauces!]

1157
00:48:05,549 --> 00:48:08,385
[Kwon's got it covered!]

1158
00:48:08,385 --> 00:48:11,354
[Step 3. Antipasto platter done!]

1159
00:48:11,354 --> 00:48:12,389
Okay.

1160
00:48:12,389 --> 00:48:14,057
[Step 4. Calling the floor staff!]
- Start serving. - Okay.

1161
00:48:14,057 --> 00:48:17,060
[Floor staff arrives!]

1162
00:48:17,060 --> 00:48:20,163
[Step 5. Giving the table number!]
Table 8, please.

1163
00:48:20,163 --> 00:48:22,065
He's really good at this.

1164
00:48:22,065 --> 00:48:25,501
I guess it's my kitchen now.

1165
00:48:25,501 --> 00:48:26,981
[Antipasto platter is going out!]
[Getting used to his cocky side]

1166
00:48:26,981 --> 00:48:29,906
- Shouldn't have praised him.
- As expected.

1167
00:48:29,906 --> 00:48:32,375
[Appetizer station handled perfectly!]

1168
00:48:32,375 --> 00:48:35,278
Day two in and he's already...

1169
00:48:35,278 --> 00:48:37,781
[Holding it down alone on day two]
blending in like a regular.

1170
00:48:37,781 --> 00:48:41,218
- Is Sung Jun getting promoted today too?
- Seriously.

1171
00:48:41,218 --> 00:48:43,186
- He's killing it.
- Honestly, I'm the obvious pick.

1172
00:48:44,788 --> 00:48:50,193
[Every dish coming out right on time]

1173
00:48:50,193 --> 00:48:51,495
So.

1174
00:48:51,495 --> 00:48:53,830
Here's the antipasto platter.

1175
00:48:53,830 --> 00:48:56,566
[How about the taste?]

1176
00:48:56,566 --> 00:48:58,802
[Mmm!]

1177
00:48:58,802 --> 00:49:04,396
[Everyone happily diving in]

1178
00:49:05,942 --> 00:49:07,843
- This goes to table A, right?
- Yeah, table A.

1179
00:49:09,880 --> 00:49:12,649
Being efficient is everything
in a kitchen like this.

1180
00:49:12,649 --> 00:49:14,150
- Especially when it's this busy.
- The more you work it...

1181
00:49:14,150 --> 00:49:17,087
[Kitchen smarts on point]
You can't get nervous.

1182
00:49:17,087 --> 00:49:18,221
Just stay calm.

1183
00:49:18,221 --> 00:49:19,723
[Server waiting]

1184
00:49:19,723 --> 00:49:21,725
Table 5.

1185
00:49:21,725 --> 00:49:23,093
- Good, thanks.
- First courses.

1186
00:49:23,093 --> 00:49:24,194
[Smooth sailing all the way]

1187
00:49:24,194 --> 00:49:26,396
[Senior An, just kicking back]

1188
00:49:26,396 --> 00:49:30,166
[Tickets keep coming and he's keeping up]

1189
00:49:30,166 --> 00:49:34,070
[Senior An trusting Kwon and backing him up]

1190
00:49:34,070 --> 00:49:35,972
[I'm the master of this kitchen]
- What table, chef? - Five.

1191
00:49:35,972 --> 00:49:37,040
Okay.

1192
00:49:37,040 --> 00:49:38,975
Table A.

1193
00:49:40,277 --> 00:49:42,245
[Eyes locked in, crushing it on apps]
We're done.

1194
00:49:42,245 --> 00:49:43,947
Let's head home.

1195
00:49:43,947 --> 00:49:46,094
Take care, see you tomorrow.

1196
00:49:46,094 --> 00:49:47,784
- Okay.
- Good work today.

1197
00:49:47,784 --> 00:49:50,220
- Thank you.
- Good night.

1198
00:49:50,220 --> 00:49:53,757
What's "thank you" in Korean?

1199
00:49:53,757 --> 00:49:55,625
- In Korean?
- Yeah.

1200
00:49:55,625 --> 00:49:56,993
- Kam-sa-ham-ni-da.
- Kam-sa...

1201
00:49:56,993 --> 00:49:58,728
[All ears]
Kam-sa-ham-ni-da.

1202
00:49:58,728 --> 00:50:00,997
- Kam-sa-ham-ni-da?
- Kam-sa-ham-ni-da.

1203
00:50:00,997 --> 00:50:02,265
[Nice and clear]
Kam-sa-ham-ni-da.

1204
00:50:02,265 --> 00:50:03,934
Kam-sa-ham-ni-da. Grazie.

1205
00:50:03,934 --> 00:50:05,368
- Kam-sa-ham-ni-da.
- We were really clicking by then.

1206
00:50:05,368 --> 00:50:08,071
And "buonanotte?"
Isn't it "an-nyeong-ha-se-yo?"

1207
00:50:08,071 --> 00:50:10,574
Nope. "Buonanotte" is "jal-ja."

1208
00:50:10,574 --> 00:50:12,042
- Jal-ja.
- Jal-ja.

1209
00:50:12,042 --> 00:50:13,310
- Jal-ja.
- That's right.

1210
00:50:13,310 --> 00:50:15,645
- Jal-ja.
- Jal-ja.

1211
00:50:15,645 --> 00:50:18,539
Paolo's super into the Korean language.

1212
00:50:18,539 --> 00:50:21,751
- Jal-ja.
- Jal-ja.

1213
00:50:21,751 --> 00:50:23,787
[Wrapping up a great day two]

1214
00:50:23,787 --> 00:50:28,692
[Kwon, riding high]

1215
00:50:28,692 --> 00:50:31,227
We're on day three tomorrow.

1216
00:50:31,227 --> 00:50:33,330
[Hmm...]

1217
00:50:33,330 --> 00:50:35,298
[Setting a new record each time, visually]
The hair, though...

1218
00:50:35,298 --> 00:50:37,367
[He's cracking up at himself]
What in the world... is this hair?

1219
00:50:37,367 --> 00:50:39,069
- Did you just shower?
- I don't know.

1220
00:50:39,069 --> 00:50:40,270
- What is this hair situation?
- When was this filmed?

1221
00:50:40,270 --> 00:50:42,372
- He just rolled out of bed?
- It must be from the hat, right?

1222
00:50:42,372 --> 00:50:44,177
[Even his look's gone undercover]
I don't know.

1223
00:50:44,177 --> 00:50:46,412
Sung Jun, what are we going to do with you?

1224
00:50:47,010 --> 00:50:49,119
Aren't you supposed to look out for the talent?

1225
00:50:49,119 --> 00:50:50,347
Save the talent.

1226
00:50:50,347 --> 00:50:51,548
Why does my hair look like that?

1227
00:50:51,548 --> 00:50:55,218
We're on day three tomorrow.

1228
00:50:55,218 --> 00:50:57,821
You made a promise for day three, didn't you?

1229
00:50:57,821 --> 00:50:59,521
Yeah, I did.

1230
00:51:02,092 --> 00:51:04,361
[Refer to Episode 1]
Truth is, I don't think I'll need all five days.

1231
00:51:04,361 --> 00:51:05,662
[Really?]

1232
00:51:05,662 --> 00:51:07,697
[Until his dish makes the menu]
I think three days will do it.

1233
00:51:07,697 --> 00:51:10,100
What's with all the confidence?

1234
00:51:10,100 --> 00:51:12,968
[Bold claims]
Easy. Just do a good job, that's it.

1235
00:51:13,903 --> 00:51:17,173
[Speechless]
According to him, day three is the end of it.

1236
00:51:17,173 --> 00:51:21,611
[Tomorrow's day three, he's got to deliver...]

1237
00:51:21,611 --> 00:51:25,856
[Lost in thought now...]

1238
00:51:29,452 --> 00:51:34,290
[That night, Sung Jun couldn't sleep,
tossing all night]

1239
00:51:34,290 --> 00:51:35,825
[The morning of day three, the day he promised]

1240
00:51:35,825 --> 00:51:37,627
Today's your deadline, right?

1241
00:51:37,627 --> 00:51:39,595
Yeah, I said that.

1242
00:51:42,265 --> 00:51:44,246
[Wiping]

1243
00:51:45,068 --> 00:51:49,873
[Naples bustles into another day]

1244
00:51:49,873 --> 00:51:53,209
[7:50 AM, too early for work]

1245
00:51:53,209 --> 00:51:55,910
[Kwon, dragging a chair onto the terrace?]
What?

1246
00:51:57,080 --> 00:51:59,716
[Dead serious]
[What's going on?]

1247
00:51:59,716 --> 00:52:01,751
[Snap]

1248
00:52:01,751 --> 00:52:03,386
[Snap]
It's his uniform.

1249
00:52:03,386 --> 00:52:05,055
There's no washing machine,
so I washed it by hand.

1250
00:52:05,055 --> 00:52:06,756
Wait, will that even dry?

1251
00:52:06,756 --> 00:52:10,025
- In Italy, it dries in three hours.
- Oh, really?

1252
00:52:10,660 --> 00:52:14,264
[Day three morning,
drained from a sleepless night]

1253
00:52:14,264 --> 00:52:17,534
[Needs an energy boost]

1254
00:52:17,534 --> 00:52:19,450
[Pouring]

1255
00:52:20,937 --> 00:52:22,939
- What is that? Ramen?
- What's that?

1256
00:52:22,939 --> 00:52:24,641
[Mmm]

1257
00:52:24,641 --> 00:52:27,543
[The aroma hits before you even sip]
Just smelling it is relaxing.

1258
00:52:28,611 --> 00:52:29,946
[Trading coffee for sujeonggwa this morning]
Hey, isn't that the thing?

1259
00:52:29,946 --> 00:52:32,782
- What is that?
- I've had that before. I know what it is.

1260
00:52:32,782 --> 00:52:34,484
It has a mild aroma and tastes amazing.

1261
00:52:34,484 --> 00:52:36,653
[Suddenly in promo mode]
I feel like anyone can drink this...

1262
00:52:36,653 --> 00:52:39,723
I bet my Italian friends
would really love this.

1263
00:52:39,723 --> 00:52:41,958
[Where've you been, Undercover Kwon?]
They've got all kinds of teas there.

1264
00:52:41,958 --> 00:52:43,326
[His morning face, so cute]
Yeah, I've had it... It's really good.

1265
00:52:43,326 --> 00:52:46,129
- Right, that's really...
- I had it this morning too.

1266
00:52:46,129 --> 00:52:49,132
Even after two or three refills...

1267
00:52:49,132 --> 00:52:50,900
the aroma's still there. So good.

1268
00:52:50,900 --> 00:52:52,035
[Born for live streaming]

1269
00:52:52,035 --> 00:52:54,270
There's another way to make it even better.

1270
00:52:54,871 --> 00:52:57,974
[Sparkling water, syrup]
That was good.

1271
00:52:57,974 --> 00:53:00,210
[Sip]

1272
00:53:00,210 --> 00:53:01,444
[Got to try this right away]

1273
00:53:01,444 --> 00:53:03,980
[Sparkling water? What?]
The syrup makes it sweet

1274
00:53:03,980 --> 00:53:06,282
and brings out the smell. So much better.

1275
00:53:07,050 --> 00:53:08,351
[Time to head to work]

1276
00:53:08,351 --> 00:53:11,421
<i>There's an Italian saying, "Mai Paura."</i>

1277
00:53:11,421 --> 00:53:12,689
[Easy, kid...]
[He's tense]

1278
00:53:12,689 --> 00:53:15,024
[Resetting his mindset]
He's nervous.

1279
00:53:15,024 --> 00:53:18,828
[Off to work, mind made up]

1280
00:53:18,828 --> 00:53:19,829
I look dead serious.

1281
00:53:19,829 --> 00:53:22,747
- It's the last day now.
- Yeah, the last day for Sung Jun.

1282
00:53:22,747 --> 00:53:23,933
- Last day for me.
- Oh, right.

1283
00:53:23,933 --> 00:53:25,813
- It's day three, his final day.
- Day three...

1284
00:53:25,813 --> 00:53:27,270
- Today.
- The last day I promised.

1285
00:53:27,270 --> 00:53:30,974
What if he just says screw it
and takes over the stove?

1286
00:53:30,974 --> 00:53:32,142
Out of my way!

1287
00:53:32,142 --> 00:53:33,810
- Move it!
- Like, "Move."

1288
00:53:33,810 --> 00:53:37,580
[8:50 AM]

1289
00:53:37,580 --> 00:53:40,917
[Zipping in on the scooter]

1290
00:53:40,917 --> 00:53:46,456
[Paolo and the kitchen crew
clock in like any other day]

1291
00:53:46,456 --> 00:53:49,926
[Stride]

1292
00:53:49,926 --> 00:53:51,127
He looks dead serious.

1293
00:53:51,127 --> 00:53:53,763
[That bedhead screams Day 3 resolve]
That hair, seriously...

1294
00:53:53,763 --> 00:53:54,864
[A stretch]
Quite a look.

1295
00:53:54,864 --> 00:53:57,233
[A deep breath]
Doesn't feel like TV at all.

1296
00:53:57,233 --> 00:53:59,469
I really look like I'm heading to work.

1297
00:53:59,469 --> 00:54:03,576
[Sung Jun, it's go time]

1298
00:54:04,541 --> 00:54:06,743
[Up until now]

1299
00:54:06,743 --> 00:54:09,546
[The stove station was off-limits for him]

1300
00:54:09,546 --> 00:54:13,650
[Kwon's been on apps and desserts
for two days straight!]

1301
00:54:13,650 --> 00:54:17,120
[But now!]

1302
00:54:17,120 --> 00:54:18,888
[Finally on the fire]

1303
00:54:18,888 --> 00:54:23,927
He's actually cooking now, on the line himself.

1304
00:54:23,927 --> 00:54:25,361
[Onto the real cooking station at last]

1305
00:54:25,361 --> 00:54:28,765
I need to make that move.
Can't just stay on apps and desserts forever.

1306
00:54:28,765 --> 00:54:32,268
[So what's the plan?]

1307
00:54:32,268 --> 00:54:34,971
Usually, the rookie cooks...

1308
00:54:34,971 --> 00:54:38,107
The best time to show your skills
is during staff meal.

1309
00:54:38,107 --> 00:54:41,811
That's basically the only time
you can show off in front of the chef.

1310
00:54:41,811 --> 00:54:43,780
- I have to make the most of it.
- Right.

1311
00:54:43,780 --> 00:54:46,352
[Gulp]

1312
00:54:46,352 --> 00:54:50,250
[The only chance to prove what I can do]

1313
00:54:51,521 --> 00:54:56,559
I'm going to try to pitch
the staff meal idea this morning.

1314
00:54:57,861 --> 00:55:00,063
[Day 3 plan: Win them over with the staff meal]
You're doing the staff meal today, right?

1315
00:55:00,063 --> 00:55:05,368
This could really be an inspiration
for a lot of chefs out there.

1316
00:55:05,368 --> 00:55:07,770
[Will his big move work today?]

1317
00:55:07,770 --> 00:55:10,306
[First thing as always: changing into uniform]

1318
00:55:10,306 --> 00:55:11,374
- Hello.
- Hi.

1319
00:55:11,374 --> 00:55:13,476
Hey, Kwon.

1320
00:55:13,476 --> 00:55:14,759
[Walking with his two seniors]

1321
00:55:14,759 --> 00:55:16,579
Okay.

1322
00:55:18,014 --> 00:55:20,350
Today is day three.

1323
00:55:20,350 --> 00:55:22,118
- Gosh, this is almost wrapped.
- Yeah.

1324
00:55:22,118 --> 00:55:24,621
- Time really flew.
- Yeah.

1325
00:55:24,621 --> 00:55:25,855
- Time really flew by.
- Small talk.

1326
00:55:25,855 --> 00:55:28,358
You call that small talk? That's micro talk.

1327
00:55:28,358 --> 00:55:29,994
- Good morning.
- Small talk.

1328
00:55:29,994 --> 00:55:32,131
Good morning.

1329
00:55:32,131 --> 00:55:34,530
- Hey.
- Hey.

1330
00:55:34,530 --> 00:55:37,166
[The big Day 3 begins in the kitchen]

1331
00:55:37,166 --> 00:55:41,104
[Watching quietly]

1332
00:55:41,104 --> 00:55:42,805
[Today's to-do list:
Tart, meatballs, cheese bread]

1333
00:55:42,805 --> 00:55:46,208
[A pretty chill day]
Today's work... they've got it all written out.

1334
00:55:47,243 --> 00:55:48,278
[Pumping himself up]

1335
00:55:48,278 --> 00:55:50,446
[Mission: win them over with staff meal]

1336
00:55:52,181 --> 00:55:54,550
So...

1337
00:55:54,550 --> 00:55:56,786
- Alright, you ready? Let's get started.
- Yes.

1338
00:55:56,786 --> 00:55:59,889
- You need to go grab some stuff over there.
- Okay.

1339
00:55:59,889 --> 00:56:01,261
- Minced meat.
- Okay.

1340
00:56:01,261 --> 00:56:02,492
- Bread.
- Okay.

1341
00:56:02,492 --> 00:56:03,693
- Eggs.
- Why not tell me as we walk?

1342
00:56:03,693 --> 00:56:05,194
- Okay.
- Cheese.

1343
00:56:05,194 --> 00:56:06,963
So he wants you to just stand and listen first.

1344
00:56:06,963 --> 00:56:10,366
- Don't worry.
- Yes.

1345
00:56:10,366 --> 00:56:15,605
Italians really do stand
closer than Koreans, no joke.

1346
00:56:15,605 --> 00:56:17,774
[Right up close]
They come in way closer when they talk.

1347
00:56:17,774 --> 00:56:20,143
[Kwon Sung Jun, nine months in Naples]
Italians, when they greet each other...

1348
00:56:20,143 --> 00:56:22,245
- They do cheek kisses.
- Exactly.

1349
00:56:22,245 --> 00:56:24,213
Sung Jun, then why don't you do it to me?

1350
00:56:29,652 --> 00:56:31,888
Try that in Korea and you're going to the cops.

1351
00:56:31,888 --> 00:56:33,589
I'd rather not feel that beard, no offense.

1352
00:56:33,589 --> 00:56:36,225
- It doesn't grow on my cheek.
- Alright, I'll think about it.

1353
00:56:36,225 --> 00:56:37,560
Do it from now on, got it?

1354
00:56:37,560 --> 00:56:40,129
[This is Undercover Chef, not a rom-com FYI]

1355
00:56:40,129 --> 00:56:43,197
[Anyway, off they go side by side]

1356
00:56:43,933 --> 00:56:46,169
[Laura's there, prepping ingredients]

1357
00:56:46,169 --> 00:56:47,170
Isn't that the owner?

1358
00:56:47,170 --> 00:56:48,171
- The owner.
- Right.

1359
00:56:48,171 --> 00:56:51,273
- The owner is so hardworking.
- Right?

1360
00:56:52,342 --> 00:56:54,477
[Hesitating]

1361
00:56:54,477 --> 00:56:57,280
[Glancing]

1362
00:56:57,280 --> 00:56:59,716
[Hesitant]

1363
00:56:59,716 --> 00:57:00,783
Okay.

1364
00:57:00,783 --> 00:57:03,152
[Carefully making his way to Laura...]

1365
00:57:03,152 --> 00:57:05,421
[Hold on...]

1366
00:57:05,421 --> 00:57:07,991
[Looking for the right time
to pitch the staff meal]

1367
00:57:07,991 --> 00:57:11,027
He's got to step up and pitch it now.

1368
00:57:11,027 --> 00:57:12,061
Exactly.

1369
00:57:12,061 --> 00:57:13,963
[Hesitating]
- Kwon, take this. - Okay.

1370
00:57:13,963 --> 00:57:16,545
- Let's take it over there.
- Okay.

1371
00:57:16,545 --> 00:57:20,603
[Missed his shot]
- You can just set it up here. - Okay.

1372
00:57:20,603 --> 00:57:22,572
- You're going to pitch it to the boss?
- I have to talk to the owner.

1373
00:57:22,572 --> 00:57:23,873
The owner's the one to ask.

1374
00:57:23,873 --> 00:57:25,041
[Just can't seem
to pitch the staff meal idea...]

1375
00:57:25,041 --> 00:57:28,080
Kwon, careful with this one too, please.

1376
00:57:28,080 --> 00:57:29,045
Okay.

1377
00:57:29,045 --> 00:57:31,481
- Put it here.
- Okay.

1378
00:57:31,481 --> 00:57:32,949
[Laura disappears once more]

1379
00:57:32,949 --> 00:57:36,419
[Where are you going now?]

1380
00:57:36,419 --> 00:57:37,787
[The moment Laura moves]

1381
00:57:37,787 --> 00:57:40,456
[He's right behind her...]

1382
00:57:40,456 --> 00:57:42,775
That's really nerve-wracking though,
bringing something like that up.

1383
00:57:42,775 --> 00:57:44,321
Right. So nerve-wracking.

1384
00:57:44,321 --> 00:57:47,163
[Waiting for another opening
to pitch the staff meal...]

1385
00:57:47,163 --> 00:57:48,431
[Looking around]

1386
00:57:48,431 --> 00:57:49,866
Laura.

1387
00:57:49,866 --> 00:57:51,567
[Oh, it's you]
Laura.

1388
00:57:51,567 --> 00:57:53,669
- Kwon! Want some black coffee?
- Yes.

1389
00:57:53,669 --> 00:57:55,805
I'll bring it to you.

1390
00:57:55,805 --> 00:57:57,473
[Ugh]

1391
00:57:57,473 --> 00:58:00,410
[Second attempt
to bring up the staff meal, failed]

1392
00:58:00,410 --> 00:58:02,378
Imagine how nervous
he'd be right before asking.

1393
00:58:02,378 --> 00:58:04,013
- Right?
- Right?

1394
00:58:04,013 --> 00:58:05,882
Honestly, it wasn't that scary...

1395
00:58:05,882 --> 00:58:08,417
I figured she'd let me do it if I just asked.

1396
00:58:09,652 --> 00:58:10,953
Please take good care of him.

1397
00:58:10,953 --> 00:58:12,388
Alright.

1398
00:58:12,388 --> 00:58:14,557
He comes off great in the edit.

1399
00:58:14,557 --> 00:58:15,858
[At ease]
Even if I don't step in for him.

1400
00:58:15,858 --> 00:58:19,262
Honestly, I've become a fan of Chef Kwon.

1401
00:58:19,262 --> 00:58:20,696
- I knew it.
- He's got something about him.

1402
00:58:20,696 --> 00:58:22,432
For sure.

1403
00:58:22,432 --> 00:58:24,167
[Found a new type to crush on]
He's got his own thing going, you know.

1404
00:58:24,167 --> 00:58:26,269
I think I'm kind of getting drawn in.

1405
00:58:26,269 --> 00:58:29,505
Like, "What's he going to say next?"

1406
00:58:29,505 --> 00:58:31,207
[Pleased]

1407
00:58:31,207 --> 00:58:33,609
[Laura's right back with the coffee...]

1408
00:58:33,609 --> 00:58:36,211
- Kwon, I'll leave your black coffee here.
- Thank you.

1409
00:58:36,813 --> 00:58:38,660
[He really has to say it now...]
He still can't bring himself to say it.

1410
00:58:38,660 --> 00:58:39,882
I'm feeling out the moment.

1411
00:58:39,882 --> 00:58:41,017
I needed that coffee.

1412
00:58:41,017 --> 00:58:43,986
[Whoosh]

1413
00:58:43,986 --> 00:58:49,592
[Watching for the right moment
to mention the staff meal...]

1414
00:58:49,592 --> 00:58:51,961
I'm reading the room. I'm timing it.

1415
00:58:51,961 --> 00:58:53,629
See, you were nervous after all.

1416
00:58:53,629 --> 00:58:56,499
- He really is tense, though.
- Right?

1417
00:58:56,499 --> 00:58:58,334
Kwon, did you get good rest last night?

1418
00:58:58,334 --> 00:59:00,303
Yes, I rested well.

1419
00:59:00,303 --> 00:59:02,304
Glad to hear it.

1420
00:59:03,339 --> 00:59:07,710
[Knocks back the coffee fast]

1421
00:59:07,710 --> 00:59:09,112
Laura.

1422
00:59:09,112 --> 00:59:10,446
- Here it comes.
- Laura.

1423
00:59:10,446 --> 00:59:15,051
Would it be okay if I made lunch?

1424
00:59:15,051 --> 00:59:17,152
- For us?
- Yes.

1425
00:59:17,887 --> 00:59:20,189
You want to cook for us?

1426
00:59:20,189 --> 00:59:22,024
[Tense...]
[Would it be okay?]

1427
00:59:22,024 --> 00:59:23,959
Sure, go for it.

1428
00:59:24,760 --> 00:59:26,080
[The staff meal pitch worked]
Okay.

1429
00:59:26,080 --> 00:59:27,263
What...

1430
00:59:27,263 --> 00:59:29,966
- She said yes right away.
- Of course.

1431
00:59:29,966 --> 00:59:32,435
A staff member bringing that up like that...

1432
00:59:32,435 --> 00:59:34,003
- It's honestly pretty adorable.
- Adorable.

1433
00:59:34,003 --> 00:59:35,805
- Yeah, makes sense.
- I mean, I'm offering, so why not.

1434
00:59:35,805 --> 00:59:38,074
What are you thinking of making?

1435
00:59:38,074 --> 00:59:41,477
Something simple, with mozzarella, basil...

1436
00:59:41,477 --> 00:59:42,612
- I see.
- Perfect.

1437
00:59:42,612 --> 00:59:45,647
Tomato risotto, is that okay?

1438
00:59:46,516 --> 00:59:47,781
[Why tomato risotto, though?]
Oh, risotto.

1439
00:59:47,781 --> 00:59:50,453
- Risotto's the way to go.
- Why did you go with tomato risotto?

1440
00:59:50,453 --> 00:59:54,157
Making sure the staff meal
tastes good matters, of course.

1441
00:59:54,157 --> 00:59:56,492
But what matters more is
how well it reflects the region.

1442
00:59:56,492 --> 00:59:57,360
[Kwon's staff meal strategy 1]

1443
00:59:57,360 --> 01:00:00,963
It's about making good use
of what Naples produces.

1444
01:00:00,963 --> 01:00:04,300
[Kwon's staff meal strategy 2]
It's all about staying true to your roots.

1445
01:00:04,300 --> 01:00:06,769
When you think of Italian food,
what ingredients come to mind?

1446
01:00:06,769 --> 01:00:10,806
Tomatoes, mozzarella cheese.

1447
01:00:10,806 --> 01:00:12,375
Those are all from Naples.

1448
01:00:12,375 --> 01:00:13,442
Tomato and cheese.

1449
01:00:13,442 --> 01:00:15,367
Not just cheese, mozzarella specifically.

1450
01:00:15,367 --> 01:00:17,559
Is mozzarella from Naples?

1451
01:00:17,559 --> 01:00:19,031
Mozzarella is from Naples.

1452
01:00:19,031 --> 01:00:20,455
Oh, really?

1453
01:00:20,455 --> 01:00:23,635
[Mozzarella is a traditional cheese
from Campania, including Naples]

1454
01:00:23,635 --> 01:00:26,791
[And has been a local specialty
consumed in the region for centuries]

1455
01:00:26,791 --> 01:00:28,983
- Tomato risotto sounds good, right?
- Right.

1456
01:00:28,983 --> 01:00:30,855
Mozzarella, basil, simple.

1457
01:00:30,855 --> 01:00:32,631
- Yes.
- Good.

1458
01:00:32,631 --> 01:00:35,239
Since you seem to like risotto...

1459
01:00:35,239 --> 01:00:37,095
Why don't you make us some?

1460
01:00:37,095 --> 01:00:39,599
[Oh, yes! I'd love to.]
I'll do that.

1461
01:00:40,487 --> 01:00:43,767
- I'll watch how you cook it.
- Yes, sir.

1462
01:00:43,767 --> 01:00:46,471
[Senior Paolo is also looking forward to it]
I should make what I'm best at.

1463
01:00:46,471 --> 01:00:49,639
- This is where he finally shows his skills.
- That's right.

1464
01:00:49,639 --> 01:00:52,879
[Q. What did you think of Kwon's meal proposal?]
They're so cute.

1465
01:00:52,879 --> 01:00:54,807
I thought it was a great idea.

1466
01:00:54,807 --> 01:00:56,179
Because we can see Kwon cook

1467
01:00:56,179 --> 01:00:57,335
and see how he moves in the kitchen.

1468
01:00:57,335 --> 01:01:00,535
From a blank slate
to the process of completing a dish.

1469
01:01:00,535 --> 01:01:02,939
That's a very important part for us.

1470
01:01:02,939 --> 01:01:03,859
- Ah, I see.
- Ah, I see.

1471
01:01:03,859 --> 01:01:04,911
You go first.

1472
01:01:04,911 --> 01:01:09,519
Exactly. Plus, I think
it's a wonderful gesture.

1473
01:01:09,519 --> 01:01:13,679
Stepping up to handle the staff meal
shortly after joining the team...

1474
01:01:13,679 --> 01:01:14,967
[Empathy]
Really shortly after.

1475
01:01:14,967 --> 01:01:17,543
Handling the staff meal

1476
01:01:17,543 --> 01:01:18,583
[Seriously]
is a big responsibility.

1477
01:01:18,583 --> 01:01:20,119
A big one.

1478
01:01:20,119 --> 01:01:25,031
So it's quite surprising and very heartening.

1479
01:01:25,031 --> 01:01:27,009
Oh, they really see him in a positive light.

1480
01:01:27,009 --> 01:01:28,179
- Right.
- Exactly.

1481
01:01:28,179 --> 01:01:29,991
- So cute.
- I know.

1482
01:01:29,991 --> 01:01:33,219
[They're totally smitten with Sung Jun]
- He's bold, yet... - Yeah.

1483
01:01:33,219 --> 01:01:37,079
[Senior Paolo is excited about
the junior's meal prep]

1484
01:01:37,079 --> 01:01:39,591
[CANZONE D'AMORE (Song of Love)
by popular Italian rapper, Geolier]

1485
01:01:39,591 --> 01:01:42,109
[The kitchen is filled with music again today]

1486
01:01:43,223 --> 01:01:44,567
In Italy, we usually listen to music

1487
01:01:44,567 --> 01:01:45,751
[Glancing] [He's in a good mood]
when we're doing prep.

1488
01:01:45,751 --> 01:01:47,119
- You like it?
- Yes.

1489
01:01:47,119 --> 01:01:49,719
Do you like the song? It's in Italian,
so it's hard to understand, right?

1490
01:01:49,719 --> 01:01:51,095
It's okay.

1491
01:01:51,095 --> 01:01:52,551
Do I have to...

1492
01:01:52,551 --> 01:01:54,743
Shall we listen to some Korean songs later?

1493
01:01:54,743 --> 01:01:55,859
That'd be great.

1494
01:01:55,859 --> 01:01:58,799
What Korean songs do you like?

1495
01:02:04,039 --> 01:02:05,519
For sure I...

1496
01:02:05,519 --> 01:02:07,159
Look at that smug face.

1497
01:02:07,159 --> 01:02:09,623
- This is an Italian expression.
- An Italian face?

1498
01:02:09,623 --> 01:02:11,143
- An Italian expression.
- Ah... that look.

1499
01:02:11,143 --> 01:02:12,791
Why is that expression so annoying?

1500
01:02:12,791 --> 01:02:14,869
[Facial muscles that provoke the viewer]
Ugh, that's so annoying.

1501
01:02:14,869 --> 01:02:16,775
[An Italian face?]
Isn't that expression so annoying?

1502
01:02:16,775 --> 01:02:19,303
It's cute, it's cute.

1503
01:02:19,303 --> 01:02:23,079
I definitely like Italian songs more.

1504
01:02:23,079 --> 01:02:25,079
[Subtle appeal]
- Oh, really? - Yes.

1505
01:02:26,503 --> 01:02:28,039
[Italian songs over K-pop?]

1506
01:02:28,039 --> 01:02:29,935
I have to appeal like this.

1507
01:02:30,887 --> 01:02:34,335
- I know Kwon likes Italy.
- That's right.

1508
01:02:35,015 --> 01:02:36,759
[Strangely fascinated]

1509
01:02:36,759 --> 01:02:38,695
What do you like so much about Italy?

1510
01:02:38,695 --> 01:02:40,911
What do you like about it?

1511
01:02:42,503 --> 01:02:44,791
First, the food.

1512
01:02:44,791 --> 01:02:46,759
Second, the music.

1513
01:02:46,759 --> 01:02:49,263
Third...

1514
01:02:52,119 --> 01:02:53,671
And there's the history.

1515
01:02:53,671 --> 01:02:55,775
- The history.
- Yes.

1516
01:02:56,407 --> 01:02:58,535
Do you play music in the kitchen
while you work?

1517
01:02:58,535 --> 01:03:00,179
Yes, that's right.

1518
01:03:00,179 --> 01:03:01,351
- Why?
- Why?

1519
01:03:01,351 --> 01:03:02,419
Is that not allowed?

1520
01:03:02,419 --> 01:03:04,689
[Fact bombing]
You guys sit and rest in the kitchen.

1521
01:03:04,689 --> 01:03:06,247
- Rather than sitting and resting...
- Why the fuss about music?

1522
01:03:06,247 --> 01:03:07,399
You play music in the kitchen?

1523
01:03:07,399 --> 01:03:08,599
That's not allowed in our kitchen.

1524
01:03:08,599 --> 01:03:10,231
- Yeah, never in our kitchen.
- Oh, it's not allowed?

1525
01:03:10,231 --> 01:03:12,439
I always listen to music in my kitchen.

1526
01:03:12,439 --> 01:03:14,295
- If you play music in the kitchen...
- Why can't you play music?

1527
01:03:14,295 --> 01:03:16,439
Because of the noise...

1528
01:03:16,439 --> 01:03:18,949
- you won't hear what others say.
- Because you can't hear?

1529
01:03:18,949 --> 01:03:21,015
It's too loud, so you can't hear anyway.

1530
01:03:21,015 --> 01:03:24,039
So my staff never play it when I'm around.

1531
01:03:24,039 --> 01:03:27,063
I yell at them to turn it off
because it's distracting.

1532
01:03:27,063 --> 01:03:29,191
[Pro-music: It's needed to work happily]
But you need music to work happily.

1533
01:03:29,191 --> 01:03:31,047
[Anti-music: It's a distraction]
No, you need to focus.

1534
01:03:31,047 --> 01:03:32,743
Playing music itself...

1535
01:03:32,743 --> 01:03:34,391
It's like, "Are you here to play?"

1536
01:03:34,391 --> 01:03:36,071
"Are you here to play?"

1537
01:03:36,071 --> 01:03:38,039
[Summoning Chengdu again]
But we don't sit down.

1538
01:03:38,039 --> 01:03:41,207
I think sitting down is worse.

1539
01:03:41,207 --> 01:03:43,591
[Preparing for service while listening
to an Italian work song]

1540
01:03:43,591 --> 01:03:45,943
Almost done.

1541
01:03:45,943 --> 01:03:47,623
- Time to eat, time to eat.
- Right now?

1542
01:03:47,623 --> 01:03:49,479
Oh, he's cooking right away.

1543
01:03:49,479 --> 01:03:52,599
What do you need? Check the list.

1544
01:03:52,599 --> 01:03:55,463
[Determined]

1545
01:03:55,463 --> 01:03:56,709
I'm not nervous.

1546
01:03:56,709 --> 01:03:58,295
I'm the one making it,
so how could it not be good?

1547
01:03:58,295 --> 01:04:00,887
[Full of confidence]
As expected.

1548
01:04:00,887 --> 01:04:03,527
[Puffy]
My face is so swollen.

1549
01:04:03,527 --> 01:04:05,303
- It's getting more swollen.
- I know!

1550
01:04:05,303 --> 01:04:06,919
I thought it was Chef Jung Ho Young.

1551
01:04:06,919 --> 01:04:08,279
Exactly.

1552
01:04:08,279 --> 01:04:11,719
[Strangely similar...]
I really thought it was Chef Jung Ho Young.

1553
01:04:11,719 --> 01:04:14,135
[Not Jung Ho Young, but Kwon Sung Jun]
The most important thing is the texture.

1554
01:04:14,135 --> 01:04:16,599
But the reason that's important is...

1555
01:04:16,599 --> 01:04:18,871
It's not easy to get it right, but for me...

1556
01:04:18,871 --> 01:04:21,047
I'm very good at balancing flavors.

1557
01:04:21,047 --> 01:04:22,407
So it wasn't that difficult.

1558
01:04:22,407 --> 01:04:24,343
The production crew laughed at me a lot.

1559
01:04:24,343 --> 01:04:27,015
[Hmph!]

1560
01:04:27,015 --> 01:04:30,007
[Finally time to show off his skills!]

1561
01:04:30,007 --> 01:04:31,879
[Thinking hard]

1562
01:04:31,879 --> 01:04:34,391
Where would the garlic be?

1563
01:04:34,391 --> 01:04:36,743
The garlic is here.

1564
01:04:36,743 --> 01:04:39,111
And the basil is here if you need it.

1565
01:04:39,111 --> 01:04:41,439
The tomatoes are...

1566
01:04:41,439 --> 01:04:44,319
[As Kwon starts looking for ingredients]
Then this door.

1567
01:04:44,319 --> 01:04:47,779
[Senior Antonio's support]
Even letting him make the staff meal...

1568
01:04:47,779 --> 01:04:49,671
[Tomato sauce]

1569
01:04:49,671 --> 01:04:51,095
[Garlic, basil, provola cheese]

1570
01:04:51,095 --> 01:04:53,847
[Simple ingredients]
Keeping it simple.

1571
01:04:53,847 --> 01:04:57,119
[About to start cooking...]

1572
01:04:58,499 --> 01:04:59,749
Why?

1573
01:04:59,749 --> 01:05:02,903
[Another glance]

1574
01:05:02,903 --> 01:05:05,719
[Whenever the junior, Kwon, moves]

1575
01:05:06,419 --> 01:05:07,575
[Senior Antonio's eyes follow him]

1576
01:05:07,575 --> 01:05:10,039
[Why does he keep looking?]
Why is he doing that?

1577
01:05:10,039 --> 01:05:11,303
He's worried.

1578
01:05:11,303 --> 01:05:13,487
Since I suddenly said I'd cook...

1579
01:05:14,183 --> 01:05:15,927
[Senior Paolo is also interested]

1580
01:05:15,927 --> 01:05:18,119
[At the news of the junior's cooking]

1581
01:05:18,119 --> 01:05:20,163
[Expectations are rising]

1582
01:05:20,163 --> 01:05:21,316
Oh, I feel the pressure.

1583
01:05:21,316 --> 01:05:23,287
[Cooking begins under the seniors' gaze!]

1584
01:05:23,287 --> 01:05:24,679
[Slicing garlic into the pan]

1585
01:05:24,679 --> 01:05:25,927
How many servings is he making?

1586
01:05:25,927 --> 01:05:28,647
- About ten servings?
- Ten servings, but that garlic...

1587
01:05:30,231 --> 01:05:32,295
[Adding plenty of olive oil]

1588
01:05:32,295 --> 01:05:34,495
Are you going to use this tomato sauce?

1589
01:05:36,039 --> 01:05:37,716
Yes, I'll use that one.

1590
01:05:39,335 --> 01:05:41,447
[Tossing it onto the counter for Kwon to use]

1591
01:05:41,447 --> 01:05:43,623
[Senior Antonio hovers by Kwon as he cooks]
Senior Antonio is so meticulous.

1592
01:05:43,623 --> 01:05:45,751
He's extremely meticulous.

1593
01:05:45,751 --> 01:05:47,159
[Meanwhile, Kwon leaves the prep area]

1594
01:05:47,159 --> 01:05:49,975
[Moving to the stove]

1595
01:05:49,975 --> 01:05:53,031
[Finally]

1596
01:05:53,031 --> 01:05:55,431
[Starts cooking]

1597
01:05:55,431 --> 01:05:57,863
[Sizzle]

1598
01:05:57,863 --> 01:06:00,727
I'll pick the leaves and use the stems
just for the aroma.

1599
01:06:00,727 --> 01:06:02,919
Oh, that's how you do it.

1600
01:06:02,919 --> 01:06:06,295
[The seniors focus their attention once again
on Kwon's skillful movements]

1601
01:06:06,295 --> 01:06:08,535
[Focusing intensely despite their gaze]

1602
01:06:08,535 --> 01:06:11,575
[Infusing olive oil with garlic and basil]

1603
01:06:11,575 --> 01:06:15,207
[Controlling the heat is basic]

1604
01:06:15,207 --> 01:06:18,199
[Surprised]

1605
01:06:18,199 --> 01:06:22,049
Kwon, do you need stock for your risotto?

1606
01:06:22,049 --> 01:06:24,871
Um... I'll use vegetable stock.

1607
01:06:24,871 --> 01:06:27,223
[Preparing vegetable stock immediately]
Oh, vegetable stock?

1608
01:06:27,223 --> 01:06:29,943
[Checking the stock Senior Antonio gave him]
Oh, thank you.

1609
01:06:29,943 --> 01:06:31,429
[Laura peeks in]
Thank you.

1610
01:06:31,429 --> 01:06:32,647
Oh, the owner is here too.

1611
01:06:32,647 --> 01:06:34,759
Everyone is interested right now.

1612
01:06:34,759 --> 01:06:39,271
You're cooking for us. That's very good.

1613
01:06:39,271 --> 01:06:40,807
[Grinning and wiggling]

1614
01:06:40,807 --> 01:06:43,167
He's so cute.

1615
01:06:44,663 --> 01:06:47,249
[Let's see...]

1616
01:06:48,599 --> 01:06:50,951
I want to add white wine...

1617
01:06:50,951 --> 01:06:53,059
Oh? White wine?

1618
01:06:53,059 --> 01:06:55,551
[Senior Antonio asks back]
Kwon, white wine?

1619
01:06:57,447 --> 01:07:00,629
[He seems skeptical, but hands him a bottle]
- You need this. - Yes.

1620
01:07:00,629 --> 01:07:03,927
[The garlic and basil are well-infused]

1621
01:07:03,927 --> 01:07:05,495
[While the owner watches]

1622
01:07:05,495 --> 01:07:06,631
I have to take them out.

1623
01:07:06,631 --> 01:07:08,615
[Starting to scoop them all out]
That's how he does it.

1624
01:07:08,615 --> 01:07:11,671
[Glance]

1625
01:07:11,671 --> 01:07:13,911
[Glancing once more]
Seriously.

1626
01:07:13,911 --> 01:07:16,700
[Leaving only the infused olive oil]
He's watching so meticulously.

1627
01:07:17,687 --> 01:07:21,431
[Adding the rice...]

1628
01:07:21,431 --> 01:07:23,639
[Glance]

1629
01:07:23,639 --> 01:07:26,572
- Why? Why don't you trust me?
- Why is he frowning?

1630
01:07:27,303 --> 01:07:29,198
[Adding the white wine Antonio gave him]

1631
01:07:29,198 --> 01:07:31,943
But the way he adds wine like that...

1632
01:07:31,943 --> 01:07:33,351
[This is the classic method!]
This is just the classic way.

1633
01:07:33,351 --> 01:07:34,883
Really?

1634
01:07:40,855 --> 01:07:42,479
[Is there a problem... with white wine?]

1635
01:07:42,479 --> 01:07:44,839
But she's really watching everything.

1636
01:07:44,839 --> 01:07:46,007
Even while doing other things.

1637
01:07:46,007 --> 01:07:47,879
Because she doesn't trust me.

1638
01:07:47,879 --> 01:07:49,009
[Eyes fixed]

1639
01:07:49,009 --> 01:07:51,895
[Under the owner's gaze,
he adds the tomato sauce...]

1640
01:07:51,895 --> 01:07:54,479
[Staring once more]

1641
01:07:54,479 --> 01:07:55,621
[Scratch]

1642
01:07:55,621 --> 01:07:56,805
Why?

1643
01:07:56,805 --> 01:07:58,899
[What's wrong, Boss?]

1644
01:07:58,899 --> 01:08:02,099
- Usually, when we make risotto,
- Yes?

1645
01:08:02,099 --> 01:08:06,967
- we add water and set a 12-minute timer.
- Yes.

1646
01:08:06,967 --> 01:08:08,055
12 minutes.

1647
01:08:08,055 --> 01:08:11,109
- The time... A 12-minute timer.
- You've already wet it.

1648
01:08:11,109 --> 01:08:14,695
[Turning on the timer as Boss Laura said]
- Yes. - Set it.

1649
01:08:14,695 --> 01:08:16,899
Oh, he follows instructions well.

1650
01:08:16,899 --> 01:08:18,087
Well, the owner is telling him.

1651
01:08:18,087 --> 01:08:19,719
- That's right.
- Since the boss said it.

1652
01:08:19,719 --> 01:08:22,343
[He listens to the boss well]

1653
01:08:22,343 --> 01:08:24,023
[Hmm...]

1654
01:08:24,023 --> 01:08:28,799
I see he knows how to make risotto.

1655
01:08:28,799 --> 01:08:32,359
He fries the garlic and removes it
when the color is right.

1656
01:08:32,359 --> 01:08:34,903
[Satisfied]
- Not bad. - The right color.

1657
01:08:34,903 --> 01:08:37,479
But there's just one thing.

1658
01:08:37,479 --> 01:08:39,703
[You didn't press the timer]
Oh? One thing?

1659
01:08:39,703 --> 01:08:42,071
- Ah, he didn't press the timer.
- The timer was not set.

1660
01:08:42,071 --> 01:08:46,799
Hmm... I don't think Kwon has

1661
01:08:46,799 --> 01:08:50,979
the ability to manage the time
of these various dishes yet.

1662
01:08:50,979 --> 01:08:54,087
[Warm critique] [Well, it's his first time...]
- No. - Right, right.

1663
01:08:54,087 --> 01:08:55,399
- No, the risotto...
- You should've timed it!

1664
01:08:55,399 --> 01:08:56,983
- Does he have a biological clock?
- Isn't that the right way?

1665
01:08:56,983 --> 01:08:58,839
No, no, because this isn't service,

1666
01:08:58,839 --> 01:09:01,399
and I'm only doing this one thing,
so I didn't really...

1667
01:09:01,399 --> 01:09:04,903
- I'd time it during service.
- Kwon still struggles with time management.

1668
01:09:04,903 --> 01:09:07,575
As a fan of Chef Kwon,

1669
01:09:07,575 --> 01:09:08,679
[No timer is Kwon's confidence]
I think it's confidence.

1670
01:09:08,679 --> 01:09:10,791
- Right, confidence!
- You'll know when you taste it.

1671
01:09:10,791 --> 01:09:14,039
[Don't be discouraged]
- That's true. - It's not service time anyway.

1672
01:09:14,039 --> 01:09:16,983
[Stirring for a long time with confident hands]

1673
01:09:16,983 --> 01:09:18,839
[Tomato risotto starts to take shape]
Oh, it looks delicious.

1674
01:09:18,839 --> 01:09:20,727
Looks delicious.

1675
01:09:20,727 --> 01:09:23,943
[Tasting it immediately]

1676
01:09:23,943 --> 01:09:25,815
[Ooh]

1677
01:09:25,815 --> 01:09:27,859
[Time for the self-proclaimed
"Seasoning Master" to taste!]

1678
01:09:27,859 --> 01:09:28,919
How was the first bite?

1679
01:09:28,919 --> 01:09:30,529
Was it seasoned perfectly?
Or was it a bit bland?

1680
01:09:30,529 --> 01:09:34,364
[The taste shows on his face]
You can tell by his cocky expression.

1681
01:09:35,749 --> 01:09:37,639
Is it good?

1682
01:09:37,639 --> 01:09:39,436
Not bad.

1683
01:09:40,327 --> 01:09:43,463
[Oh? So it's good?]

1684
01:09:43,463 --> 01:09:45,927
[Sneaking over]

1685
01:09:45,927 --> 01:09:48,279
- Antonio, give it a taste.
- I'll taste it.

1686
01:09:48,279 --> 01:09:51,535
[Senior Chef Antonio steps up]

1687
01:09:54,913 --> 01:09:56,591
I'm curious what he'll say.

1688
01:09:56,591 --> 01:09:59,767
[What will the review be?]

1689
01:09:59,767 --> 01:10:01,539
[One bite... two bites... tasting it...]

1690
01:10:01,539 --> 01:10:04,019
[Curious]

1691
01:10:04,019 --> 01:10:06,530
[The boss is curious too]
How is it?

1692
01:10:07,687 --> 01:10:09,783
- It's good.
- Is it good?

1693
01:10:09,783 --> 01:10:11,271
- It's good.
- Is it good?

1694
01:10:11,271 --> 01:10:13,447
[As expected?] [Proud of the praise]
He says it's good.

1695
01:10:13,447 --> 01:10:14,759
[The boss steps in after hearing the news]

1696
01:10:14,759 --> 01:10:16,679
I should try it too.

1697
01:10:16,679 --> 01:10:17,909
They're all so suspicious.

1698
01:10:17,909 --> 01:10:20,503
Then I should try it too.

1699
01:10:20,503 --> 01:10:22,199
[Is this a famous restaurant?]
Shall I?

1700
01:10:22,199 --> 01:10:24,129
An inspection, and it's not even finished yet.

1701
01:10:24,129 --> 01:10:27,398
[It's like Kwon is taking an exam]
- A test. - Yes, a test.

1702
01:10:28,929 --> 01:10:31,409
[Takes a bite with a smile]

1703
01:10:31,409 --> 01:10:33,527
I wonder how they'll react. I'm so curious.

1704
01:10:33,527 --> 01:10:37,249
[Senior Chef Pa also takes a careful bite]

1705
01:10:37,249 --> 01:10:39,079
[How is it?]

1706
01:10:39,079 --> 01:10:40,279
It tastes good and it's cooked well.

1707
01:10:40,279 --> 01:10:41,509
[Satisfied]
- It's not overcooked. - Okay.

1708
01:10:41,509 --> 01:10:43,149
A compliment.

1709
01:10:43,879 --> 01:10:45,319
I think it needs a bit more salt.

1710
01:10:45,319 --> 01:10:49,169
Even considering the cheese,
it needs more salt, right?

1711
01:10:49,169 --> 01:10:51,223
- We'll have to see.
- Let's see.

1712
01:10:51,223 --> 01:10:54,649
[The staff's evaluation that Kwon missed]
Add the cheese and try it.

1713
01:10:55,999 --> 01:10:57,759
[Whispering]
- Let's add more salt. - Salt?

1714
01:10:57,759 --> 01:10:59,679
[Senior Chef An tells him right away]
Oh, from the side...

1715
01:10:59,679 --> 01:11:01,279
[Puzzled]
He's quietly giving him a tip.

1716
01:11:01,279 --> 01:11:03,703
They definitely eat quite salty.

1717
01:11:03,703 --> 01:11:05,913
- Should I add more sauce?
- Okay.

1718
01:11:05,913 --> 01:11:07,704
- There's too little tomato.
- Okay.

1719
01:11:07,704 --> 01:11:09,799
[Adding more sauce to adjust the seasoning]

1720
01:11:09,799 --> 01:11:11,939
[Kwon's risotto gets a richer color]
Now, let's do the mantecare.

1721
01:11:11,939 --> 01:11:14,538
- Okay.
- Let's move it away from the fire.

1722
01:11:14,538 --> 01:11:16,504
- On the countertop.
- Yes.

1723
01:11:16,504 --> 01:11:18,959
[Finishing the risotto with Senior Chef An]

1724
01:11:18,959 --> 01:11:20,549
I should add the cheese, right?

1725
01:11:20,549 --> 01:11:23,069
- Tell me when to stop!
- Okay.

1726
01:11:25,063 --> 01:11:26,449
A little more!

1727
01:11:26,449 --> 01:11:30,159
- Let's taste it after the cheese.
- Okay...

1728
01:11:30,159 --> 01:11:31,249
[Kwon shows off his mantecare skills]

1729
01:11:31,249 --> 01:11:32,769
Is this scene coming up now? Now?

1730
01:11:32,769 --> 01:11:35,139
[Glance]
Mantecare.

1731
01:11:35,139 --> 01:11:37,607
[Heave-ho...]

1732
01:11:37,607 --> 01:11:40,039
[Working hard]

1733
01:11:40,039 --> 01:11:42,229
[Napoli Matfia used to do
such cool mantecare...]

1734
01:11:42,229 --> 01:11:43,859
He's cute.

1735
01:11:43,859 --> 01:11:47,879
[But here, he's doing it in a corner...]

1736
01:11:47,879 --> 01:11:49,319
[The kitchen staff isn't interested...]

1737
01:11:49,319 --> 01:11:50,439
No one is watching.

1738
01:11:50,439 --> 01:11:52,319
Well, this is a given. In Italy,

1739
01:11:52,319 --> 01:11:53,429
doing mantecare

1740
01:11:53,429 --> 01:11:55,719
[Suddenly humble...]
is only considered special in Korea.

1741
01:11:55,719 --> 01:11:57,699
[Sweating while doing mantecare alone]

1742
01:11:57,699 --> 01:11:59,599
- Is there more left?
- It's all done.

1743
01:11:59,599 --> 01:12:01,239
- Is it good?
- Yes.

1744
01:12:01,239 --> 01:12:02,399
[Confident]

1745
01:12:02,399 --> 01:12:03,939
Let's plate it now.

1746
01:12:03,939 --> 01:12:05,409
No.

1747
01:12:06,119 --> 01:12:08,519
[While Kwon goes to get a ladle]
- It's there. - Okay.

1748
01:12:10,642 --> 01:12:11,779
[Senior Chef An tastes it one more time...]

1749
01:12:11,779 --> 01:12:14,056
Is he secretly adding something?

1750
01:12:16,199 --> 01:12:19,649
[How is the seasoning, Senior Chef An?]
How is the seasoning?

1751
01:12:19,649 --> 01:12:21,279
- Let's add one more pinch of salt.
- Okay.

1752
01:12:21,279 --> 01:12:23,079
Wow, they really like it salty.

1753
01:12:23,079 --> 01:12:24,999
They eat much saltier than I thought.

1754
01:12:24,999 --> 01:12:29,249
[Senior Chef An's salt seasoning and
Sung Jun's mantecare complete the risotto]

1755
01:12:29,249 --> 01:12:33,559
[The appetizer ends up as a collaboration...]

1756
01:12:33,559 --> 01:12:36,369
In a kitchen, you don't usually
do everything from start to finish alone.

1757
01:12:36,369 --> 01:12:38,529
[Quickly changing his stance]
There's someone to help with the prep,

1758
01:12:38,529 --> 01:12:41,969
[Embarrassing] [This is how a kitchen works]
and someone to help add the ingredients.

1759
01:12:41,969 --> 01:12:43,199
Right.

1760
01:12:43,199 --> 01:12:44,479
This is his charm.

1761
01:12:44,479 --> 01:12:48,159
Changing his stance quickly,
and admitting things quickly.

1762
01:12:48,159 --> 01:12:49,729
[You're charming, Chef Kwon]
That's not easy to do.

1763
01:12:49,729 --> 01:12:51,819
I admit it immediately.

1764
01:12:52,819 --> 01:12:57,779
[Plating Kwon's first staff meal
that they somehow made together]

1765
01:12:57,779 --> 01:13:02,979
[One by one, they fill the table]

1766
01:13:02,979 --> 01:13:04,719
[Kwon's first staff meal, finished after
many hurdles feat. Senior Chefs]

1767
01:13:04,719 --> 01:13:06,519
It looks delicious.

1768
01:13:06,519 --> 01:13:08,259
- Seriously.
- It's simple.

1769
01:13:08,259 --> 01:13:10,529
[Laura]
Kwon! Let's go eat.

1770
01:13:10,529 --> 01:13:14,159
[Heading over to have the meal...]

1771
01:13:14,159 --> 01:13:15,349
I made this.

1772
01:13:15,349 --> 01:13:17,969
- You did this?
- Yes.

1773
01:13:17,969 --> 01:13:19,299
I wonder if she had high expectations.

1774
01:13:19,299 --> 01:13:21,559
I'm curious about that.

1775
01:13:21,559 --> 01:13:23,109
[To those who sat down first]
Enjoy your meal.

1776
01:13:23,109 --> 01:13:25,039
Enjoy your meal.

1777
01:13:25,799 --> 01:13:29,169
[Extremely nervous]

1778
01:13:29,169 --> 01:13:31,109
[Will it live up to the 3-day promise?]
[Who will take the first bite?]

1779
01:13:31,109 --> 01:13:33,699
[The boss goes first]

1780
01:13:33,699 --> 01:13:37,439
[Laura takes a big bite...]

1781
01:13:37,439 --> 01:13:40,367
[How does it taste?]

1782
01:13:41,169 --> 01:13:42,289
It's good.

1783
01:13:42,289 --> 01:13:43,599
It's delicious.

1784
01:13:43,599 --> 01:13:44,759
- It's good.
- It looks delicious.

1785
01:13:44,759 --> 01:13:45,909
[The boss is satisfied]

1786
01:13:45,909 --> 01:13:50,689
Tomato, provola cheese, and basil.

1787
01:13:50,689 --> 01:13:52,659
When choosing ingredients,

1788
01:13:52,659 --> 01:13:54,309
he used ingredients from our region, Campania.

1789
01:13:54,309 --> 01:13:55,619
Neapolitan ingredients.

1790
01:13:55,619 --> 01:13:57,679
She values things like that.

1791
01:13:57,679 --> 01:13:59,029
It's the most important thing.

1792
01:13:59,029 --> 01:14:01,399
I think Kwon showed us respect

1793
01:14:01,399 --> 01:14:07,671
by serving us this risotto.

1794
01:14:07,671 --> 01:14:10,999
[Local ingredients pass]
I like his idea, and it's delicious.

1795
01:14:10,999 --> 01:14:12,599
- She knows exactly.
- As expected.

1796
01:14:12,599 --> 01:14:15,649
[That's our boss]
- She caught the intention. - Right away.

1797
01:14:15,649 --> 01:14:17,729
[I agree!]
It tasted like authentic Naples.

1798
01:14:17,729 --> 01:14:19,799
[Authenticity also passes]
It's similar, I ate it.

1799
01:14:19,799 --> 01:14:23,249
- I would've made it the same way.
- Recognition from the boss.

1800
01:14:23,249 --> 01:14:25,329
[But...]

1801
01:14:25,329 --> 01:14:27,479
Huh? Wait a second.

1802
01:14:28,849 --> 01:14:35,379
The composition is too simple
for it to be on the menu...

1803
01:14:35,379 --> 01:14:40,289
For example, if you added
some special ingredients...

1804
01:14:40,289 --> 01:14:43,889
Or something people would like...

1805
01:14:43,889 --> 01:14:48,529
Maybe if there was a contrasting texture,
like something crispy.

1806
01:14:48,529 --> 01:14:52,469
Like how our restaurant's risotto has
fried friarielli...

1807
01:14:52,469 --> 01:14:55,589
or salsiccia on top.

1808
01:14:55,589 --> 01:14:56,959
[Fried Friarielli] [Salsiccia]
[Risotto with both crispy and chewy textures]

1809
01:14:56,959 --> 01:14:58,479
That's right. The chef is actually...

1810
01:14:58,479 --> 01:15:01,269
- quite progressive.
- You're right.

1811
01:15:01,269 --> 01:15:06,679
[Laura felt the lack of textures was a shame]
It should be fitting in a restaurant menu.

1812
01:15:06,679 --> 01:15:08,929
I guess she expected
something a bit more special.

1813
01:15:08,929 --> 01:15:10,199
- She had high expectations.
- But it was just so...

1814
01:15:10,199 --> 01:15:12,869
- Basic.
- He went too traditional.

1815
01:15:12,869 --> 01:15:15,639
But in a way, showing that is meaningful.

1816
01:15:15,639 --> 01:15:17,059
- Right.
- Showing that he knows the basics.

1817
01:15:17,059 --> 01:15:18,869
That's true.

1818
01:15:20,209 --> 01:15:21,509
[Now only the two seniors' reviews remain]

1819
01:15:21,509 --> 01:15:24,567
[Senior Paolo joins the meal]

1820
01:15:24,567 --> 01:15:27,639
[Senior Antonio joins too]
[Finally, both seniors are seated]

1821
01:15:28,259 --> 01:15:30,689
Antonio doesn't usually eat lunch.

1822
01:15:30,689 --> 01:15:32,479
Antonio doesn't usually eat lunch.

1823
01:15:32,479 --> 01:15:33,559
That's right. I don't eat lunch.

1824
01:15:33,559 --> 01:15:35,109
He's eating because Kwon made it.

1825
01:15:35,109 --> 01:15:36,529
Oh, really?

1826
01:15:36,529 --> 01:15:39,699
[Kwon feels a bit more pressure]

1827
01:15:39,699 --> 01:15:43,089
[Senior Antonio watched him the whole time]
Is it later?

1828
01:15:43,089 --> 01:15:46,949
[Senior Paolo, No. 2 in charge of mains]

1829
01:15:46,949 --> 01:15:50,679
[The first staff meal by the junior, Kwon]

1830
01:15:50,679 --> 01:15:53,959
[Will he capture the seniors' taste buds?]

1831
01:15:55,189 --> 01:15:57,089
Chef Kwon's 3-day promise...

1832
01:15:57,089 --> 01:15:58,479
[Embarrassed]
It's a bit different,

1833
01:15:58,479 --> 01:16:01,095
but he hasn't properly started yet.

1834
01:16:01,095 --> 01:16:02,639
[Crying]

1835
01:16:02,639 --> 01:16:04,839
But we don't know yet!

1836
01:16:04,839 --> 01:16:06,119
The second person to promote...

1837
01:16:06,119 --> 01:16:07,809
We never said only one person
would be promoted.

1838
01:16:07,809 --> 01:16:09,399
- We didn't.
- Right. I might be the only one.

1839
01:16:09,399 --> 01:16:11,109
[But three days is too short!]
It's too short. It's impossible.

1840
01:16:11,109 --> 01:16:12,629
[Is it a smoke screen?]
It's too short, right?

1841
01:16:12,629 --> 01:16:14,229
- It's too short.
- Three days is too short.

1842
01:16:14,229 --> 01:16:16,609
[The last candidate's excuse]
- It's too short. - It is.

1843
01:16:16,609 --> 01:16:19,729
Last week, Chef Jung Ji Sun...

1844
01:16:19,729 --> 01:16:21,719
was right on the verge
of a Wok station promotion.

1845
01:16:21,719 --> 01:16:23,459
She's waiting for it.

1846
01:16:23,459 --> 01:16:25,199
- Second...
- But before you watch this,

1847
01:16:25,199 --> 01:16:26,979
you need to see
what my direct supervisor is like.

1848
01:16:26,979 --> 01:16:28,129
- Why?
- Oh, your direct supervisor?

1849
01:16:28,129 --> 01:16:30,369
- There's a specific supervisor, right?
- Yes.

1850
01:16:30,369 --> 01:16:31,719
[Undercover Sunny]
You'll see, I don't have a supervisor.

1851
01:16:31,719 --> 01:16:32,789
- Really?
- Yes.

1852
01:16:32,789 --> 01:16:34,819
[Suddenly, a supervisor?]

1853
01:16:34,819 --> 01:16:36,799
[Very beginning of today's recording]
Right now, for the viewers,

1854
01:16:36,799 --> 01:16:39,189
- the senior chefs are very popular.
- That's right.

1855
01:16:39,189 --> 01:16:40,949
- Really?
- Right now,

1856
01:16:40,949 --> 01:16:42,099
[Our MZ senior, Xu Jian Kai]
- No... - our Xu Jian Kai.

1857
01:16:42,099 --> 01:16:43,751
- He's cute.
- As you'll see,

1858
01:16:43,751 --> 01:16:45,459
is Xu Jian Kai my senior?

1859
01:16:45,459 --> 01:16:47,079
- Yes.
- Why?

1860
01:16:47,079 --> 01:16:48,929
- No...
- Isn't he your senior?

1861
01:16:48,929 --> 01:16:50,209
Isn't the head of the Prep station my senior?

1862
01:16:50,209 --> 01:16:52,119
Did you think he was your junior?

1863
01:16:52,119 --> 01:16:53,669
[Maybe a cute 22-year-old colleague?]
- No, then... - A colleague.

1864
01:16:53,669 --> 01:16:54,855
A colleague?

1865
01:16:54,855 --> 01:16:57,111
Now that I see, she's worse than Sung Jun.

1866
01:16:57,111 --> 01:16:59,489
I didn't learn anything from him.

1867
01:16:59,489 --> 01:17:02,449
- This is...
- Unacceptable.

1868
01:17:02,449 --> 01:17:06,567
First, let's see if he's really
her supervisor or not.

1869
01:17:06,567 --> 01:17:10,119
[Most importantly]
Let's see if a second promotion happens.

1870
01:17:10,119 --> 01:17:12,599
Let's watch Chef Jung Ji Sun's episode.

1871
01:17:13,299 --> 01:17:17,299
[Undercover junior Day 2, Chengdu, China]
[Sunny, not Jung Ji Sun]

1872
01:17:17,299 --> 01:17:22,279
[Last time, the male boss said]
I think it'd be good to practice more tonight.

1873
01:17:22,279 --> 01:17:24,239
So that during tomorrow's service,

1874
01:17:24,239 --> 01:17:26,529
you can work at the Wok station.

1875
01:17:26,529 --> 01:17:29,297
You can work at the Wok station.

1876
01:17:29,939 --> 01:17:32,739
[Sunny has a chance to move to the Wok station]
Well, first, the opportunity is there.

1877
01:17:32,739 --> 01:17:35,259
- Wow...
- The opportunity is finally...

1878
01:17:36,199 --> 01:17:37,569
[But...]

1879
01:17:37,569 --> 01:17:38,951
- Isn't it this guy?
- That's right.

1880
01:17:38,951 --> 01:17:40,295
- Right?
- It's Xu Jian Kai. Yes.

1881
01:17:40,295 --> 01:17:43,429
He looks a bit disappointed.

1882
01:17:43,429 --> 01:17:44,529
[Glance]

1883
01:17:44,529 --> 01:17:46,551
[With Sunny's possible move to the Wok station]

1884
01:17:46,551 --> 01:17:49,299
[The Prep station atmosphere gets awkward]

1885
01:17:49,299 --> 01:17:52,519
[But she must focus on work
without time to worry!]

1886
01:17:52,519 --> 01:17:54,309
[Now that the path to the Wok station is clear]

1887
01:17:54,309 --> 01:17:55,809
She's doing everything she learned.

1888
01:17:55,809 --> 01:17:58,439
[A moment more important than ever]

1889
01:17:58,439 --> 01:18:02,299
[She must do well to move to the next level]
She's got a good head for work.

1890
01:18:03,779 --> 01:18:06,869
[The corn Sunny prepared is almost fried]

1891
01:18:06,869 --> 01:18:09,409
[But]

1892
01:18:09,409 --> 01:18:11,329
You can't do that.

1893
01:18:11,329 --> 01:18:12,719
Why?

1894
01:18:12,719 --> 01:18:14,279
You have to coat it with powder again.

1895
01:18:14,279 --> 01:18:15,879
Oh, wait. The powder.

1896
01:18:15,879 --> 01:18:17,999
- Wait.
- Sunny was the one who coated it.

1897
01:18:17,999 --> 01:18:19,669
You have to coat it with powder again.

1898
01:18:19,669 --> 01:18:21,509
[Emergency]
- Emergency. - Redo it.

1899
01:18:21,509 --> 01:18:23,519
Those corn fritters can't be served.

1900
01:18:23,519 --> 01:18:26,479
- Redo... Redo them?
- Redo them.

1901
01:18:26,479 --> 01:18:28,639
Oops! I realized it too.

1902
01:18:29,749 --> 01:18:33,359
[Sunny makes a huge mistake
right before her promotion]

1903
01:18:33,359 --> 01:18:34,849
[No.2 Liu Dai Yu]
Is there a problem?

1904
01:18:34,849 --> 01:18:37,539
The powder on Sunny's corn fritters
is insufficient.

1905
01:18:37,539 --> 01:18:39,999
[A stern reprimand!]
Teach Sunny again!

1906
01:18:41,719 --> 01:18:45,839
[Flustered, Sunny follows the No. 3 senior
to fix the situation]

1907
01:18:45,839 --> 01:18:50,380
[Starting over from the beginning]

1908
01:18:51,329 --> 01:18:54,149
[A mistake at the worst possible time]

1909
01:18:54,149 --> 01:18:57,213
[Promotion to the Wok station is near...]
She's moving to the station tomorrow.

1910
01:18:58,689 --> 01:19:02,019
[Seeing if it's truly unusable]
Grandma, try this.

1911
01:19:02,019 --> 01:19:03,269
The powder is all gone.

1912
01:19:03,269 --> 01:19:06,149
[Absolutely not]
It won't look good for the customers.

1913
01:19:06,149 --> 01:19:09,189
[Sunny realizes the reason later]
Since the corn has moisture...

1914
01:19:09,189 --> 01:19:12,259
When you coat it with custard powder,

1915
01:19:12,259 --> 01:19:14,309
it gets absorbed.

1916
01:19:14,309 --> 01:19:16,269
It melts away.

1917
01:19:17,329 --> 01:19:19,859
[The corn must be coated thoroughly]

1918
01:19:19,859 --> 01:19:21,559
Every single kernel must be coated.

1919
01:19:21,559 --> 01:19:24,369
[The coating should remain after frying]
But since some time had passed...

1920
01:19:24,369 --> 01:19:25,879
- It melted.
- Too much time passed.

1921
01:19:25,879 --> 01:19:29,079
- You did it too early.
- Yes.

1922
01:19:29,079 --> 01:19:33,439
She prepared it too early
because she was so eager.

1923
01:19:34,639 --> 01:19:40,638
[Was she too ambitious?]
[She made a mistake she rarely makes]

1924
01:19:40,638 --> 01:19:43,199
The male boss must have cooked a lot.

1925
01:19:43,199 --> 01:19:45,919
He took one look and rejected it immediately.

1926
01:19:45,919 --> 01:19:49,178
[She was clearly flustered]
So I was a little worried.

1927
01:19:52,259 --> 01:19:54,389
- You must have been very surprised.
- I bet.

1928
01:19:54,389 --> 01:19:55,939
[She wasn't surprised?]
Actually... I wasn't really...

1929
01:19:55,939 --> 01:19:57,539
[Wait, what?]
I wasn't that surprised.

1930
01:19:57,539 --> 01:19:59,089
- Wait a minute.
- A kitchen junior...

1931
01:19:59,089 --> 01:20:01,629
A kitchen junior can make a mistake once.

1932
01:20:02,999 --> 01:20:04,949
- Wait a minute.
- She's generous to herself,

1933
01:20:04,949 --> 01:20:07,119
- She's different from me.
- but harsh on others.

1934
01:20:07,119 --> 01:20:08,549
You're so different from me.

1935
01:20:08,549 --> 01:20:12,549
[Hee Tae, the habitual offender?]
Then how many times do you make that mistake?

1936
01:20:12,549 --> 01:20:14,519
- I only do it once.
- Oh, really?

1937
01:20:14,519 --> 01:20:16,519
[I... did it three times]
- Of course. - You only do it once, right?

1938
01:20:16,519 --> 01:20:18,929
- I only do it once.
- Really? Let's see.

1939
01:20:18,929 --> 01:20:22,769
[Surely she won't make the same mistake again?]
No way she'd do it three times.

1940
01:20:22,769 --> 01:20:24,949
[Taking the newly prepared corn]

1941
01:20:24,949 --> 01:20:28,749
[Handing it to the Wok station head]
You need to use plenty of oil this time.

1942
01:20:30,579 --> 01:20:33,309
[Will it go well this time?]

1943
01:20:34,129 --> 01:20:40,129
[Anxious]

1944
01:20:41,409 --> 01:20:44,939
[Restarting the Duck Egg Corn Fritters]
- Again, again. - Again.

1945
01:20:48,369 --> 01:20:52,169
[While it's being cooked]

1946
01:20:52,819 --> 01:20:56,869
[Sunny is nervous]

1947
01:20:56,869 --> 01:21:00,139
The chef set the oil temperature wrong earlier.

1948
01:21:00,999 --> 01:21:02,819
[Xu Jian Kai sides with Sunny in case she gets blamed]
Oh, Xu Jian Kai!

1949
01:21:02,819 --> 01:21:04,679
- Xu Jian Kai!
- Her supervisor is taking her side.

1950
01:21:04,679 --> 01:21:06,789
- Look at that!
- He's taking her side.

1951
01:21:06,789 --> 01:21:08,239
[Excited]
Look at that!

1952
01:21:08,239 --> 01:21:11,109
[About the kind senior chef]
He's like a gentle lamb...

1953
01:21:11,109 --> 01:21:13,039
- He's such a nice person.
- No...

1954
01:21:13,039 --> 01:21:14,179
He's saying it's not the senior's fault.

1955
01:21:14,179 --> 01:21:15,619
No!

1956
01:21:15,619 --> 01:21:19,239
My goodness, Xu Jian Kai is taking her side.

1957
01:21:19,239 --> 01:21:22,189
[To the kind senior...]
Jung Ji Sun is being mean.

1958
01:21:27,519 --> 01:21:32,679
[Meanwhile, the second attempt
at the Duck Egg Corn Fritters is done]

1959
01:21:34,339 --> 01:21:36,509
[Glance]

1960
01:21:37,619 --> 01:21:41,799
[Will it be right this time?]

1961
01:21:41,799 --> 01:21:47,089
[The owner arrives at the Wok station
just in time]

1962
01:21:47,089 --> 01:21:52,549
[Nervous]

1963
01:21:52,549 --> 01:21:55,119
[No.3 Xu Jian Kai also notices]

1964
01:21:55,119 --> 01:21:57,179
Yes, it's done!

1965
01:21:57,889 --> 01:22:00,209
[Success this time!]
Yes, it's done!

1966
01:22:02,899 --> 01:22:06,809
[Served as soon as the owner approves]
- It should be like this. - It's different.

1967
01:22:07,479 --> 01:22:09,119
It looks delicious.

1968
01:22:09,119 --> 01:22:10,259
I think kids would love it.

1969
01:22:10,259 --> 01:22:13,699
[The hard-earned corn fritters go to kids]
That's a must-order for kids.

1970
01:22:16,819 --> 01:22:19,609
[Munching]

1971
01:22:20,659 --> 01:22:25,024
[Orders piling up due to the corn mistake]

1972
01:22:25,909 --> 01:22:29,519
[Meanwhile, in the dining area]

1973
01:22:29,519 --> 01:22:33,069
[Many people are waiting for their food...]

1974
01:22:34,759 --> 01:22:36,471
Five servings, right?

1975
01:22:39,039 --> 01:22:43,929
[Five dishes must go out immediately]

1976
01:22:44,579 --> 01:22:49,579
[Cooking starts without a moment to lose]

1977
01:22:51,199 --> 01:22:53,829
[It really does look delicious...]
It looks good.

1978
01:22:53,829 --> 01:22:55,789
It looks really good.

1979
01:22:57,249 --> 01:23:01,339
[Hoping for five plates...]

1980
01:23:02,279 --> 01:23:05,639
[Starting to plate]

1981
01:23:05,639 --> 01:23:08,459
[Hoping for five plates...]

1982
01:23:09,619 --> 01:23:12,559
The amount is tight...

1983
01:23:15,119 --> 01:23:17,639
This is a bit short.

1984
01:23:18,849 --> 01:23:22,279
[Not enough for one plate]
[Empty]

1985
01:23:22,279 --> 01:23:24,629
The Prep station must have given too little.

1986
01:23:24,629 --> 01:23:26,899
Is it the Wok station's fault?

1987
01:23:26,899 --> 01:23:28,199
Or is it the Prep station's fault?

1988
01:23:28,199 --> 01:23:29,319
- What should we do?
- That's...

1989
01:23:29,319 --> 01:23:31,219
- Whose fault is it?
- Prep station's.

1990
01:23:31,219 --> 01:23:33,009
Oh, it's the Prep station's fault.

1991
01:23:33,009 --> 01:23:36,179
[The Prep station failed to provide
enough ingredients...]

1992
01:23:36,179 --> 01:23:37,939
Is it all done?

1993
01:23:37,939 --> 01:23:40,429
[Brutally honest]
That's so "T" of you.

1994
01:23:42,359 --> 01:23:46,299
[What's wrong with everything today?]

1995
01:23:47,839 --> 01:23:50,309
We need to stir-fry one more.

1996
01:23:50,309 --> 01:23:52,389
Five servings, right?

1997
01:23:55,539 --> 01:23:57,299
[Scanning the portions]

1998
01:23:57,299 --> 01:23:59,839
[Five servings is possible!]
It's possible!

1999
01:24:00,709 --> 01:24:04,799
[As she re-divides it into five plates]

2000
01:24:05,799 --> 01:24:08,699
[Final boss Grandma appears]
Oh, the owner.

2001
01:24:10,959 --> 01:24:13,219
[Grandma approaches Sunny due to the noise]
It's not enough.

2002
01:24:13,219 --> 01:24:15,609
There are a lot of issues today.

2003
01:24:17,169 --> 01:24:19,599
It's a bit small, right, Grandma?

2004
01:24:19,599 --> 01:24:21,939
Should we just serve it?

2005
01:24:21,939 --> 01:24:23,439
[The senior is nervous, too]
Should we just serve it?

2006
01:24:23,439 --> 01:24:25,269
Yeah, it's a bit lacking.

2007
01:24:25,269 --> 01:24:27,329
It's a bit small.

2008
01:24:27,329 --> 01:24:28,999
Should we just serve it?

2009
01:24:28,999 --> 01:24:30,949
Yeah, it's a bit lacking.

2010
01:24:30,949 --> 01:24:32,279
[Firm]
Make one more!

2011
01:24:32,279 --> 01:24:33,969
She said to do it again.

2012
01:24:33,969 --> 01:24:35,519
Yeah, making one more is right.

2013
01:24:35,519 --> 01:24:37,589
[Grandma turns the 5 plates back into 4]
- Exactly. - Serving small portions is wrong.

2014
01:24:37,589 --> 01:24:38,849
Again...

2015
01:24:38,849 --> 01:24:41,219
- You can just make one more.
- Sunny split that into five.

2016
01:24:41,219 --> 01:24:43,159
[The portions were small, but you split it?]
You divided it into five?

2017
01:24:43,159 --> 01:24:46,359
But I thought the amount was sufficient.

2018
01:24:46,359 --> 01:24:48,839
[Actually a 24-year veteran]
Hey, what does a kitchen junior know!

2019
01:24:48,839 --> 01:24:51,113
What does a kitchen junior know!

2020
01:24:51,879 --> 01:24:53,859
[Suddenly playing the junior card?]
- Are you the junior here? - It's the seniors' fault.

2021
01:24:53,859 --> 01:24:55,479
Are you the kitchen junior here now?

2022
01:24:55,479 --> 01:24:58,559
[Shameless today]
Wow, seriously.

2023
01:24:59,239 --> 01:25:03,089
Things are unintentionally going wrong today.

2024
01:25:03,089 --> 01:25:05,082
Hurry up and make one more!

2025
01:25:05,082 --> 01:25:06,716
Make one more.

2026
01:25:07,339 --> 01:25:09,149
- We're short one?
- Yes.

2027
01:25:09,809 --> 01:25:11,343
[The prep station chief is troubled]
What's missing?

2028
01:25:11,343 --> 01:25:14,709
Short on ingredients? No way...

2029
01:25:14,709 --> 01:25:18,367
[Sunny is flustered by the series of problems]

2030
01:25:21,509 --> 01:25:25,229
[Apologetic and flustered]

2031
01:25:25,879 --> 01:25:27,889
Is there another fish for the room?

2032
01:25:27,889 --> 01:25:30,159
It's steaming now.

2033
01:25:30,159 --> 01:25:31,199
What else is there?

2034
01:25:31,199 --> 01:25:33,489
One more stir-fried green chili pepper.

2035
01:25:33,489 --> 01:25:36,269
[She's out of it...]

2036
01:25:36,879 --> 01:25:40,849
[Instead of the stunned Sunny]

2037
01:25:40,849 --> 01:25:43,139
[No.3 senior Xu Jian Kai
covers for her with Grandma?]

2038
01:25:43,139 --> 01:25:44,559
Xu Jian Kai is...

2039
01:25:44,559 --> 01:25:46,439
He's really good at backing her up.

2040
01:25:46,439 --> 01:25:47,779
What should I prepare for this?

2041
01:25:47,779 --> 01:25:50,629
Next is the fish dish.

2042
01:25:50,629 --> 01:25:52,119
- It's that one.
- He's teaching her everything.

2043
01:25:52,119 --> 01:25:54,559
Two, two of them.

2044
01:25:54,559 --> 01:25:56,549
[Xu Jian Kai even checks Sunny's orders]
She asks him when she's confused.

2045
01:25:56,549 --> 01:25:57,919
- She asks Xu Jian Kai.
- That's right.

2046
01:25:57,919 --> 01:26:00,099
Well, there are so many dishes on day two,

2047
01:26:00,099 --> 01:26:02,186
- and the portions are huge...
- Exactly.

2048
01:26:02,186 --> 01:26:03,589
Of course I'd be confused.

2049
01:26:03,589 --> 01:26:05,459
- Xu Jian Kai is doing a great job.
- He's a real mentor.

2050
01:26:05,459 --> 01:26:07,059
- He really is.
- He's a true mentor.

2051
01:26:07,059 --> 01:26:08,979
Oh-ho.

2052
01:26:08,979 --> 01:26:10,099
[My mentor, whom I'm not ready to admit?]

2053
01:26:10,099 --> 01:26:12,539
What's with the "Oh-ho"?

2054
01:26:14,119 --> 01:26:17,679
[For Sunny, who's still confused]
There's more. Wait.

2055
01:26:18,419 --> 01:26:20,769
It's done. You can take it out.

2056
01:26:20,769 --> 01:26:22,239
[Casually drops the ingredients]

2057
01:26:22,239 --> 01:26:24,679
- He's looking out for her in a casual way.
- He really is.

2058
01:26:24,679 --> 01:26:26,869
Xu Jian Kai is being a bit casual...

2059
01:26:26,869 --> 01:26:28,339
- without making it obvious.
- He's a bit of a tsundere.

2060
01:26:28,339 --> 01:26:31,719
Since he's acting like a tsundere,
she probably didn't realize he was her mentor.

2061
01:26:31,719 --> 01:26:33,799
- That's...
- He moves like a shadow.

2062
01:26:33,799 --> 01:26:35,759
- He was a shadow mentor.
- Exactly.

2063
01:26:35,759 --> 01:26:37,299
Am I the only one who can't see it?

2064
01:26:37,299 --> 01:26:38,759
- See what?
- What?

2065
01:26:38,759 --> 01:26:40,129
Xu Jian Kai.

2066
01:26:40,129 --> 01:26:41,399
[Here's Xu Jian Kai]
- Why? Why? - Right now.

2067
01:26:41,399 --> 01:26:42,879
- He's right there.
- He's clearly visible.

2068
01:26:42,879 --> 01:26:44,289
[Here's Xu Jian Kai again]
You can't see him there?

2069
01:26:44,289 --> 01:26:45,939
- He's right next to you.
- Exactly.

2070
01:26:45,939 --> 01:26:47,059
He's been there the whole time.

2071
01:26:47,059 --> 01:26:48,629
Well, Chef Jung Ji Sun only...

2072
01:26:48,629 --> 01:26:50,419
[Only those who teach skills are mentors]
recognizes someone as a mentor

2073
01:26:50,419 --> 01:26:51,649
if they teach her technical skills.

2074
01:26:51,649 --> 01:26:53,109
- That's her standard.
- So that's a mentor to her.

2075
01:26:53,109 --> 01:26:55,519
[Teasing her]
Just being kind and caring...

2076
01:26:55,519 --> 01:26:57,429
and doing things like that...

2077
01:26:57,429 --> 01:26:58,679
[Kindness alone doesn't make a mentor]
and looking out for her...

2078
01:26:58,679 --> 01:27:00,229
Comforting her and saying,
"It's okay, you're the junior."

2079
01:27:00,229 --> 01:27:01,989
That's not a mentor to her.

2080
01:27:01,989 --> 01:27:04,479
She judges them by whether
she has something to learn from them.

2081
01:27:04,479 --> 01:27:06,389
Then are Senior An and Senior Lu mentors?

2082
01:27:06,389 --> 01:27:07,879
They definitely are.

2083
01:27:07,879 --> 01:27:09,249
- Are they?
- Absolutely.

2084
01:27:09,249 --> 01:27:10,289
- What about them?
- They are.

2085
01:27:10,289 --> 01:27:11,729
What about Sorem?

2086
01:27:11,729 --> 01:27:12,919
- Sorem is too.
- Right.

2087
01:27:12,919 --> 01:27:15,969
He comes over to help with things
and points out mistakes.

2088
01:27:15,969 --> 01:27:18,019
[Why not Xu Jian Kai?]
- But not Xu Jian Kai? - Xu Jian Kai...

2089
01:27:18,019 --> 01:27:19,489
He doesn't teach you?

2090
01:27:19,489 --> 01:27:21,219
I hope Xu Jian Kai doesn't watch this show.

2091
01:27:21,219 --> 01:27:22,919
Xu Jian Kai's feelings will be hurt.

2092
01:27:22,919 --> 01:27:24,789
- Won't he be so hurt?
- This is going to hurt.

2093
01:27:24,789 --> 01:27:28,629
[Difficulty: Max] [Becoming Sunny's Mentor]
Let's see.

2094
01:27:28,629 --> 01:27:31,649
He seems to take good care of her
in a subtle way.

2095
01:27:31,649 --> 01:27:33,319
Should I serve two orders?

2096
01:27:33,319 --> 01:27:35,799
Be careful not to burn your hands.

2097
01:27:35,799 --> 01:27:38,259
He's telling her to be
careful not to get burned.

2098
01:27:38,259 --> 01:27:39,519
He's so thoughtful.

2099
01:27:39,519 --> 01:27:40,919
- Such a sweet guy...
- He's so kind.

2100
01:27:40,919 --> 01:27:42,099
My goodness.

2101
01:27:42,099 --> 01:27:44,049
He even wiped the plate clean.

2102
01:27:44,049 --> 01:27:45,939
There's a saying in China.

2103
01:27:45,939 --> 01:27:48,769
"Is it not a joy
to have friends come from afar?"

2104
01:27:48,769 --> 01:27:50,529
Wow, "from afar."

2105
01:27:50,529 --> 01:27:53,089
"Is it not a joy
to have friends come from afar?"

2106
01:27:54,149 --> 01:27:55,269
"From afar."

2107
01:27:55,269 --> 01:27:56,469
He called her a friend. Oh, my.

2108
01:27:56,469 --> 01:27:57,779
A friend.

2109
01:27:57,779 --> 01:27:59,039
He called her a friend. Oh, my.

2110
01:27:59,039 --> 01:28:00,199
A friend.

2111
01:28:00,199 --> 01:28:02,159
[Touched]
- Oh, wow. - That's amazing.

2112
01:28:02,159 --> 01:28:03,839
[Sorry, Xu Jian Kai]
Please edit out what I said earlier.

2113
01:28:03,839 --> 01:28:06,419
[I can't believe the MZ senior was
such a pure soul]

2114
01:28:06,419 --> 01:28:07,619
I'm breaking out in a sweat.

2115
01:28:07,619 --> 01:28:09,079
"Is it not a joy to have friends

2116
01:28:09,079 --> 01:28:10,739
come from afar?"

2117
01:28:10,739 --> 01:28:12,608
- I'm about to cry.
- That was so moving.

2118
01:28:12,608 --> 01:28:14,369
- I'm actually tearing up.
- I'm getting emotional.

2119
01:28:14,369 --> 01:28:16,279
Oh, our Xu Jian Kai.

2120
01:28:16,279 --> 01:28:17,589
Chef Sunny was too harsh.

2121
01:28:17,589 --> 01:28:19,139
He'd be so disappointed if he heard her.

2122
01:28:19,139 --> 01:28:20,719
- I'll cry if I see him.
- Look at Xu Jian Kai.

2123
01:28:20,719 --> 01:28:22,019
Such a kind-hearted senior.

2124
01:28:22,019 --> 01:28:23,829
[Everyone acknowledges him]
I want a mentor like him.

2125
01:28:23,829 --> 01:28:25,079
I'm so touched.

2126
01:28:25,079 --> 01:28:26,319
[It's truly hard to get Sunny's approval...]
Seriously.

2127
01:28:26,319 --> 01:28:29,209
- I wish I had a senior like him.
- I know, right?

2128
01:28:29,617 --> 01:28:31,586
There's a saying in China.

2129
01:28:31,586 --> 01:28:34,728
Do you know that, "Is it not a joy
to have friends come from afar?"

2130
01:28:34,728 --> 01:28:37,128
- Using such a quote...
- Exactly.

2131
01:28:37,779 --> 01:28:40,369
It's what I usually do anyway.

2132
01:28:40,369 --> 01:28:42,159
I thought I'd be more familiar and faster.

2133
01:28:42,159 --> 01:28:45,619
Plus, the corn fritters failed once.

2134
01:28:45,619 --> 01:28:50,566
So I felt I had to hurry and help her.

2135
01:28:52,769 --> 01:28:54,179
Wow, really.

2136
01:28:54,179 --> 01:28:55,399
His heart...

2137
01:28:55,399 --> 01:28:56,959
- Xu Jian Kai is a great senior.
- He really is.

2138
01:28:56,959 --> 01:28:58,619
My goodness.

2139
01:28:59,539 --> 01:29:02,119
A friend came from afar.

2140
01:29:02,119 --> 01:29:03,319
My goodness.

2141
01:29:03,319 --> 01:29:06,939
[Despite Xu Jian Kai's affectionate help]

2142
01:29:07,809 --> 01:29:13,419
[Things keep going wrong for Sunny today]

2143
01:29:14,629 --> 01:29:19,019
[I've become someone who only
receives help from the seniors...]

2144
01:29:19,839 --> 01:29:24,119
[Feeling a sense of self-reproach]

2145
01:29:25,109 --> 01:29:28,621
[Approaching aggressively once again]

2146
01:29:28,621 --> 01:29:30,304
The boss.

2147
01:29:32,039 --> 01:29:35,479
[Flinch]

2148
01:29:35,479 --> 01:29:37,029
Please prepare this order first.

2149
01:29:37,029 --> 01:29:39,299
- This one?
- Yes.

2150
01:29:39,299 --> 01:29:43,329
[What is Sunny's next dish?]

2151
01:29:43,329 --> 01:29:45,429
[The Duck Egg Corn Fritters she messed up]
We're doing corn again.

2152
01:29:45,429 --> 01:29:46,769
- Corn.
- Oh, that.

2153
01:29:46,769 --> 01:29:48,649
A second attempt.

2154
01:29:49,329 --> 01:29:53,199
[Trying again on her own without any help]

2155
01:29:53,919 --> 01:29:55,859
[The cause of the previous failure:
custard powder]

2156
01:29:55,859 --> 01:29:57,719
Now, the custard powder.

2157
01:29:57,719 --> 01:30:00,709
- Earlier, she coated it too early.
- Yes.

2158
01:30:00,709 --> 01:30:02,799
It'll be done quickly now.

2159
01:30:02,799 --> 01:30:04,679
[Adding a handful more just in case]

2160
01:30:04,679 --> 01:30:06,339
A lot.

2161
01:30:06,339 --> 01:30:07,589
I'm just going to use a lot.

2162
01:30:07,589 --> 01:30:09,629
Since I don't know when I'll fry it.

2163
01:30:12,159 --> 01:30:14,099
Is it not enough? Or is it enough?

2164
01:30:14,099 --> 01:30:16,389
It's enough.

2165
01:30:16,389 --> 01:30:19,899
[Perfectly set
after checking repeatedly for mistakes]

2166
01:30:22,529 --> 01:30:25,294
Now, into this...

2167
01:30:28,479 --> 01:30:30,951
[Crispy texture, perfect sweet and salty mix]
- Is it sweet? - It's very sweet.

2168
01:30:30,951 --> 01:30:32,359
It's sweet and salty.

2169
01:30:32,359 --> 01:30:34,247
[A huge success this time]
The sweetness is more...

2170
01:30:34,247 --> 01:30:37,095
- Yes, custard powder is very sweet.
- It must have a savory kick.

2171
01:30:37,095 --> 01:30:39,703
It looks delicious.

2172
01:30:39,703 --> 01:30:43,939
[Quickly returning after delivery]

2173
01:30:43,939 --> 01:30:47,503
[Setting up the next dish immediately]

2174
01:30:48,343 --> 01:30:49,911
- Does it just go out like this?
- Yes.

2175
01:30:49,911 --> 01:30:51,729
It's Stir-fried Beef Aorta.

2176
01:30:51,729 --> 01:30:53,943
[Chengdu Granny's specialty: beef aorta]
- This is beef aorta. - Aorta?

2177
01:30:53,943 --> 01:30:56,599
An aorta dish?

2178
01:30:57,271 --> 01:30:59,255
[Sunny is extra meticulous today]

2179
01:30:59,255 --> 01:31:02,167
Next is this.

2180
01:31:02,167 --> 01:31:03,879
This is... this one, right?

2181
01:31:03,879 --> 01:31:06,543
It's Braised Freshwater Fish with Agastache!

2182
01:31:07,479 --> 01:31:09,959
[Sunny finishes the braised fish too]
It must be steamed freshwater fish.

2183
01:31:09,959 --> 01:31:12,775
These are the green onions
to sprinkle at the end.

2184
01:31:12,775 --> 01:31:15,055
That looks delicious.

2185
01:31:16,631 --> 01:31:18,167
Does this go out right away too?

2186
01:31:18,167 --> 01:31:21,143
No, it can wait a bit.

2187
01:31:21,143 --> 01:31:25,129
[Checking every little detail meticulously]

2188
01:31:25,959 --> 01:31:30,959
[Sunny, the best at her job]
[Zero mistakes after that!]

2189
01:31:31,909 --> 01:31:32,983
You can take a break.

2190
01:31:32,983 --> 01:31:35,549
There are seats outside.

2191
01:31:37,139 --> 01:31:41,607
[After four hours of dinner service]
[Getting some fresh air]

2192
01:31:41,607 --> 01:31:45,079
[Staring blankly]

2193
01:31:45,079 --> 01:31:46,407
Sunny, you speak Chinese well.

2194
01:31:46,407 --> 01:31:48,103
Chinese?

2195
01:31:48,103 --> 01:31:50,289
It's hard. It's really hard.

2196
01:31:50,289 --> 01:31:52,309
I can't understand what you're saying.

2197
01:31:52,309 --> 01:31:55,143
I can't understand anything when it gets busy.

2198
01:31:55,143 --> 01:31:58,919
That's because
you're all using Sichuan dialect.

2199
01:31:58,919 --> 01:32:01,111
But Sunny, you speak Chinese really well.

2200
01:32:01,111 --> 01:32:02,895
- Really?
- Yes.

2201
01:32:04,343 --> 01:32:06,508
[She's smiling on the outside]

2202
01:32:06,508 --> 01:32:08,229
Why?

2203
01:32:08,229 --> 01:32:12,602
While I was working,
I kept thinking that I was such a fool.

2204
01:32:13,319 --> 01:32:14,679
I was so embarrassed.

2205
01:32:14,679 --> 01:32:15,911
I just kept feeling...

2206
01:32:15,911 --> 01:32:19,159
[Helplessness from hitting a wall]
It's the first time I've felt like I've hit my limit.

2207
01:32:19,159 --> 01:32:21,111
You can't do that.

2208
01:32:21,111 --> 01:32:24,231
[Mistakes right before the promotion]
You have to coat it with powder again.

2209
01:32:24,231 --> 01:32:25,479
Redo it.

2210
01:32:25,479 --> 01:32:29,671
Do it over.

2211
01:32:29,671 --> 01:32:31,175
[Even the usually warm Grandma scolds her]

2212
01:32:31,175 --> 01:32:33,679
Welcome. How many in your party?

2213
01:32:34,679 --> 01:32:37,097
Tomorrow is the third day.

2214
01:32:38,471 --> 01:32:40,375
I need to change my strategy.

2215
01:32:40,375 --> 01:32:41,687
[She can't lose the chance to be promoted]
I need to be quick.

2216
01:32:41,687 --> 01:32:43,319
Because I don't have much time.

2217
01:32:43,319 --> 01:32:47,239
- I kept thinking I had to do something.
- Of course.

2218
01:32:47,239 --> 01:32:49,447
[Sunny is deep in thought]

2219
01:32:49,447 --> 01:32:52,119
Have you ever been to a Korean restaurant here?

2220
01:32:52,119 --> 01:32:54,439
Have you ever tried Korean food?

2221
01:32:54,439 --> 01:32:56,775
No? None of you have?

2222
01:32:56,775 --> 01:32:59,815
There are only Korean buffets here.

2223
01:32:59,815 --> 01:33:01,719
Korean buffets are expensive.

2224
01:33:01,719 --> 01:33:04,599
Are they very expensive?

2225
01:33:04,599 --> 01:33:06,775
Are there many people there?

2226
01:33:06,775 --> 01:33:08,183
Yes, there are.

2227
01:33:08,183 --> 01:33:11,527
It's very crowded at night.

2228
01:33:11,527 --> 01:33:13,847
You said there aren't many people at night?

2229
01:33:14,695 --> 01:33:18,007
[Deep in thought...]

2230
01:33:18,007 --> 01:33:20,039
[What is Sunny thinking?]
Oh? What is it?

2231
01:33:20,039 --> 01:33:22,055
What is it? What is it?

2232
01:33:22,055 --> 01:33:24,631
Let's clean up now.

2233
01:33:24,631 --> 01:33:25,975
[We can go home after cleaning!]
Let's clean up.

2234
01:33:25,975 --> 01:33:27,943
- Let's clean up.
- Cleaning? Okay.

2235
01:33:27,943 --> 01:33:29,647
- Let's clean.
- Okay.

2236
01:33:30,711 --> 01:33:32,295
[Cleaning time before heading home]
Careful, careful.

2237
01:33:32,295 --> 01:33:33,431
Cleaning time is the best.

2238
01:33:33,431 --> 01:33:35,949
Okay, okay.

2239
01:33:41,063 --> 01:33:44,679
If the staff saw her cleaning...

2240
01:33:44,679 --> 01:33:47,079
- They'd find it refreshing, right?
- Exactly.

2241
01:33:48,391 --> 01:33:51,591
[The owner-chef is cleaning the floor!]
They'd be like, "The chef is cleaning?"

2242
01:33:51,591 --> 01:33:54,599
[After a day of excitement for a promotion
and a series of mistakes]

2243
01:33:54,599 --> 01:33:56,839
[The morning of day three in Chengdu dawns]
The morning of day three.

2244
01:33:56,839 --> 01:33:58,311
Now, it's day three.

2245
01:33:58,311 --> 01:33:59,863
[Sunny is nervous after yesterday's mistakes]
I was really nervous on day three.

2246
01:33:59,863 --> 01:34:01,543
Day three is important.

2247
01:34:01,543 --> 01:34:03,719
I was so nervous.

2248
01:34:03,719 --> 01:34:05,599
[6:00 AM. Sunny gets ready for work early]
Woke up early.

2249
01:34:05,599 --> 01:34:08,319
Is she going to eat?

2250
01:34:08,319 --> 01:34:11,079
<i>You have to coat it in powder again.</i>

2251
01:34:11,079 --> 01:34:14,383
<i>Do it over.</i>

2252
01:34:15,831 --> 01:34:16,919
[Day 1 / Day 3]

2253
01:34:16,919 --> 01:34:20,699
[Her eyeliner is as thick as her determination]

2254
01:34:21,839 --> 01:34:24,919
[With a more determined step than usual]

2255
01:34:24,919 --> 01:34:26,631
[She heads somewhere...]

2256
01:34:26,631 --> 01:34:30,111
[Looking around]

2257
01:34:30,919 --> 01:34:33,191
Wait a minute.

2258
01:34:33,191 --> 01:34:35,287
[Walking briskly]

2259
01:34:35,287 --> 01:34:36,343
Jianbing.

2260
01:34:36,343 --> 01:34:38,327
- Jianbing.
- Yes.

2261
01:34:38,327 --> 01:34:39,815
[What is jianbing?]
- Is that jianbing? - Yes.

2262
01:34:39,815 --> 01:34:41,909
[Spreading the grain batter thinly]
This grain batter...

2263
01:34:41,909 --> 01:34:43,303
It's different in every region,

2264
01:34:43,303 --> 01:34:45,863
[Topped with scallions, sausage, and buckwheat]
and different at every shop.

2265
01:34:45,863 --> 01:34:47,239
That looks good.

2266
01:34:47,239 --> 01:34:49,279
- That looks good.
- That's fried buckwheat.

2267
01:34:49,279 --> 01:34:50,839
[Jianbing, a popular Chinese street snack]
- Fried buckwheat. - Is that buckwheat?

2268
01:34:50,839 --> 01:34:51,959
I'm hungry.

2269
01:34:51,959 --> 01:34:54,471
It's delicious to eat it plain like this.

2270
01:34:54,471 --> 01:34:56,519
[Moist and chewy]

2271
01:34:56,519 --> 01:34:57,639
Jianbing is delicious.

2272
01:34:57,639 --> 01:34:59,191
Just to eat jianbing,

2273
01:34:59,191 --> 01:35:00,807
I've even done day trips to Shanghai.

2274
01:35:00,807 --> 01:35:02,099
- Really? That much?
- Yes.

2275
01:35:02,099 --> 01:35:03,909
Because when I was studying in China,

2276
01:35:03,909 --> 01:35:07,439
[She ate jianbing every morning as a student]
I ate it every morning.

2277
01:35:08,247 --> 01:35:10,183
[She still looks for jianbing
when she needs energy]

2278
01:35:10,183 --> 01:35:13,839
[Chomp]

2279
01:35:13,839 --> 01:35:15,799
Mmm.

2280
01:35:15,799 --> 01:35:19,575
[The taste from her student days]
[Mmm, mmm]

2281
01:35:19,575 --> 01:35:21,207
How is it?

2282
01:35:21,207 --> 01:35:23,479
It's delicious.

2283
01:35:24,413 --> 01:35:26,352
I'll be a bit faster today.

2284
01:35:26,352 --> 01:35:29,553
[No mistakes today with the power of jianbing!]

2285
01:35:30,887 --> 01:35:33,799
[Day 3 of undercover. Sunny is at work!]
Good morning.

2286
01:35:33,799 --> 01:35:35,383
[The hall is already crowded with staff]

2287
01:35:35,383 --> 01:35:36,567
Wow, there are so many people.

2288
01:35:36,567 --> 01:35:38,287
There really are.

2289
01:35:39,015 --> 01:35:42,455
[Sunny comes out after changing clothes]

2290
01:35:42,455 --> 01:35:44,679
[Swish!]

2291
01:35:44,679 --> 01:35:47,823
Please take one of these.

2292
01:35:48,647 --> 01:35:50,887
Take one of these.

2293
01:35:50,887 --> 01:35:53,329
- She's handing something out.
- It's good for you. Help yourself.

2294
01:35:53,329 --> 01:35:57,127
[Sunny handing something out?]
- It's good for you. I take it too! - Thank you.

2295
01:35:57,127 --> 01:35:58,439
Oh, this.

2296
01:35:58,439 --> 01:36:00,326
I brought it to share with them all.

2297
01:36:00,326 --> 01:36:03,057
- Is it red ginseng?
- Yes, red ginseng extract.

2298
01:36:04,503 --> 01:36:06,631
It's red ginseng.

2299
01:36:06,631 --> 01:36:08,311
Red ginseng.

2300
01:36:08,311 --> 01:36:10,791
Do you know red ginseng? Red ginseng!

2301
01:36:10,791 --> 01:36:12,039
Hong-san?

2302
01:36:12,039 --> 01:36:13,839
- It's...
- Hong-san?

2303
01:36:13,839 --> 01:36:15,911
- Is it Korean coffee?
- I take this every day.

2304
01:36:15,911 --> 01:36:18,135
No, no. This is good for your health.

2305
01:36:18,135 --> 01:36:20,183
I have one every day! Try it.

2306
01:36:20,183 --> 01:36:21,623
[Seniors are intrigued by the health benefits]
- What is it? - Thank you.

2307
01:36:21,623 --> 01:36:23,367
Right, they'll love gifts like that.

2308
01:36:23,367 --> 01:36:25,799
You can eat it like this!

2309
01:36:25,799 --> 01:36:28,262
[All eyes on the ginseng]
Is it a cat treat?

2310
01:36:28,262 --> 01:36:29,731
It's not a cat treat.

2311
01:36:29,731 --> 01:36:31,495
[Like this?]

2312
01:36:31,495 --> 01:36:33,111
Try it.

2313
01:36:33,111 --> 01:36:34,407
[But why red ginseng all of a sudden?]

2314
01:36:34,407 --> 01:36:37,687
I wanted to get closer to them.

2315
01:36:37,687 --> 01:36:39,287
[Handing them out one by one]
She's earning a lot of points.

2316
01:36:39,287 --> 01:36:40,807
- It's strategic.
- I see.

2317
01:36:40,807 --> 01:36:42,343
[Red ginseng from the rookie]
- I want to be friends. - Try one.

2318
01:36:42,343 --> 01:36:44,375
I need to learn from that.

2319
01:36:44,375 --> 01:36:47,863
[Sunny's secret weapon from Korea!]

2320
01:36:47,863 --> 01:36:49,591
Ginseng.

2321
01:36:49,591 --> 01:36:52,839
- I know it's very precious in China.
- Thank you.

2322
01:36:52,839 --> 01:36:55,569
First of all, it's for... Guanxi, I guess?

2323
01:36:55,569 --> 01:36:57,655
[Building connections through the Guanxi culture]
I'm also grateful to them, so...

2324
01:36:57,655 --> 01:36:59,703
I'm giving them out to everyone.

2325
01:36:59,703 --> 01:37:03,063
It's to improve my image.

2326
01:37:03,063 --> 01:37:05,655
[A sort of bribery strategy?]
I thought they'd see me in a better light.

2327
01:37:05,655 --> 01:37:07,271
- Hello, Boss.
- This is good.

2328
01:37:07,271 --> 01:37:08,535
- Please take one of these.
- Yes.

2329
01:37:08,535 --> 01:37:10,471
[Please look kindly upon me]
- What's this? Coffee? - It's for your health.

2330
01:37:10,471 --> 01:37:12,707
It's not coffee.

2331
01:37:13,383 --> 01:37:17,607
[With Sunny's big-picture strategy...]

2332
01:37:17,607 --> 01:37:20,391
[A red ginseng tasting session opens in the back]
- What's this? - Hong-san.

2333
01:37:20,391 --> 01:37:22,471
- Hong-san.
- You tried it, what does it taste like?

2334
01:37:22,471 --> 01:37:24,983
It tastes like medicine.

2335
01:37:24,983 --> 01:37:26,819
It's their first time trying it.

2336
01:37:26,819 --> 01:37:29,383
- It's a health supplement.
- It has a sweet, honey-like taste too.

2337
01:37:29,383 --> 01:37:30,903
Sunny said she takes this every day.

2338
01:37:30,903 --> 01:37:32,951
She probably took it often as an athlete.

2339
01:37:32,951 --> 01:37:34,919
[The supplement she took as a boxer?]
Ah, since she was an athlete...

2340
01:37:34,919 --> 01:37:36,039
"Then I'll take it."

2341
01:37:36,039 --> 01:37:39,175
[An unexpected boost in credibility...]
They're thinking, "This must be legit."

2342
01:37:39,175 --> 01:37:41,559
Who would think she's 44 years old?

2343
01:37:41,559 --> 01:37:42,951
Red ginseng was the secret.

2344
01:37:42,951 --> 01:37:45,831
- 44?
- Yeah!

2345
01:37:45,831 --> 01:37:50,270
[Sunny's red ginseng gift earns her points]
Who would think she's 44?

2346
01:37:51,089 --> 01:37:53,474
- Be elegant and do your job properly.
- I'm getting used to the roll call now.

2347
01:37:53,474 --> 01:37:54,609
Me, too.

2348
01:37:54,609 --> 01:37:56,764
I'd feel empty without it now.

2349
01:37:57,879 --> 01:38:02,047
[09:10 AM, prep begins after the meeting]
Let the Squid Game begin.

2350
01:38:04,183 --> 01:38:05,783
[Day 3 of the kitchen undercover mission]
Day 3.

2351
01:38:05,783 --> 01:38:09,183
[Current position:
Still the Prep station junior]

2352
01:38:10,423 --> 01:38:11,591
[Focusing and organizing the prep station]

2353
01:38:11,591 --> 01:38:13,607
Okay, clean up the Prep station.

2354
01:38:13,607 --> 01:38:15,623
For tomorrow's service,

2355
01:38:15,623 --> 01:38:17,911
practice so you can handle stir-fries.

2356
01:38:17,911 --> 01:38:21,319
[Promotion to the Wok station is near]
He said she'd be on the stove today.

2357
01:38:21,319 --> 01:38:25,351
[She must perform perfectly without mistakes]

2358
01:38:25,351 --> 01:38:26,695
[Determined, she starts slicing duck gizzards]
Duck gizzards?

2359
01:38:26,695 --> 01:38:28,479
They're huge.

2360
01:38:29,463 --> 01:38:31,655
[Then, Grandma arrives at work]
Oh, Grandma is here too.

2361
01:38:31,655 --> 01:38:33,823
Grandma's here.

2362
01:38:34,871 --> 01:38:38,975
[Grandma quietly enters the kitchen]

2363
01:38:39,831 --> 01:38:42,783
[Putting on her chef's hat]

2364
01:38:43,991 --> 01:38:45,495
[Looking around]

2365
01:38:45,495 --> 01:38:50,023
[She scans the entire kitchen]

2366
01:38:50,023 --> 01:38:51,831
[Hey!]

2367
01:38:51,831 --> 01:38:54,855
You, slice some pork belly.

2368
01:38:54,855 --> 01:38:56,599
Slice it a bit thick.

2369
01:38:56,599 --> 01:38:58,959
Keep it consistent.

2370
01:38:59,939 --> 01:39:01,959
- She's checking everything.
- Everything.

2371
01:39:01,959 --> 01:39:04,087
She's checking every detail.

2372
01:39:04,087 --> 01:39:05,399
We don't have peanuts right now.

2373
01:39:05,399 --> 01:39:07,903
You don't need peanuts.

2374
01:39:09,079 --> 01:39:12,919
[This time, she approaches Sunny...]

2375
01:39:12,919 --> 01:39:15,855
[Glance]

2376
01:39:17,319 --> 01:39:18,551
[Let's see your knife work]

2377
01:39:18,551 --> 01:39:21,415
A knife work test! She must be nervous.

2378
01:39:21,415 --> 01:39:24,695
[Nervous]

2379
01:39:24,695 --> 01:39:26,119
[It's a chance to show her skills!]

2380
01:39:26,119 --> 01:39:27,783
- You're making flower shapes?
- That's right.

2381
01:39:27,783 --> 01:39:30,039
[She calmly starts scoring the meat...]
I'll score it like this.

2382
01:39:30,039 --> 01:39:31,879
A bit deeper.

2383
01:39:31,879 --> 01:39:33,735
You have to cut deeper!

2384
01:39:33,735 --> 01:39:35,239
Try going a bit deeper.

2385
01:39:35,239 --> 01:39:36,967
- Shallow?
- No, harder.

2386
01:39:36,967 --> 01:39:39,111
I'll show you.

2387
01:39:39,111 --> 01:39:41,111
I want to see Grandma's knife work.

2388
01:39:41,999 --> 01:39:45,087
[Watch closely!]

2389
01:39:47,095 --> 01:39:49,367
Slice it further down like this.

2390
01:39:49,367 --> 01:39:51,607
[Scoring it as deeply as possible]
Deeper.

2391
01:39:53,367 --> 01:39:56,151
[Then turning it to slice sideways]

2392
01:39:56,151 --> 01:39:57,799
She's making it look pretty.

2393
01:39:57,799 --> 01:39:59,623
She has to make it look like a flower, right?

2394
01:39:59,623 --> 01:40:02,631
[The flower shape is complete]

2395
01:40:02,631 --> 01:40:05,383
When you fry it, it spreads out like a flower.

2396
01:40:05,383 --> 01:40:06,919
It looks like it'll be chewy.

2397
01:40:06,919 --> 01:40:09,607
Make the cuts as deep as you can!

2398
01:40:09,607 --> 01:40:11,943
Deeper.

2399
01:40:11,943 --> 01:40:15,223
That way, it'll bloom beautifully
when it's fried.

2400
01:40:15,223 --> 01:40:17,151
I understand.

2401
01:40:18,167 --> 01:40:21,191
[Re-challenge]

2402
01:40:21,191 --> 01:40:23,695
[As deep as possible]

2403
01:40:25,159 --> 01:40:27,431
[Blink, blink]

2404
01:40:27,431 --> 01:40:30,495
[She carefully slices each one...]

2405
01:40:31,783 --> 01:40:33,169
Should I cut it deeper?

2406
01:40:33,169 --> 01:40:35,159
That's enough.

2407
01:40:35,159 --> 01:40:37,583
[A successful attempt]

2408
01:40:38,295 --> 01:40:40,695
[Seeing that Sunny has the hang of it...]

2409
01:40:40,695 --> 01:40:42,807
[Swish]

2410
01:40:42,807 --> 01:40:45,431
[I'm on my way]

2411
01:40:45,431 --> 01:40:47,559
Too thick. Thinner.

2412
01:40:47,559 --> 01:40:51,159
[She coolly leaves without looking back]

2413
01:40:51,159 --> 01:40:52,727
Looking at her today,

2414
01:40:52,727 --> 01:40:55,191
Sunny's knife work has improved.

2415
01:40:55,191 --> 01:40:57,767
She's doing better than yesterday.

2416
01:40:57,767 --> 01:41:00,391
She was always good.

2417
01:41:00,391 --> 01:41:03,879
[Because she's a 24-year veteran chef]
It's because she's already skilled.

2418
01:41:03,879 --> 01:41:06,991
[Our Sunny is so good,
there's no need to watch her]

2419
01:41:07,767 --> 01:41:12,495
[She's starting to show her true skills!]

2420
01:41:15,639 --> 01:41:18,303
For lunch today,

2421
01:41:19,143 --> 01:41:21,463
let's have Stir-fried Chicken
with Water Spinach.

2422
01:41:21,463 --> 01:41:23,399
- Stir-fried chicken?
- Yeah.

2423
01:41:23,399 --> 01:41:25,559
[Okay, got it]

2424
01:41:25,559 --> 01:41:28,095
[Staff meal?]

2425
01:41:28,711 --> 01:41:30,871
[Glance]

2426
01:41:30,871 --> 01:41:34,783
[Sunny glancing at the senior chefs?]

2427
01:41:35,943 --> 01:41:40,215
[Just then, the head of the Prep station
approaches Sunny...]

2428
01:41:40,215 --> 01:41:43,889
What are you having for the staff meal today?

2429
01:41:43,889 --> 01:41:46,231
Originally,

2430
01:41:46,231 --> 01:41:49,279
we were going to have
Stir-fried Chicken with Water Spinach.

2431
01:41:49,279 --> 01:41:52,199
Could I prepare the staff meal today?

2432
01:41:52,199 --> 01:41:53,895
- Oh, of course.
- It's the same.

2433
01:41:53,895 --> 01:41:55,287
- Exactly.
- You're identical.

2434
01:41:55,287 --> 01:41:56,807
- Closer.
- She had the same idea as me.

2435
01:41:56,807 --> 01:41:58,183
[Both planning to volunteer for the staff meal]
You're exactly the same.

2436
01:41:58,183 --> 01:42:00,215
But don't you usually think that way?

2437
01:42:00,215 --> 01:42:02,055
Laura.

2438
01:42:02,055 --> 01:42:05,271
[Ctrl+C]
Could I try making lunch?

2439
01:42:05,271 --> 01:42:08,503
[Ctrl+V]
Could I prepare the staff meal today?

2440
01:42:08,503 --> 01:42:09,975
- Of course.
- Is that possible?

2441
01:42:09,975 --> 01:42:12,099
Even the timing is the same.
Lunch on the third day.

2442
01:42:12,099 --> 01:42:13,367
- Just say you're siblings.
- They're identical.

2443
01:42:13,367 --> 01:42:14,951
From now on, you two are siblings.

2444
01:42:14,951 --> 01:42:16,343
The Jung-Kwon siblings.

2445
01:42:16,343 --> 01:42:18,423
- They're siblings, I'm telling you.
- They really are similar.

2446
01:42:18,423 --> 01:42:19,687
How did this happen?

2447
01:42:19,687 --> 01:42:22,695
Could I prepare the staff meal today?

2448
01:42:22,695 --> 01:42:23,911
- Of course.
- Is that possible?

2449
01:42:23,911 --> 01:42:25,543
Of course you can.

2450
01:42:25,543 --> 01:42:27,655
Tell me what you need me to prepare.

2451
01:42:27,655 --> 01:42:30,599
I've prepared the meat.

2452
01:42:30,599 --> 01:42:32,759
I bought the necessary ingredients outside.

2453
01:42:32,759 --> 01:42:33,831
I already bought them.

2454
01:42:33,831 --> 01:42:34,919
You already bought them?

2455
01:42:34,919 --> 01:42:37,351
[Bought meat while getting breakfast]
- You brought it yourself? - Yes.

2456
01:42:37,351 --> 01:42:39,991
So, besides the meat, I need onions...

2457
01:42:39,991 --> 01:42:41,489
- What is she making?
- Exactly.

2458
01:42:41,489 --> 01:42:43,543
I need other vegetables.

2459
01:42:43,543 --> 01:42:45,191
Do you have carrots?

2460
01:42:45,191 --> 01:42:46,359
- Carrots?
- Yes.

2461
01:42:46,359 --> 01:42:47,959
[What will Sunny make for lunch?]
What is it?

2462
01:42:47,959 --> 01:42:50,151
- It's a red radish.
- I see.

2463
01:42:50,151 --> 01:42:52,263
- You can use these carrots.
- Yes, that's right.

2464
01:42:52,263 --> 01:42:53,639
Is it Korean food?

2465
01:42:53,639 --> 01:42:55,735
I'll prepare a meat dish.

2466
01:42:55,735 --> 01:42:58,196
- It's a Korean dish.
- I see, I see.

2467
01:42:58,196 --> 01:43:00,711
- It's a Korean dish.
- I see, I see.

2468
01:43:00,711 --> 01:43:02,567
[Why Korean food instead of Chinese?]
I'll prepare a dish.

2469
01:43:02,567 --> 01:43:04,295
I thought I shouldn't...

2470
01:43:04,295 --> 01:43:06,551
I shouldn't approach this with Chinese cuisine.

2471
01:43:06,551 --> 01:43:07,939
- Instead?
- Instead?

2472
01:43:07,939 --> 01:43:09,009
- Yes.
- This is the opposite.

2473
01:43:09,009 --> 01:43:10,199
I'm supposed to know nothing.

2474
01:43:10,199 --> 01:43:11,879
I thought they'd find it strange
if I suddenly cooked Chinese food.

2475
01:43:11,879 --> 01:43:13,751
[Menu selection considering her cover]
Right, she's an athlete.

2476
01:43:13,751 --> 01:43:15,079
That's true.

2477
01:43:15,079 --> 01:43:17,479
[Day 3 undercover: Staff meal challenge!]
- It's a Korean dish. - I see.

2478
01:43:17,479 --> 01:43:20,071
Okay, I'll prepare a dish.

2479
01:43:20,071 --> 01:43:22,759
[Hearing Sunny is making the staff meal,
the Prep station head...]

2480
01:43:22,759 --> 01:43:25,111
Prepare the ingredients Sunny needs.

2481
01:43:25,111 --> 01:43:28,039
Sunny is going to cook for us today.

2482
01:43:28,039 --> 01:43:29,191
The word is out.

2483
01:43:29,191 --> 01:43:30,759
- Later, Sunny will...
- Wow, the word is out.

2484
01:43:30,759 --> 01:43:32,327
- make Korean food.
- That's very...

2485
01:43:32,327 --> 01:43:35,607
[The kitchen's source of information]
He talks more than he looks.

2486
01:43:37,319 --> 01:43:41,095
[The news spreads everywhere]
Sunny bought the meat herself.

2487
01:43:41,095 --> 01:43:43,127
She's making Korean food for us.

2488
01:43:43,127 --> 01:43:45,415
Who bought the ingredients?

2489
01:43:45,415 --> 01:43:46,629
Sunny did.

2490
01:43:46,629 --> 01:43:49,439
[News of Sunny's staff meal spreads]
- Sunny bought it herself? - Yes.

2491
01:43:49,439 --> 01:43:51,119
She prepared a lot.

2492
01:43:52,295 --> 01:43:55,783
[Attention focuses on Sunny
thanks to the kitchen source]

2493
01:43:55,783 --> 01:43:57,943
What are you making?

2494
01:43:57,943 --> 01:43:59,447
I'm making beef bulgogi.

2495
01:43:59,447 --> 01:44:02,191
- Bulgogi?
- Yes, Korean-style bulgogi.

2496
01:44:02,855 --> 01:44:04,887
- Bulgogi.
- Bulgogi, bulgogi.

2497
01:44:04,887 --> 01:44:08,455
[Why Sunny chose beef bulgogi
for the staff meal?]

2498
01:44:08,455 --> 01:44:10,743
Do you have this vegetable in Korea?

2499
01:44:10,743 --> 01:44:12,151
Do you have Sichuan-style sausages
in Korea too?

2500
01:44:12,151 --> 01:44:13,666
We do, but they're a bit different.

2501
01:44:13,666 --> 01:44:16,711
What kind of dishes do you have in Korea?

2502
01:44:16,711 --> 01:44:18,167
What else is there?

2503
01:44:18,167 --> 01:44:20,743
Koreans eat rice cakes, right?

2504
01:44:20,743 --> 01:44:22,231
- You eat rice cakes, right?
- Yes, we do.

2505
01:44:22,231 --> 01:44:24,567
Do you have vegetables like this in Korea?

2506
01:44:24,567 --> 01:44:26,487
Yes, we do.

2507
01:44:26,487 --> 01:44:29,479
[They're so interested in Korean food...]

2508
01:44:29,479 --> 01:44:33,239
Have you ever been to a Korean restaurant here?

2509
01:44:33,239 --> 01:44:35,015
Have you ever tried it?

2510
01:44:35,015 --> 01:44:36,311
No?

2511
01:44:36,311 --> 01:44:37,559
You've never had Korean food?

2512
01:44:37,559 --> 01:44:41,029
Aren't there no Korean restaurants around here?

2513
01:44:41,029 --> 01:44:44,055
[So they've never had Korean food before?]

2514
01:44:44,055 --> 01:44:47,215
[The menu she chose after much thought]

2515
01:44:47,847 --> 01:44:49,649
[Beef bulgogi!]
Bulgogi.

2516
01:44:50,807 --> 01:44:53,255
[Beef bulgogi]

2517
01:44:53,255 --> 01:44:55,463
That sounds delicious.

2518
01:44:55,463 --> 01:44:57,575
It's a common dish.

2519
01:44:57,575 --> 01:45:00,487
I thought it'd be approachable,
so I went with that.

2520
01:45:00,487 --> 01:45:03,719
I chose something that Koreans love the most.

2521
01:45:03,719 --> 01:45:05,703
And soy sauce is also widely used in China.

2522
01:45:05,703 --> 01:45:07,703
[A soy sauce-based dish familiar to Chinese]
It's soy sauce-based.

2523
01:45:07,703 --> 01:45:09,943
I was wondering what to make...

2524
01:45:09,943 --> 01:45:14,069
[In Chengdu, the city of mala]

2525
01:45:14,069 --> 01:45:18,069
[Showcasing the taste of Korean beef bulgogi]
- This is bound to be good. - Of course.

2526
01:45:20,183 --> 01:45:26,183
[Can she aim for a promotion
to the Wok station?]

2527
01:45:27,159 --> 01:45:30,319
We'll get to have proper Korean bulgogi later!

2528
01:45:31,509 --> 01:45:35,735
[Shall we get started?]

2529
01:45:35,735 --> 01:45:38,663
[Concerned]

2530
01:45:38,663 --> 01:45:42,119
I'll need a lot to make enough.

2531
01:45:42,119 --> 01:45:45,287
I didn't have a sense of
how much I needed back then.

2532
01:45:45,287 --> 01:45:46,871
How many servings? Is it for 40 people?

2533
01:45:46,871 --> 01:45:48,711
- Right, how many people?
- Back then, about...

2534
01:45:48,711 --> 01:45:51,063
[Bulgogi for 40-50 people]
I think I made about 40 to 50 servings.

2535
01:45:51,063 --> 01:45:52,479
Wow, that's no joke.

2536
01:45:52,479 --> 01:45:56,727
[This massive banquet hall where Sunny is]

2537
01:45:56,727 --> 01:45:59,219
[Total number of restaurant staff]

2538
01:45:59,219 --> 01:46:00,455
[About 40 people]

2539
01:46:00,455 --> 01:46:03,029
- That's a lot.
- That's really a lot.

2540
01:46:03,029 --> 01:46:08,980
[She must prepare a large amount for 40 people]

2541
01:46:10,487 --> 01:46:12,423
How much lettuce do you need?

2542
01:46:12,423 --> 01:46:16,535
Onions, carrots, and garlic are enough.

2543
01:46:16,535 --> 01:46:18,887
How many onions do you need?

2544
01:46:18,887 --> 01:46:20,775
Six is enough.

2545
01:46:20,775 --> 01:46:22,791
This size is okay, right?

2546
01:46:22,791 --> 01:46:24,167
Yes, six.

2547
01:46:24,167 --> 01:46:26,559
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

2548
01:46:27,751 --> 01:46:29,639
[Carrots]
Thank you.

2549
01:46:29,639 --> 01:46:32,167
- Do you need this many leeks?
- Okay.

2550
01:46:32,167 --> 01:46:34,951
[Washing the leek leaves thoroughly]

2551
01:46:34,951 --> 01:46:36,679
[With the help of Prep station Head Tang Wei]
Thank you.

2552
01:46:36,679 --> 01:46:38,791
[Prep work is done!]

2553
01:46:38,791 --> 01:46:41,975
- The vibe here is really good.
- I know.

2554
01:46:41,975 --> 01:46:46,087
[10:26 AM, 30 minutes before lunch service]
[Chop chop chop]

2555
01:46:46,087 --> 01:46:48,807
[Chop chop chop]
Bulgogi isn't easy to make.

2556
01:46:49,751 --> 01:46:51,815
[A sound that catches everyone's attention?]

2557
01:46:51,815 --> 01:46:53,187
[Chop chop chop]

2558
01:46:53,187 --> 01:46:55,009
I just didn't care anymore.

2559
01:46:55,009 --> 01:46:57,431
- I didn't care anymore.
- You had to make 40 servings.

2560
01:46:57,431 --> 01:47:00,438
I had to chop it all myself, so I didn't care.

2561
01:47:00,438 --> 01:47:01,623
[What's this?]
Why is everyone...

2562
01:47:01,623 --> 01:47:03,015
- She suddenly got better.
- Her knife work suddenly...

2563
01:47:03,015 --> 01:47:05,415
[Am I seeing things?]
This is so weird.

2564
01:47:05,415 --> 01:47:08,535
Did she act like she couldn't chop before?

2565
01:47:08,535 --> 01:47:11,285
- She's busted.
- I forgot for a moment then.

2566
01:47:11,895 --> 01:47:13,807
[All eyes on her]

2567
01:47:16,423 --> 01:47:18,983
[Gasp...]

2568
01:47:18,983 --> 01:47:20,919
You're a pro!

2569
01:47:20,919 --> 01:47:21,975
What?

2570
01:47:21,975 --> 01:47:26,391
- You're a pro at Korean cooking.
- They think she's good because it's her own cuisine.

2571
01:47:26,391 --> 01:47:29,095
Your knife work is so fast!

2572
01:47:29,095 --> 01:47:31,351
Were you pretending to be bad earlier?

2573
01:47:31,351 --> 01:47:34,135
- Oh!
- He's sharp.

2574
01:47:34,135 --> 01:47:38,247
I finally got the hang of it.

2575
01:47:38,247 --> 01:47:39,559
[Puzzled]
He's sharp.

2576
01:47:39,559 --> 01:47:42,063
It's weird, it's weird.

2577
01:47:44,503 --> 01:47:47,969
[Mincing garlic so naturally]

2578
01:47:47,969 --> 01:47:49,575
[She has those skills too?]
She's busted.

2579
01:47:49,575 --> 01:47:50,839
- She's busted.
- It's all so weird.

2580
01:47:50,839 --> 01:47:53,207
- They're suspicious now.
- They're smiling, but it's weird.

2581
01:47:53,207 --> 01:47:56,311
- What? They're all like, "What?"
- What's going on?

2582
01:47:56,311 --> 01:47:58,709
From their perspective, it's strange.

2583
01:47:58,709 --> 01:48:01,639
"Oh, she's good because it's Korean food."

2584
01:48:01,639 --> 01:48:02,839
But this is weird.

2585
01:48:02,839 --> 01:48:04,439
- Her knife work is good for Korean food.
- But slicing is the same.

2586
01:48:04,439 --> 01:48:07,159
She's clumsy with Chinese food?
That makes no sense.

2587
01:48:07,159 --> 01:48:10,351
They must be very suspicious now.

2588
01:48:11,159 --> 01:48:12,807
[Busy prepping ingredients
regardless of their suspicion...]

2589
01:48:12,807 --> 01:48:14,103
Wow, look at the amount.

2590
01:48:14,103 --> 01:48:15,239
That's a lot.

2591
01:48:15,239 --> 01:48:17,463
[Sunny's excuse]
It was quite a large amount.

2592
01:48:17,463 --> 01:48:19,423
She's like a military cook.

2593
01:48:21,459 --> 01:48:23,095
[Glance]

2594
01:48:23,095 --> 01:48:24,759
Sunny, you slice so fast.

2595
01:48:24,759 --> 01:48:27,175
[Is that so?]

2596
01:48:27,175 --> 01:48:30,447
[Bringing the onions]

2597
01:48:31,239 --> 01:48:34,511
[Suspicions about Sunny continue to grow...]

2598
01:48:36,855 --> 01:48:39,879
[Whether she knows it or not...]
It's so uniform.

2599
01:48:39,879 --> 01:48:42,991
[Slicing even more excitedly]
Oh, boy.

2600
01:48:44,935 --> 01:48:47,287
I wasn't even paying attention then.

2601
01:48:47,287 --> 01:48:49,111
You're a total pro.

2602
01:48:49,111 --> 01:48:51,495
[Caught you, Sunny]
You're a pro.

2603
01:48:51,495 --> 01:48:52,599
You're a total pro.

2604
01:48:52,599 --> 01:48:55,767
- I just sliced without thinking.
- She gave up.

2605
01:48:55,767 --> 01:48:58,391
You're a master at knife work.

2606
01:48:58,391 --> 01:48:59,783
[Playing dumb...]

2607
01:48:59,783 --> 01:49:02,327
It turns out your knife work...

2608
01:49:02,327 --> 01:49:04,535
Your knife work is impressive!

2609
01:49:04,535 --> 01:49:07,991
- Is it?
- Now that he sees it, she's good.

2610
01:49:07,991 --> 01:49:11,639
She was amazing
when she was slicing for the Korean dish.

2611
01:49:11,639 --> 01:49:14,423
Her knife work was so skilled.
She sliced without hesitation!

2612
01:49:14,423 --> 01:49:17,407
She didn't seem like a beginner.

2613
01:49:18,167 --> 01:49:20,967
[It's suspicious no matter how I look at it...]

2614
01:49:20,967 --> 01:49:24,271
[Whether suspected of being a pro or not]

2615
01:49:25,159 --> 01:49:27,591
[Quickly finished prepping vegetables]
Oh, so she's going to stir-fry that herself?

2616
01:49:27,591 --> 01:49:29,767
Yes.

2617
01:49:29,767 --> 01:49:33,335
[Setting the prepped vegetables aside]

2618
01:49:33,335 --> 01:49:36,663
[Heading out to find the
most important ingredient...]

2619
01:49:36,663 --> 01:49:39,111
[Bringing in the meat bought earlier]

2620
01:49:39,111 --> 01:49:41,191
[What is that?]

2621
01:49:41,191 --> 01:49:43,695
[Thump]

2622
01:49:44,839 --> 01:49:46,807
What is this?

2623
01:49:46,807 --> 01:49:49,439
[Beef for bulgogi]
Oh, beef.

2624
01:49:49,439 --> 01:49:51,911
[Checking their reaction]
[There's more]

2625
01:49:51,911 --> 01:49:53,463
[Shocked]
What?

2626
01:49:53,463 --> 01:49:54,899
She really bought a lot!

2627
01:49:54,899 --> 01:49:56,007
It's enough, right?

2628
01:49:56,007 --> 01:49:57,511
[What's going on?]
It's too much.

2629
01:49:57,511 --> 01:49:59,366
Is it not enough?

2630
01:49:59,366 --> 01:50:00,464
Is it a lot?

2631
01:50:00,464 --> 01:50:02,103
This should be enough, right?

2632
01:50:02,103 --> 01:50:03,959
It's more than enough.

2633
01:50:03,959 --> 01:50:05,351
[One more pack]
[They're cracking up]

2634
01:50:05,351 --> 01:50:07,287
Isn't that way too much?

2635
01:50:07,287 --> 01:50:10,471
[Why did you buy so much...]

2636
01:50:10,471 --> 01:50:14,023
[Curiosity brings everyone over]

2637
01:50:14,023 --> 01:50:15,079
[Let's see too]

2638
01:50:15,079 --> 01:50:16,599
They're all gathered around.

2639
01:50:16,599 --> 01:50:17,895
It's enough.

2640
01:50:17,895 --> 01:50:19,303
[One lump]
Beef.

2641
01:50:19,303 --> 01:50:20,935
[Two lumps]
Is it enough?

2642
01:50:20,935 --> 01:50:22,023
[Three lumps]

2643
01:50:22,023 --> 01:50:23,223
No, but that's way too much.

2644
01:50:23,223 --> 01:50:25,255
It's too much. We can't eat it all.

2645
01:50:25,255 --> 01:50:26,951
You... can't eat all this?

2646
01:50:26,951 --> 01:50:28,167
Yes, yes.

2647
01:50:28,167 --> 01:50:32,135
- If you use all that meat...
- If I add vegetables to the meat...

2648
01:50:32,135 --> 01:50:34,648
- The dish will be...
- Is it enough?

2649
01:50:35,999 --> 01:50:37,607
It's too much.

2650
01:50:37,607 --> 01:50:39,351
[Massive]
How many kilos is that?

2651
01:50:39,351 --> 01:50:40,679
It looks like about 5kg.

2652
01:50:40,679 --> 01:50:42,739
I think it's about 5kg.

2653
01:50:42,739 --> 01:50:45,959
[By Sunny's standards]
That's about 40 to 50 servings.

2654
01:50:45,959 --> 01:50:47,463
She's a bit heavy-handed.

2655
01:50:47,463 --> 01:50:49,299
[40 servings... 8 to 9 large plates]
It filled about eight large plates...

2656
01:50:49,299 --> 01:50:50,951
nine plates.

2657
01:50:50,951 --> 01:50:53,943
- Thinking about that, I honestly...
- Is that a lot?

2658
01:50:53,943 --> 01:50:55,303
[Hard to gauge with so many people]
- Since there are many people... - Yes.

2659
01:50:55,303 --> 01:50:57,219
They're so surprised.

2660
01:50:57,219 --> 01:50:58,503
Are you sure it won't be short?

2661
01:50:58,503 --> 01:51:00,087
[Firm]
It won't be short.

2662
01:51:00,087 --> 01:51:01,495
Will it really be enough?

2663
01:51:01,495 --> 01:51:03,111
Of course it's enough.

2664
01:51:03,111 --> 01:51:04,567
We can't eat it all.

2665
01:51:04,567 --> 01:51:06,967
It's more than enough.

2666
01:51:06,967 --> 01:51:08,535
Okay, I understand!

2667
01:51:08,535 --> 01:51:10,711
You won't finish it! For sure.

2668
01:51:10,711 --> 01:51:11,975
Of course we can't finish it all!

2669
01:51:11,975 --> 01:51:13,495
- Half would be enough.
- They say half is enough.

2670
01:51:13,495 --> 01:51:16,535
- Even our boss isn't this generous.
- Right.

2671
01:51:16,535 --> 01:51:18,183
[Even in China,
Sunny is known for her scale...]

2672
01:51:18,183 --> 01:51:20,599
You have to admit,
Jung Ji Sun is really generous.

2673
01:51:20,599 --> 01:51:23,831
Can I use soy sauce and sugar?

2674
01:51:23,831 --> 01:51:27,047
[Now seasoning the bulgogi]
Yes, I'll get them ready.

2675
01:51:27,047 --> 01:51:28,975
[Pouring soy sauce]

2676
01:51:31,059 --> 01:51:32,327
Didn't you put in too much?

2677
01:51:32,327 --> 01:51:33,607
I think it'll be salty.

2678
01:51:33,607 --> 01:51:35,839
[Sugar]

2679
01:51:40,951 --> 01:51:42,775
Oh, you're adding sugar.

2680
01:51:42,775 --> 01:51:44,295
He's watching with great interest.

2681
01:51:44,295 --> 01:51:45,783
Everyone is watching with great interest.

2682
01:51:45,783 --> 01:51:49,663
[Everyone gathers as Sunny marinates the meat]
They must be so curious to taste it.

2683
01:51:50,455 --> 01:51:51,687
Do you need anything else?

2684
01:51:51,687 --> 01:51:53,223
[Everyone listening intently]
And also...

2685
01:51:53,223 --> 01:51:54,919
How many people are there?

2686
01:51:54,919 --> 01:51:57,419
They're really interested.

2687
01:51:59,199 --> 01:52:02,295
Pour it in! More! More! More!

2688
01:52:02,295 --> 01:52:03,671
[And then she adds oyster sauce...]

2689
01:52:03,671 --> 01:52:05,423
Oyster sauce too.

2690
01:52:06,279 --> 01:52:08,967
[Catastrophe]

2691
01:52:08,967 --> 01:52:11,959
[Participating with one mind]
- What? - All together.

2692
01:52:11,959 --> 01:52:13,463
It's okay, it's okay.

2693
01:52:13,463 --> 01:52:16,183
Don't worry about it.

2694
01:52:16,183 --> 01:52:17,975
Oh, like that.

2695
01:52:17,975 --> 01:52:20,151
She's massaging the meat.

2696
01:52:20,151 --> 01:52:22,343
Massaging the meat.

2697
01:52:22,343 --> 01:52:25,175
[Finishing off with a meat massage?]

2698
01:52:25,175 --> 01:52:26,279
What are you going to do with this?

2699
01:52:26,279 --> 01:52:28,663
I'm going to stir-fry it in a wok!

2700
01:52:28,663 --> 01:52:30,687
- In a wok?
- Yes.

2701
01:52:31,527 --> 01:52:33,351
[Finally complete, bulk beef bulgogi]
- Done. - It's all done, right?

2702
01:52:33,351 --> 01:52:36,039
- Yes, it's all done.
- I'm so excited.

2703
01:52:36,039 --> 01:52:39,367
- It's bound to be delicious.
- That'll definitely be good.

2704
01:52:39,367 --> 01:52:42,919
[A little later]

2705
01:52:42,919 --> 01:52:45,223
There's too much meat to flip.

2706
01:52:45,223 --> 01:52:46,679
There's just too much.

2707
01:52:46,679 --> 01:52:48,423
The amount is too much,

2708
01:52:48,423 --> 01:52:49,927
so we should split it up.

2709
01:52:49,927 --> 01:52:52,247
It'll be too hard to fry all at once.

2710
01:52:52,247 --> 01:52:54,199
[Too much to stir-fry at once]
- It's too... - It's too much.

2711
01:52:54,199 --> 01:52:56,599
Right, it's too much.

2712
01:52:56,599 --> 01:52:59,175
Sunny has to do it, so leave it be.

2713
01:52:59,175 --> 01:53:00,871
Just watch Sunny do it.

2714
01:53:00,871 --> 01:53:02,807
Sunny can handle it herself.

2715
01:53:02,807 --> 01:53:06,407
[Sunny must make it all on her own]
This will make it easier to stir-fry.

2716
01:53:06,407 --> 01:53:08,447
It's so heavy.

2717
01:53:09,927 --> 01:53:11,911
[Will Sunny overcome this hurdle...]

2718
01:53:11,911 --> 01:53:13,383
[...and move on to the next level?]
Will it work?

2719
01:53:13,383 --> 01:53:15,849
Will this work?

2720
01:53:17,699 --> 01:53:20,979
[While everyone is worried...]

2721
01:53:20,979 --> 01:53:22,339
[A game-changing...]

2722
01:53:22,339 --> 01:53:24,423
[crucial moment]
Hold on.

2723
01:53:24,423 --> 01:53:25,687
[Only three days left]
In this restaurant,

2724
01:53:25,687 --> 01:53:28,423
[No more time to lose]
my goal is to serve my dish.

2725
01:53:28,423 --> 01:53:29,927
From the dinner service,

2726
01:53:29,927 --> 01:53:31,889
you'll be in the main section.

2727
01:53:31,889 --> 01:53:33,063
[Will Kwon finally enter the main zone?]
Okay.

2728
01:53:33,063 --> 01:53:34,727
Thank you for this opportunity.

2729
01:53:34,727 --> 01:53:36,839
[Give your all to every opportunity]

2730
01:53:36,839 --> 01:53:39,719
[Escaping junior status]
Hee Tae, come over here.

2731
01:53:41,059 --> 01:53:43,287
[Performance at the next level]
It was very good.

2732
01:53:43,287 --> 01:53:46,407
[Showing skills through the staff meal]

2733
01:53:46,407 --> 01:53:47,759
[Anything! No matter what! Must succeed!]

2734
01:53:47,759 --> 01:53:49,447
Is it salty?

2735
01:53:49,447 --> 01:53:52,503
[An incident that Kwon encountered!]

2736
01:53:52,503 --> 01:53:55,327
[Cook the perfect cod steak]
The seasoning is perfect.

2737
01:53:59,575 --> 01:54:02,311
I can't eat this cod steak.

2738
01:54:02,311 --> 01:54:04,551
It's too salty.

2739
01:54:04,551 --> 01:54:07,159
[Food returned?]
They say it's too salty to eat!

2740
01:54:07,159 --> 01:54:08,695
[A complaint as soon as he's promoted?]
The main section was so...

2741
01:54:08,695 --> 01:54:11,639
busy and hectic that everyone...

2742
01:54:11,639 --> 01:54:14,099
[What are we going to do...]

2743
01:54:14,099 --> 01:54:17,319
[The owner steps in herself?]

2744
01:54:17,319 --> 01:54:18,615
[Nervous]
This is a real emergency.

2745
01:54:18,615 --> 01:54:20,151
A complaint.

2746
01:54:20,151 --> 01:54:23,039
[Will Sung Jun overcome this crisis?]

2747
01:54:23,655 --> 01:54:25,303
[And...]

2748
01:54:25,303 --> 01:54:26,951
[Grooving to the beat!]

2749
01:54:26,951 --> 01:54:30,071
[Hee Tae is working hard at social life?]

2750
01:54:30,071 --> 01:54:32,983
Oh! How do you know English so well?

2751
01:54:32,983 --> 01:54:34,855
I studied in America.

2752
01:54:34,855 --> 01:54:37,279
So you weren't just a farmer?

2753
01:54:37,279 --> 01:54:38,855
[Dazed by unexpected questions]
It was already beyond repair.

2754
01:54:38,855 --> 01:54:41,294
- It's already over.
- No.

2755
01:54:41,294 --> 01:54:44,734
[Undercover Hee Tae's identity exposed?]
This is why you shouldn't lie.
